title: pumpcream parfait
directions: Combine pudding mix, sugar, spices in saucepan; add milk; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and mix in pumpkin.
Cover with plastic wrap or wax paper and chill.

title: cranberry christmas punch
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water. Stir in lemonade.
Add cold water and cranberry juice.
Place in large bowl (punch) with trays of ice cubes.
Pour punch over ice.
Slowly add the ginger ale.

title: cranberry-fig muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Adjust oven rack to above oven center. In a small saucepan, heat water to a rolling boil.
Stir in oat bran and remove from heat.
Continue stirring until smooth and free of lumps.
Set aside to cool for 5 minutes.
Stir milk and oil into oat mixture.
Beat egg whites with sugar just until foamy.
Stir in oat mixture.
Combine flour with baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg white mixture with figs and cranberries. Spoon batter into 12 (2 3/4-inch) muffin tins lined with paper baking cups.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Cover pork chops with sauce.
Place cover over baking dish.
Cook at 325° for 2 hours.
Turn chops once while baking.

title: pineapple velvet
directions: Dissolve gelatin using 1 1/2 cups water.
Chill until almost set.
Whip until light and fluffy.
Fold in whipped cream and pineapple.
Pour into serving dish and chill until firm.
Decorate with almonds.

title: crab rockefeller
directions: Mix all together.
Put in greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until hot (or put into individual baking dishes and bake about 15 minutes).

title: eggs for brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Remove crust from bread and line slices in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cheese over bread and spread crumbled bacon over cheese.
Beat together the rest of the ingredients and pour on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: finger food squash
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 minutes or until knife blade comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.

title: egg rolls
directions: One recipe makes 18 egg rolls, 2 makes 36 or 4 makes 72.
Just as easy to make a big batch and freeze cooked egg rolls for later.

title: homemade peanut butter candy
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar and salt in a large saucepan (3 quart size).
Add milk gradually; mix thoroughly and bring to a bubbly boil on high heat, stirring continuously.
Reduce heat to medium and continue to boil the mixture without stirring until it reaches a temperature of 232° or until a small amount of mixture forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water.
(Be sure bulb of thermometer is not resting on bottom of saucepan.)
Remove saucepan from heat; add butter and vanilla to mixture.
Do not stir.
Allow candy to cool at room temperature until it reaches 110°.

title: charlotte russe
directions: Whip the cream until stiff; add vanilla and sugar, also sherry to taste.
Soften gelatin in cold milk, then dissolve in warm milk.
When cool, add to above mixture, beating the cream all of the time.
Add beaten egg whites.
Pour in bowl or dessert glasses lined with ladyfingers.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Bring tomato soup and cream cheese to a boil.
Add gelatine; take off burner.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir up, then refrigerate for a good long time.
Serve with crackers.
Recipe can be doubled for large amount.

title: crock-pot corn
directions: Melt the margarine and cream cheese in microwave while cooking corn according to directions on bag. Drain corn and stir margarine mixture into corn.
Add sugar.
Put in crock-pot and cook for 4 hours.
You can let this simmer on top of the stove if you prefer.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bacon. Shape into loaf. Lay bacon strips across top of loaf. Bake at
375° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serve with roasted potatoes.

title: champ's chicken
directions: Stew the vegetables, mushrooms and onions in a small amount of water.
Mix the chicken and eggs together.
Drain the vegetable mixture from the water and add to the chicken and eggs.
Stir mixture in a nonstick frying pan (Pam spray works well).
Add cheese; blend well.
Serve over rice.
Makes 2 servings.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Break tortillas into bite size pieces.
Line flat casserole with them.
Add layer of chicken, layer of mixture, layer of tortilla bits, chicken and mixture.
Top with 2 cups grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 60 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Lay rolls flat and pinch together on large, greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350° or until browned lightly. Cool.

title: jewel cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs. Sift flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, allspice and cloves together; add, then beat. Fold in gumdrops, nuts and dates. Shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper; chill. Cut into 1/4 inch slices or freeze, then slice. Place on a greased cookie sheet. Bake 7 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven. Yields about 6 dozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, milk, Parmesan cheese, onion and sour cream.
Stir in chicken and zucchini.
Add spaghetti; toss gently to coat.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart dish or casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbling.
Serve with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.
Makes about 4 cups.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine together; beat in egg.
Sift flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and cloves together.
Stir in nuts and raisins. Puree persimmon pulp until smooth and stir in baking soda.
Add persimmon mixture and dry ingredients alternately to creamed margarine and sugar mixture, mixing well after each addition. Drop by heaping teaspoonful on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat eggs; blend in bananas.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with creamed mixture.
Place in loaf pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown and crumble bacon, hamburger and onion. Drain beans (reserve juices) and combine with meat. Add rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or longer.

title: hot cheese loaf
directions: Slice top off bread and scoop out center. Combine all remaining ingredients. Fill hollowed loaf with cheese mixture. Replace top of bread and wrap in foil. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with bread that was removed and bread can be pinched off of loaf and dipped in cheese mixture.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
On bottom of casserole dish, put drained hamburger, then cheese.
Next add the Tater Tots.
Mix the soup with the water and pour over the potatoes.
Bake at 375° uncovered for 35 minutes.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix together, stir and put in plastic bowl.
Let set for 6 days, then freeze.

title: hamburger and rice
directions: Put 1 cup raw rice in bottom of baking dish.
Brown hamburger along with onions and mushrooms.
Layer pats of margarine over raw rice and salt and pepper.
Pour hamburger mixture over rice and then pour on 1 cup broth, adding a little water if needed to cover rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: barbecued franks and noodles(heart healthy)
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and pour into baking dish.
Arrange hot dogs over noodles.
Prick hot dogs. Cook onion in oil for 10 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over hot dogs and noodles.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Cook altogether (20 to 30 minutes).
Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1 cup milk together and pour slowly into other ingredients. Add 1/2 pound Velveeta cheese, cubed.
Turn off heat and let cheese melt.
Serve.

title: creamed chicken on corn bread ring
directions: Melt chicken fat.
Add flour and seasonings and stir over low heat until blended.
Add cold stock and milk together.
Stir and cook over low heat until thickened.
Add chicken; heat thoroughly. Add more seasonings, if desired.
Serve piping hot.

title: apple smiles
directions: Spread one side of each apple slice with peanut butter.
Place 3 or 4 marshmallows on top of another slice.
Place second slice of apple, peanut butter side down, on top of marshmallows; press gently.

title: lo-fat spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.
Makes 4 cups.

title: soda cracker pie(mock apple pie)
directions: Bring to a
boil.
Prepare
pie
crust for double crust pie. Into
unbaked
pie	crust,	crumble
soda
crackers. Sprinkle cinnamon or
nutmeg,
add pats of butter.
Pour sugar water combination over crackers.	Add top crust.	Bake at 425° for 15 minutes or until crust is done.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare vegetables according to package directions.
Drain.
In a pan, heat soup, cream cheese and Cheddar cheese until sauce is smooth and cheese melted.
Combine vegetables and sauce.
Add mushrooms and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place corn flakes and spices in plastic storage bag and crush with rolling pin. Sprinkle crushed flakes over top of casserole and drizzle with melted margarine.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: icebox bran muffins
directions: Place bran in large bowl; pour the water and buttermilk over bran and mix.
Add salt, sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Add raisins, dates and nuts; mix well again.
Add flour and soda and mix thoroughly.
Close and cover tightly and store in refrigerator.
Will keep in fridge for 6 to 8 weeks.
When you want muffins, fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Boil cabbage in salted water until very tender; drain.
Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add cheese and cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Add soup and water and blend in well, over low heat; add cabbage and mix well.
Add bread crumbs until mixture is desired consistency; stir in salt and pepper.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish; sprinkle with remaining bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly hot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Crush 1 package of Ritz crackers and put on top. Cut up 1 stick of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: party casserole
directions: Mix dressing with melted margarine.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan put 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over dressing.
Spread rest of dressing on top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: low-fat pumpkin bread
directions: Combine ingredients and beat until smooth.
Pour into 3 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with Dream Whip.

title: italian macaroons
directions: Line aluminum foil on your cookie sheet.
Work the almond paste with your hands.
Then add sugar and egg whites.
Constantly knead.
Now add flour and powdered sugar.
Now add fruit.
Place 1/2 teaspoon of mix on the lined aluminum foil cookie sheet until all the mix is used.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Next day bake at 300° 25 to 30 minutes.
Decorate each cookie with a bright red cherry or green citron.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk and yeast.
Stir with fork.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
This mixture will keep in refrigerator for about 1 week.
Bake at 375° for about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add bananas and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Add alternately with buttermilk. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
(Raisins and/or dates may be added with nuts just before putting in pan.)

title: banana cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Cream Crisco and add sugar in separate bowl.
Cream until very light; beat in, one at a time, 2 eggs.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Mix, then add flour mixture in 3 parts, alternating with thirds of the banana mixture.

Stir batter after each addition until smooth. Bake in greased tube pan 45 to 50 minutes or 2 (8-inch) round pans for 25 minutes, or sheet cake pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Cool 1/2 hour or so before removing cake.

title: veal marsala
directions: Pound cutlets very thin.
Cut into pieces 6 inches square. Sprinkle with salt and pepper; flour lightly.
Melt butter in large frypan.
When hot, put veal in and brown through on both sides over high heat.
When well browned, add Marsala (keep flame high).
Let meat cook 1 minute longer.
Place meat in serving dish.
Add stock or water to pan, scraping bottom and sides, and pour over meat.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and rice.
Pour into baking dish. Cover with chicken breasts and sprinkle soup mix over top. Cover with foil and bake about 2 hours at 350° or until chicken is tender. Remove foil and brown.

title: diabetic - cheese appetizers
directions: Blend cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add flour, onion, salt and pepper; stir until smooth.
Shape dough into a roll, 1 1/4 inches in diameter.
Wrap in plastic wrap or aluminum foil. Chill.
Cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes. Yields 24 servings.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together; add to hot water to taste.

title: reuben casserole
directions: In a greased casserole, layer all ingredients.
Pour melted margarine over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: jalapeno black-eyed pea and rice casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter until tender.
Add ground beef and brown.
Stir in black-eyed peas, rice and tomatoes.
Mix well. Spoon mixture into a 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serves 6 to 8.
Double recipe for larger servings.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and flavoring.
Sift dry ingredients and add.
Mix in nuts.
Chill 2 hours.
Roll into small balls. Lightly press down on ungreased cookie sheet (not too flat).
Bake at 350° until set (not brown), 7 to 9 minutes. Roll into sifted powdered sugar while still warm, then again after they have cooled.
Store in tight containers.
They freeze well.

title: plantation salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand 24 hours before serving.

title: pickled corn
directions: Boil corn-on-cob 10 minutes.
Cut and scrape corn from cob when cooled; pack loosely in jar.
Pour vinegar mixture over corn. Makes approximately 15 quarts.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until almost done. Drain and combine with next 6 ingredients.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Top with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: old fashioned chocolate pudding with sauce
directions: Heat bread crumbs, sugar, egg, milk and chocolate, stirring until thick and thoroughly mixed.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: custard pie
directions: Bake pie crust in a 450° oven for 5 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake(fast and easy)
directions: Place sugar and flour together in large bowl.
Bring margarine, cocoa and water to a rapid boil in a saucepan.
Pour over flour and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour batter into a greased 16 x 11-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: taco chicken
directions: Mix soup, chili sauce, water and hot pepper sauce.
Dust chicken with flour; dip in soup mixture.
Roll in chips.
Place on rack in shallow baking pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Mix butter and cheese at room temperature.
Add balance of ingredients and mix.
Shape into sausage shaped roll, about 2-inches in diameter.
Wrap in wax paper and chill.
You can freeze at this point.
Slice 1/4-inch thick slices (as for icebox cookies).
Bake in 375° oven on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields about 40 wafers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.

title: baked eggs
directions: Butter casserole, layer chilies, cheese, eggs and sprinkle with seasoned salt and flour.
Repeat with second layer and dot each layer with butter.

title: stove top stuffing meat loaf
directions: Mix meat, onion, peppers and egg(s).
Mix small package first, then bread crumbs.
Mix in tomato sauce.
Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lime dill dressing
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except olive oil.
Add oil in a steady stream, whisking or blending until thoroughly combined. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Makes 1/2 cup.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; add crabmeat last. Save 1/2 of Cheddar cheese for top. Put in casserole dish. Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Combine buttermilk, parsley, onion, garlic and Blue cheese. Add mayonnaise.
Mix through.
Add seasonings to taste.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Add cubes to boiling water until dissolved.
Add lemon, onion and cream cheese. Beat until smooth.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Slowly brown chicken in 1/4 cup hot olive oil; remove from skillet.
Add onions and garlic; cook until tender, but not brown. Combine remaining ingredients, except cooking wine.
Add chicken to skillet; pour sauce over.
Cover; simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in cooking wine.
Cook, uncovered, turning chicken occasionally, about 20 minutes or until chicken is tender and sauce is thick.
Skim off excess fat and remove bay leaves.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together in a large bowl granulated sugar, brown sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Combine, in a second bowl, flour, salt and baking soda. Add dry ingredients gradually to the creamed mixture, mixing with a wooden spoon.
Stir in chocolate chips, using a wooden spoon.

title: one dish salad supper
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Serves 6 to 8.

title: washington apple cake
directions: Cream together sugar and corn oil.
Add eggs, one at a time and vanilla.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add dry mixture to apples and nuts.
Add creamed mixture.
Batter will be thick (a stiff doughy mixture).
Bake in greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Stir first 7 ingredients together and set aside.
Boil remaining ingredients and let cool; pour over the other mixture. Cover and chill for 24 hours.
Drain and serve.
You may use 2 cans of French-style green beans if you need more salad.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with rice.
Add dry soup mix and stir.
Place 4 to 6 chicken breasts on top of rice.
Combine chicken broth, cream of mushroom soup and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: krackle krackers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet; cover with crackers.
Boil sugar and butter 2 to 3 minutes.
Spread sugar mix over crackers.
Bake until bubbly, plus 1 to 2 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and drizzle over top.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.
Break into chunks.
Store in covered containers in cool, dry place.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Empty 1 can of beans into a 1 1/2-quart casserole; combine brown sugar and mustard.
Sprinkle half of mixture over beans. Top with second can of beans; sprinkle with remaining brown sugar mixture and the cut bacon.
Spread catsup over all.
Arrange 3 or 4 more bacon slices on top, if desired.
Cook, uncovered, over slow coals about 1 hour on grill, or bake 1 hour, uncovered, in 350° oven, or a bit longer.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix eggs, milk and mustard.
Layer bread, sausage and cheese in 11 x 13-inch pan.
Pour egg and milk mixture over layers.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add zucchini, vanilla, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon and flour.
Blend well.
Add nuts.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir sugar and syrup together.
Heat 5 to 6 minutes in a small microwave.
Stir in peanuts.
Heat for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring after 2 or 2 1/2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla to syrup, blending well.
Heat for 2 or 3 minutes. Peanuts will be slightly browned and syrup very hot.
Add soda and stir gently until light and foamy.
Pour mixture onto lightly buttered cookie sheet.
Cool for 1 hour.
When cool, break into small pieces and store in airtight container.
Ziploc bag is the best to store the candy in.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in water to cover with onion until tender with salt added. Cool chicken (save broth). Remove bones and skin (discard). Cut chicken into small pieces. Melt butter in saucepan. Stir in flour. Add 4 cups liquid (juice from mushrooms and broth) and evaporated milk. Cook and stir until sauce is thick and smooth. Add 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, turmeric and oregano. Spread rice in bottom of pan; top with chicken, onions, sauce and mushrooms. Sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, sugar and salt altogether.
Mix egg, buttermilk and shortening; add to dry mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight (if you wish).

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; stir into sugar mixture just until blended.
Stir in bananas, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about one hour or until center is firm.
Cool about 5 minutes in pan, then onto wire rack.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa, then add milk and mix well.
Cook slowly and stir until dissolved.
After dissolved, do not stir.
Cook until a small amount will form a soft-ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
Set pan in sink of cold water and stir until thick.
Put on greased platter.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Beat milk, egg, vanilla and margarine until blended.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to egg mixture and beat well.
Beat additional 1 minute at high speed.
Stir in raisins.
Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Drop by heaping teaspoons on lightly greased sheet.
Bake at 350° in oven for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool 1 minute. Remove from sheets.
Store tightly covered.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 tablespoons per 8 ounces hot water.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and blend. Gradually add flour; blend thoroughly.
Mix nuts and apples into batter.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine ingredients in a bowl and spread a thin layer over tortillas.
Roll up tortillas tightly and roll in wax paper. Chill for several hours or overnight.
When ready to serve, slice tortillas and serve with picante sauce.

title: date nut bread
directions: Dredge all fruit and nuts in the cup flour.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat eggs and brown sugar.
Add flour mixture to brown sugar and egg mixture.
Add nuts and fruit mixture.
Mix. Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breakfast dish
directions: Brown sausage and crumble.
Mix with cream cheese.
Spread bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with one package of crescent rolls.
Pour cheese and sausage over this and top with remaining package of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Line cookie sheet with waxed paper.
Melt butterscotch and milk chocolate chips.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls.
Chill until set.
Makes 4 dozen.
Yummy!!

title: hard soap
directions: Mix Borax and lye together.
When dissolved and cooled, add melted grease.
Stir well, then add ammonia.
Stir again until it thickens.
Let stand until morning, then cut in squares.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients with rotary beater.
Mix well; add pecans.
Pour into 9-inch pastry lined pan.
Bake until set and pastry is nicely browned at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes. Serve cold or slightly warm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: kroppkakor (potato dumplings)
directions: Cut pork steak in small pieces.
Add onion, small amount of salt and the allspice.

title: crab salad
directions: Trim crust off bread and butter slices.
Cut into cubes.
Mix bread cubes with onion and eggs.
Set overnight in refrigerator. Four hours before serving, add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Drop by teaspoon onto baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine in large mixing bowl: Crisco, sugar, eggs and cold water until well mixed.
Add to mixture: flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add mashed bananas.
Pour mixture into two greased and floured loaf pans.
Cook 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool approximately 30 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese dip
directions: I use a hand grinder and grind the cheese and peppers fine. Mix with the mayonnaise.
Let set overnight for better flavor and bite.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients well.
Sprinkle nuts over top.
Serve chilled.

title: hamburger kidney bean casserole
directions: Press raw hamburger in
the
bottom of a 3 quart casserole; sprinkle with salt
and pepper.
Layer the can of kidney beans with juice next
and
sprinkle
with
chili powder.
Add chopped onion in a
layer.
Layer the top with sliced potatoes with salt, pepper and
sugar
over
the
top.
Pour
undrained chopped tomatoes over the
top.
Bake,
covered,
in 400° oven for 1 hour. Remove lid
and bake another 20 minutes to remove excess liquid.

title: microwave southern barbecued ribs
directions: In oblong baking dish, arrange ribs, meaty side down.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over ribs.
Cover with wax paper.
Heat at High 10 minutes and at Medium-low 25 to 30 minutes, or until ribs are tender.
Halfway through heating, turn ribs over; rearrange.
Spoon sauce over ribs.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cherry bars
directions: Mix together butter, shortening, sugar, vanilla, eggs, flour and salt.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan (save 1/4 of batter to put on top).
Stir almond extract into cherry pie filling.
Spread over crust and top with spoonfuls of reserved batter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: cucumber dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender; shake well before serving.

title: easy chicken tetrazzini
directions: Boil noodles in salted water for 8 minutes.
Combine noodles, soup, cheese, mushrooms and chicken in a bowl.
Stir in sour cream.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry nut salad
directions: Drain all juices; dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Fold in remaining ingredients, except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a large dish and chill until firm.
Spread top with sour cream. Add other half of ingredients and return to refrigerator until firm.

title: french creams
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and egg.
Press into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, cheese, eggs and almond extract.
Mix and pour over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern sweet potato bread
directions: Grease pan.
Cream butter; add brown sugar and beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, sweet potatoes, milk and orange rind.
Beat with mixer until thoroughly combined.
Add flour, nutmeg and allspice to sweet potato mixture with nuts.
Mix thoroughly until smooth.
Turn batter into prepared pan.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove to cake rack.
Cool before slicing.

title: green rice casserole
directions: In melted margarine, saute chopped onions and chopped celery. Mix together with broccoli, mushroom soup, Cheez Whiz and rice. Regular rice works better than Minute rice.
Put in 8 x 8-inch glass baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together oil, sugar and eggs, mixing well.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Beat together with sugar mixture.
Stir in vanilla mixing well.
Add carrots, nuts, coconut and pineapple.
Pour into well greased and floured 10 inch Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour. Cover with cream cheese frosting.

title: easy chicken paprika
directions: In skillet, in 1 tablespoon hot margarine, cook chicken for 10 minutes, or until browned on both sides.
Remove.
In skillet, combine soup, sour cream, paprika and pepper; heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet.
Cover; cook over heat for 5 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir often.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: peanut butter balls(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in coconut or whatever.

title: pintos and posole (hominy)
directions: Soak hominy overnight.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low about 6 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat in together margarine and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light golden brown.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: cheesy brat stew
directions: In 3-quart casserole, stir together bratwurst or Polish sausage, potatoes, green beans, cream of mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese and onion.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in fat until golden brown.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper.
Brown beef; drain.
Add drained green peas, beaten egg and tomato soup.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Mash the potatoes.
Add milk, margarine, salt and pepper (the same way you would eat creamed potatoes by themselves).
Spoon into mounds over meat.
Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad and rolls.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Cover cucumbers in salt; let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze all juice from cucumbers.
Add onion, sour cream and vinegar.
Add pepper. Yields 4 servings.

title: uncle george's clam chowder
directions: Wash clams thoroughly in fresh water to remove sand.
Just cover clams with water.
Steam clams until they open (15 minutes). Remove clams from shells.
Chop clams.
Set aside clams.
Saute onions and salt pork with butter in pan.
Add all ingredients except clams to clam water used for steaming.
Add more water if necessary, slow boil 8 to 10 minutes then add clams.
Cook 2 to 5 minutes.
Makes 6 to 12 servings.

title: old fashion corn pone(from macel thorpe of richwood)
directions: Place meal, sugar and salt in a bowl; add boiling water to make a smooth paste.
Let stand overnight.
In the morning, add flour, buttermilk, eggs and baking powder.
Dissolve soda in a small amount of water and add butter.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into well-greased iron skillet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and turn upside down to cool.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Saute garlic, celery and onions with beef for 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, sauce, spices, seasonings, monosodium glutamate, chili peppers, sugar and beans.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese balls
directions: Set cream cheese out to soften.
Mince onion and green pepper very fine.
Squeeze out all water.
Mix cream cheese, drained pineapple, onion, green pepper and grated cheese.
Add seasoned salt to taste (1 1/2 tablespoons).
Roll into 2 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, cheese and pepper.
Fold in 1 cup marinara sauce. With wet hands, pat mixture firmly into 8 x 4-inch loaf pan, pour remaining sauce over loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 6 servings.

title: peanut butter chocolate bars
directions: Cream peanut butter and butter.
Add sugar, vanilla, eggs (one at a time) and flour.
Mix in 1 cup of chocolate chips.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle remaining chips on top after removal from oven.
Smooth chocolate; let cool 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Enjoy!

title: blueberry bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Blend all ingredients except berries in a food processor.
Fold in the berries as you pour the batter. Grease a 12 muffin pan and pour in batter.
Bake about 20 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to package directions.
Add pineapple juice and Sprite or ginger ale.
Finish filling container with water.
Makes 2 1/2 gallons.

title: cauliflower salad bowl
directions: In a large bowl, combine cauliflower, olives, green pepper, pimento and onion.
Mix well.
In another mixing bowl, combine oil, lemon juice, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix well. Pour oil mixture over vegetable mixture.
Toss to coat vegetables. Refrigerate, covered, 4 hours or overnight.
To serve, spoon vegetable mixture into a salad bowl lined with lettuce leaves.

title: easy cheesy casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order listed except the cheese. Pour into well-greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: sugar-free one layer yellow cake
directions: Mix sugar-free pudding according to directions.
Let set. Spoon all of pudding between the 2 layers of cake.
Top with Chocolate Sauce and sliced almonds.

title: potato cheese bake
directions: Peel potatoes and boil for 1/2 hour.
Cut or slice potatoes and place them into a baking dish.
Break bread into small pieces and place on top of potatoes.
Add all remaining ingredients and bake for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Blend pepper and vinegar.
Let cook until mixed.
Add sugar slowly, stirring until all is added.
Let come to a rolling boil. Add Sure-Jell and food color.
Pour into jelly jars and seal.

title: recycled cake
directions: Prepare pudding; let set until firm.
Break cake into bite size pieces.
Combine pudding and cake.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: hot bean dip
directions: Put all ingredients except bacon in a blender.
Cover and run on high until smooth.
Serve hot. Crumble bacon over top.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Pour in a big floured bread pan.
Bake about 25 minutes.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Place all wet ingredients into a plastic container.
Stir in all dry ingredients.
Soak chicken, skin side up, 12 to 24 hours. Char-broil.

title: new england chowder
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Saute next 3 ingredients until tender.
Put potatoes in small saucepan with chicken broth and cook until barely done.
After celery, onion and pepper are tender, add flour and stir until roux has formed.
Then gradually add milk, stirring constantly until thickened and smooth.
Add clam juice, watching closely not to burn.
Add clams, potatoes, broth and seasoning and simmer 10 minutes more.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine potatoes and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients; add to potato mixture.
Drop by tablespoons onto greased skillet

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Grease 2-quart mold.
Combine all ingredients as listed.
Mix only until all ingredients are well coated (by hand is best). Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: angi's rabbit stew
directions: Boil rabbits in salt water for 10 minutes.
Remove rabbits and discard water.
Again cover rabbits with salted water, and simmer until meat
is tender.
Retain 2 c. broth.
Remove rabbit, drain, and cool.
Remove meat from bone, and cut into bite-size pieces.
In dutch oven, add broth, meat, vegetables, tomato sauce, salt, and pepper.
Bring to boil, and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Thicken with cornstarch and cold water mix.

title: pecan pie
directions: Bake in preheated 425° oven for 10 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° and bake for 45 to 55 minutes more until filling is firm.

title: caesar salad
directions: Using a food processor fitted with metal blade or a wire whisk, combine garlic, olive oil, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, Scramblers, lemon juice, wine vinegar and Parmesan cheese.
Combine until smooth.

title: chicken with pasta
directions: Saute chicken breasts in 2 tablespoons of oil until almost done. Add sliced peppers and garlic to chicken.
Cook until tender.
Add sauce, olives, chicken broth, rosemary and thyme. Mix.
Cooked pasta can now be added to mixture.
Heat through.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients, except oil, in blender on low speed for 5 seconds. Remove lid and add oil slowly until all ingredients are blended. Refrigerate. Serve over greens, avocado, citrus sections or shrimp. Makes 1 cup.

title: ranch beans
directions: Combine beans and bacon.
Combine remaining ingredients, and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pour over beans, and mix.
Bake 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt milly's blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400° (moderate hot).
Grease bottom of muffin cups or use paper baking cups.
Beat egg with fork.
Stir in milk and oil.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Stir in flour until moistened.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Blend in one cup of well-drained blueberries before filling cups.
Makes 12 muffins or 8 small muffins.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, oil and margarine together.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add vanilla, lemon extract and dry ingredients; mix well.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Shape dough into small balls.
Wet bottom of glass; dip in sugar and press balls down.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet until brown, about 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced apple corn fritters
directions: In a deep-fryer or heavy saucepan, heat 4 inches of vegetable oil to 350°.
In a mixer with dough hooks, beat together the corn, egg, baking powder, salt and sugar on medium speed.
This can be done by hand.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Debone cooked chicken and cube.
Mix together chicken, sour cream and soup.
Add seasoning to taste.
Add salsa, if desired. Fill tortilla shell; roll and place in greased pan.
Repeat with remaining mixture and shells.
Pour tomato sauce over rolled shells.
Top with grated cheese.
Heat about 20 minutes to melt cheese in 350° oven.
If desired, garnish with tomatoes, avocados and olives on top.

title: uncle frank's steak and noodles
directions: In a large skillet brown the steak and cut up into small bite size pieces.
Add the onions chopped into small pieces, add 1 teaspoon salt and cook until the steak is done.

title: nana's chiffon cake
directions: Break the six eggs and put whites into a bowl and set aside. In large bowl, mix the flour, sugar, egg yolks, extracts, oil and water.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until peaks form.
Gently fold batter into egg whites.
Pour into ungreased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Cool upside down in pan for 2 to 3 hours.
After cooled, scrape around side and bottom of pan and turn cake out.
Serve with any fruit or ice cream or just plain.

title: country style cabbage
directions: Saute onions in margarine in a large skillet until tender. Add green pepper.
Cover and cook 5 minutes over low heat. Arrange cabbage and tomatoes over onion mixture.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and egg.
Mix flour, soda, salt and cinnamon together and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Mix in apples, vanilla, coffee and nuts.
Beat well.
Pour in lightly greased pie pan and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes, 325° for glass pie plate.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo until tender.
Add other ingredients except cheese and mix well.
Top with cheese and bake in 300° oven for 25 minutes.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat sugar with eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add milk, beating well.
Add Eagle Brand milk and vanilla, beating well.
Fruit can be added such as a pound of strawberries or a pint of finely chopped fresh peaches.
If frozen fruit is used, thaw prior to adding to mix.
Freeze as usual in a one gallon freezer bowl.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Melt margarine in 11 x 14-inch pan.
Spread rice over margarine.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Pour water and broth over all and bake covered 2 hours at 300°.
Cooked and boned chicken can be used.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Sprinkle with nuts.
Coconut and cherries can be added.
Store in refrigerator night before serving.

title: spice cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and soda.
Sift in flour and cinnamon.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° to 400° oven.

title: no name cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake in a Bundt pan (spray with Pam) at 350° for 1 hour.
If baked in a 9 x 12 x 2-inch pan, may take less time.

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in buttered casserole dish.

title: guacamole
directions: Peel avocados and remove seeds.
Cut lengthwise into slices. Finely dice slices to make about 3 cups.
Put 1 cup cubed avocado, 1/2 cup onion and half of lime juice into blender and puree. Scrape into bowl and add remaining avocado, chopped onion, tomato and chopped chilies.
Add more lime juice if desired.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir to blend.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach and potato in broth
directions: In large saucepan, gently brown garlic in olive oil.
Add to pot: broth, water and potato.
Add spinach.
Cover and cook 15 minutes.
Goes great with pork or chicken.
Delicious.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Mix dressing and red pepper in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: no-bake banana cake
directions: Break the angel food cake into small pieces.
Place about 1/3 of the cake in a rinsed 1 1/2-quart mold.
Make banana pudding according to directions.
Fold sliced bananas in pudding, then fold pudding with whipped topping (reserving enough to top each slice of cake).
Spoon some of the pudding mixture over the cake, alternating pudding and cake pieces until the mold is filled. Chill in refrigerator overnight if possible.
When ready to serve, unmold on cake plate and cut in slices.
Top each slice with whipped topping.

title: stuffed baked sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Cut a 1-inch lengthwise strip from top of each sweet potato.
Carefully scoop pulp from shells.
Combine sweet potato pulp, orange juice, margarine and salt.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in pineapple.
Stuff shells with potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Slice zucchini very thin (end to end).
Combine in bowl the cream cheese, cottage cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper. Brown hamburger; add spices and tomato sauce.

title: pickled beets
directions: Make a syrup of 1 cup liquid drained from beets, sugar, vinegar and spices.
When it comes to boil, add sliced, drained beets and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cocoa cake
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift 3 times with soda, salt and cocoa.
Cream shortening until soft.
Add sugar and blend thoroughly.
Add beaten eggs and beat vigorously until smooth and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla.
Add flour mixture.
Bake in cake pans at 350° until cake springs back at the touch.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil an 8-inch square baking dish.
Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes, or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.
Serve warm, and if desired, with vanilla ice milk, vanilla yogurt, or yogurt dessert sauce.
Makes 4-6 servings.
(double recipe - use a 9 x 13-inch baking dish).

title: creamy dutch apple dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, mix together milk, sour cream and lemon juice.
Spread evenly over crust.
Spoon pie filling over creamy layer.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until set. Cool slightly.
In small dish, mix nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
May be served hot or cold.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend pudding, pineapple (do not drain), marshmallows and nuts, then fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir first 5 ingredients until well blended. Stir in nuts; pour into shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients except soda over low heat until nuts turn brown. Remove from heat and add soda. Stir quickly and spread on buttered baking sheet. Break into pieces when cold.

title: microwave asparagus with orange mayonnaise(serves 6; has 30 calories per serving)
directions: Wash asparagus and break off woody bases.
Arrange asparagus in a shallow baking dish with the tips facing the center.
Add the water.
Cover with vented clear plastic wrap.
Cook on 100% power (High) for 7 to 9 minutes (8 to 10 minutes in low wattage oven) or until asparagus is tender, rearranging once.
Drain.

title: chunky chocolate chip, nut raisin cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix everything except raisins, nuts and chips. Now add raisins, nuts and chips.
Place cookies on ungreased tin. Preheat oven to 375.
Bake cookies 9 to 11 minutes.
Remove from tins and cool.
Makes 10 dozen cookies.

title: watermelon rind hors d'oeuvre
directions: Cut the watermelon rind pickles into 4 pieces each.
Cook the bacon until fatty and soft, drain.
Wrap the bacon around the watermelon rind pieces and secure with toothpicks.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot. May do the first part ahead and refrigerate to bake later.

title: miami heat chili
directions: In a Dutch oven or a large saucepot, heat 2 teaspoons oil until hot.
Add meat, a few pieces at a time.
Cook and stir until browned on all sides.
Remove to a plate.
Repeat until all meat is browned.
Heat remaining 3 teaspoons oil until hot.
Add chili powder, cumin, garlic, oregano, paprika and red and black peppers. Cook and stir 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in tomato sauce, beer, water and reserved meat.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, until meat is tender, about 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Serve with cooked pinto beans, chopped onions, jalapeno peppers and grated Cheddar cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese casserole bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add milk, 2 eggs, salt and 1 cup of flour.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl constantly, 30 seconds.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in remaining flour, cheese and pepper. Scrape bowl; cover and let rise in a warm place until double, about 40 minutes.

title: juicy hamburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients; form into patties and broil 4 minutes on each side.

title: banana-pineapple pound cake
directions: Preheat oven 350°.
Spray a tube pan and set aside.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt and soda.
Add bananas, pineapple and juice, vanilla, eggs and oil.
Blend well with spoon.
DO NOT OVERBEAT!
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: quick and easy fudge
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium saucepan. Bring to boil on high heat. Lower temperature to slow boil until mixture reaches hard-boil stage. Remove from heat and cool to 110°. Beat for 4 minutes and pour into 8 x 8 buttered pan. Cool and cut.

title: graham cracker treats
directions: Note:
Will need large cookie sheet with an edge.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat in cold water until ready to pour into a buttered dish.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Pound flour and seasonings into steak with meat hammer or mallet.
Cut meat into 4 pieces.
Cook green pepper, onion and garlic in shortening.
Remove from skillet.
Brown steak well on both sides.
Add onion, green pepper and remaining ingredients. Top each piece of steak with lemon slice.
Cover, simmer about 1 hour or until steak is tender, stirring occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Grease medium size casserole dish.
Put one layer macaroni on bottom of dish, then add layer of browned beef and tomato sauce.
Rotate macaroni, beef and tomato sauce.
Slice cheese and lay on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream cucumbers
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine vinegar, water, sugar and salt. Pare cucumbers.
Cut into slices.
Put cukes in a glass or plastic bowl.
Pour dressing over cucumbers.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.
Drain.
Mix in sour cream and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: rice con queso
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan sticks
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolk, cinnamon, flour and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Spread 1/4-inch thick in well-greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Add sugar to beaten egg white and brush over top of dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Remove seeds and membrane from peppers and cook peppers in boiling water for 15 to 18 minutes, almost tender.
While peppers are cooking, cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions. Take peppers and place in casserole dish with a small amount of water.
Spoon Rice-A-Roni into peppers and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and top with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco mix.
Peel, pit and mash avocados.

title: chocolate cream cheese delight
directions: Cream together Cool Whip, cream cheese and sugar.
Place in crust and let set in refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Fix pudding according to directions on box.
Pour on cream mixture in crust. Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate to serving time.

title: sue's prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-cup bundt pan-set aside.
In mixer bowl, combine all cake ingredients except walnuts.
Beat at low speed until all ingredients are moistened.
Increase speed to medium.
Continue beating until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour 15 minutes.
Cool cake in pan for 20 minutes. Remove from pan to wire rack.

title: brick cheese bake
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 12-inch pan and set aside.
Mix eggs and milk; fold in flour.
Add melted butter and cheese.
Salt the top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: walk-to-school cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour, salt and vanilla.
Stir in Grape-Nuts.
Form cookies the size of a walnut.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until set, 12 to 15 minutes.
Cookies are done when set, not brown.
The baked cookies freeze well.

title: kielbasa pasta salad
directions: Saute bacon until crisp.
Remove from pan.
Add kielbasa and mushrooms and brown.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over kielbasa and mushrooms.
Cook until lightly thickened.
Add macaroni and parsley.
Serve slightly warm.

title: lemon pie
directions: Grate the lemon and squeeze juice.
Mix sugar with the cornstarch.
Add grated lemon rind and juice.
Stir in beaten egg yolks.
Add boiling water gradually, stirring constantly.
Cook over medium heat 2-3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Cover with meringue made from the stiffly beaten egg whites and 4 Tbsp. sugar.
Seal to edge.
Bake in 350° oven for 12-15 minutes or till golden.

title: pound cake
directions: Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken jambalaya
directions: Melt shortening in big skillet or Dutch oven.
Brown seasoned chicken and remove.
Cook pepper, onion, garlic and rice in meat drippings for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add seasoning, tomato sauce and broth.
Arrange chicken parts in mix.
Bring to boil and simmer tightly covered 35 to 40 minutes until rice is fluffy and chicken is tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grilled cheese and mushrooms
directions: Mix salad dressing, Worcestershire sauce, mustard, salt and cayenne pepper.
Add Cheddar and Blue cheese, mushrooms and onion. Make 8 sandwiches using 1/3 mixture for each.
In a shallow dish, combine eggs, milk and Parmesan cheese.
Dip both sides of sandwiches in egg mixture.
Cook on buttered griddle (or iron skillet) over medium heat, 3 minutes on each side, or until brown. Makes 8.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Cook and drain spinach and onion.
Combine, cover and chill. Shape into 1-inch balls and chill until serving or can be frozen at this point.
Place chilled or frozen balls on baking sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown (chilled 10 to 12 minutes, frozen 12 to 15 minutes).

title: microwave country style potatoes(cooking time:  18 to 21 minutes)
directions: Place potatoes in 2-quart microproof casserole with water. Cook, covered, on High for 10 to 12 minutes, or until steaming hot.
Drain.
Add milk, salt, chives and butter.
Stir carefully, then stir in Parmesan cheese and sprinkle with paprika.
Cook, uncovered, on simmer (50) for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Makes 6 servings.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Mix soup according to directions on can.
Saute onions in butter or margarine.
Flavor soup with cheese to taste.
While simmering soup, cook broccoli.
Mix together.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Boil or pressure cook chicken until tender.
Pull chicken from bones.
Place in a 13 x 8 x 2-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup with sour cream.
Spread on top of chicken.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Slice margarine on top.
Sprinkle with poppy seed.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: lemon butter cookies
directions: In a bowl beat sugar, powdered sugar, butter and oil until light and fluffy.
Add lemon peel, lemon juice and egg, blending well.
Stir in flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt, mixing well.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: gone-all-day-stew
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Put all ingredients in large casserole with lid to fit.
No need to brown meat.
Mix all ingredients. Cover.
Bake for 5 hours.

title: jumbo oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine.
Add eggs and beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Add flakes and oatmeal.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix dates, fruit (cut fine) and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add spices to the sifted and measured flour.
Add the dissolved soda to the creamed mixture.
Then alternately add the flour and liquid. Pour the batter over fruit and nuts, mixing well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans supreme
directions: Fry and partially drain bacon.
Saute onions in a small amount of bacon grease.
Mix in a large bowl the three cans of beans. Add bacon (cut in 1-inch pieces) and mix.
Blend catsup, brown sugar, salt and vinegar and add to bean mixture.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: triple-layer butterscotch pie
directions: In a small bowl, mix melted chocolate and sweetened condensed milk until well blended. Pour into crust. Sprinkle pecans evenly on top. Refrigerate 10 minutes.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook turkey or chicken until done.
Bake Cornbread and biscuits day before.
Crumble both.	Saute onion and celery in butter.
Add all remaining ingredients and mix well.
Place in baking dish; top with almonds or water chestnuts and bake.

title: sausage balls
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix together and shape into balls (1 tablespoon size).
Bake 15 minutes, covered.
Uncover and turn oven to 350°.
Bake 30 minutes longer.

title: mcgee's cracklin corn bread
directions: Heat a heavy 10-inch skillet with ovenproof handle in oven 5 to 10 minutes.

title: refrigerator cake
directions: Use all liquid from fruit in cake.
Mix and bake as 2 layer cake about 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Mix and spread over layers and refrigerate the Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and crushed pineapple.

title: bay roasted potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Break bay leaves into roasting pan and melt with butter in oven.
Toss chunks of potatoes in mixture. Cover pan with foil and bake for 30 minutes.
Uncover and cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, until potatoes are crisp and browned.

title: spaghetti with meat sauce
directions: Combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, onion, garlic, mushrooms with liquid, nutmeg and sugar in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil on top of the stove.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 250°.
Cover and cook sauce in the oven for 2 hours.
After 2 hours, add ground beef.
(You may crumble or make meatballs.)
Cook 1 hour.
Add tomato juice or water and cheese and cook for 20 minutes.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Wash chicken. Salt and pepper and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan or dish. Pour rice over chicken. Pour soup and water over rice. Saute onion in butter and mix with ingredients in dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is done.

title: betty's hamburger supreme
directions: Brown meat in 1 tablespoon oleo.
Add salt and tomato sauce. Turn off heat; cook noodles and drain.
Put noodles in a bowl and add cottage cheese, softened cream cheese and poppy seed.
In a small pan cook peppers and onion in remaining oleo.
Add to noodle mixture and stir.
Put all of noodle mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread.
Pour meat mixture over noodles and spread.
Bake 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Serves 6.

title: pan coat for cakes
directions: Mix and store in a covered container. This is used to coat all cake pans. Cakes will brown evenly and are easy to remove from pans.

title: nana's cheese straws
directions: Mix all ingredients; roll small portions at a time into small balls.
Press out on a floured board and roll out with a rolling pin.
Cut into strips that are 1/4-inch wide.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake for approximately 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wax paper.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix milk, lemon juice, bananas, and pineapple. Then pour into graham cracker crust shell & chill.
Top with whipped cream, and garnish with coconut, maraschino cherry & pecans.

title: sausage lentil soup
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown sausage. Drain fat and crumble sausage; return to Dutch oven along with remaining ingredients, except mustard. Simmer, covered, 1 hour or until lentils and vegetables are tender. Stir in the mustard. Remove and discard bay leaf before serving. Yield: 6 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a casserole dish, combine all ingredients.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and mango in Teflon skillet.
Drain off grease.
Place in 5 or 6-quart covered pan.
Add tomato paste and smooth with meat.
Add one can of water from paste can, then add tomato sauce and water from rinsing out each tomato sauce can. Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer.
Stirring frequently, cook for approximately 4 hours. Sprinkle to taste with chili powder.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion; pour off fat.
Brown hamburger.
Mix molasses, ketchup and mustard together.
Pour over pork and beans. Add hamburger mixture.
Sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Bake in slow oven; the longer the better.

title: rice krispie fudge sandwiches
directions: Mix peanut
butter and butterscotch chips over low heat until smooth.
Add
rice	cereal	and mix well.
Press half of this mixture into
a
buttered
x
9-inch pan and chill in refrigerator while mixing remaining ingredients.

title: taco spread
directions: Layer 1:
Cream the cream cheese, sour cream and package taco seasoning. Layer 2:
Ground beef and 1 package taco seasoning cooked together. Layer 3:
Shredded cheese. Layer 4:
Green peppers, green onions, tomatoes.

title: crabmeat coaramesett
directions: Combine the 12 ounces of cream cheese with the Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, mayonnaise and grated onion.
Add a dash of garlic salt.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except bacon. Top with bacon slices. Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: sarah's grilled chicken with dijon mayonnaise(makes 2 servings)
directions: In medium mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, except chicken, and stir until thoroughly combined.
Add chicken and turn to coat with mayonnaise mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all together.
Put in bottom of pan.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump pineapple with juice into buttered 9 x 13 inch baking pan, spread evenly. Dump cherry pie filling evenly over pineapple. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit. Slice butter very thin and distribute over top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups flour and powdered sugar and cut in margarine; mix together until it looks like pie dough.
Press into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Beat together eggs, sugar and lemon juice with mixer.
Sift 1/4 cup flour and baking powder; stir into egg mixture.
Pour over baked crust and bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool; cut into bars.

title: green beans
directions: To make good green beans, put in a small piece of fatback. Boil about 1/2 hour, then put in green beans and let cook about 1 hour or until beans are done.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into 1 large ball or 2 smaller balls.
Roll in 1 cup of chopped nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs and butter on top.
Bake in a covered dish for 55 minutes at 350°.
Last 5 minutes uncover and finish baking.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs. Top with remaining ingredients and press down firmly.

title: easy fruit crumb pie
directions: Melt one stick margarine or butter in either microwave or saucepan.
Add flour, sugar and baking soda to make crumb mixture. Grease a 9-inch pie plate and put in 1/2 of crumb mixture.
Pour in one can of pie filling and top with remaining 1/2 of crumbs. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin dessert brown
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil, eggs, pumpkin and nuts. Stir with spoon well.
Pour into 2 loaf pans that are greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons of cinnamon and 3/4 cup sugar mixed.
Place cinnamon and sugar balls in buttered Bundt or angel food cake pan.
Then add 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, sugar (1 cup), margarine, pecans, vanilla and water in saucepan and bring to boil.
Place this heated mixture over cinnamon-sugar balls and bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: potatoes and onions in herb butter sauce
directions: Drain potatoes and divide over 4 to 6 heavy-duty aluminum foil squares, approximately 1 foot square.
Divide all ingredients over potatoes.
Wrap tightly, sealing edges.
Lay on top of coals for 10 to 20 minutes.
Turn and cook another 10 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, cinnamon, pumpkin, flour and baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes on a greased jelly roll pan or cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Loosen cake from pan and slide onto Saran Wrap same size as pan.

title: roho pollo("red chicken")
directions: Cut chicken into bite-sized pieces.
Heat oil in pan; fry chicken until browned.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1 cup red wine.
Turn heat down; reduce liquid by half.
Add ketchup; cook on low heat or in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours or until very tender.
Serve over rice.

title: granola bars
directions: Toast oats in shallow baking dish (ungreased) for 17 minutes at 350°.
Combine oats with all other ingredients and mix well. Press into 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool and serve.

title: new zealand anzac biscuits
directions: Mix together oats, coconut, flour and sugar.
Melt butter and syrup.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to butter mix. Stir liquid into dry ingredients.
Place in small spoonfuls on a cold, well-greased tray.
Bake until flat and dark golden brown in 350° oven.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Pour soup in pressure cooker.
Mix other 5 ingredients together.
Form into balls (slightly smaller than golf balls). Place into tomato soup.
Cover the pressure cooker.
When pressure regulator attains a gentle rocking motion turn burner down to medium-low.
Cook for 15 minutes.
(4 servings.)
(You may cook in a regular large pan for 40 minutes.
You may also need to add 1 c. water to soup.)

title: nutria-oysters casserole
directions: Remove from bone, 15 to 20 pieces of nutria, 1 to 3-inch by 1/2 to 1-inch.
The back bone or fore and hind legs are preferable.
Only part of one animal will be needed.

title: myra's instant tea
directions: Mix together.
Use 2 tablespoons per cup added to hot water.

title: "easy as pie" pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy. Gradually add sweetened condensed milk and stir until well blended.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Turn into crust.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Garnish with chilled cherry pie filling before serving. Serves 8.

title: beef or pork barbecue
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with pork or beef.
Let simmer.

title: cheese squash
directions: Cut up squash in chunks.
Place in a 2-quart saucepan.
Add onions.
Add water to cover.
Place over medium heat, approximately 10 to 20 minutes.
Cook until tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain water off.
Add cheese, salt and pepper to taste. Mix until cheese is blended.
Squash cooks down.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Make in patties, using enough cracker meal for good consistency.
Cook in hot oil until brown.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Line 13 x 9-inch baking dish with broccoli.
Layer chicken over broccoli. Combine soup, mayonnaise, curry and lemon juice and pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Saute onion and celery; blend bread cubes and seasoning.
Add onion, celery, margarine and beaten eggs and stir.
Add broth gradually, stirring lightly.
Add more seasoning, if desired. Extra stuffing may be baked in a loaf pan or casserole.
Cook 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, beat together eggs, milk, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon of salt.
Dip bread in egg mixture, coating both sides. In a skillet or on a grill, cook bread on both sides in a small amount of hot butter over medium-high heat until golden brown.
Add more butter when needed.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and powdered sugar.
Serve with maple flavored syrup.
Serves 5.

title: easy meat dip
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill.
Serve with crisp, raw vegetables, relishes or potato chips.

title: tasty bars
directions: Layer ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix onion, celery, mayonnaise, cheese, and Veg-All.
Spoon into 8 or 9-inch casserole dish.
Apply topping and
bake at 350° for 15-20 minutes.

title: peach peanut patties
directions: Mash the peach halves.
Then add the cream cheese and peanut butter.
Use the mixture as a spread on peanut butter cookies.

title: chili cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients well; make into logs and roll in chili powder.
Refrigerate.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: Place the corned beef in a large soup kettle or Dutch oven. Add the onions, halved carrots, celery and parsley sprigs.
Cover with cold water and bring to a boil, then reduce the heat.
Cover and simmer for 2 3/4 to 3 hours.
When the meat is tender, remove it from kettle and keep warm.
Strain the broth and return it to the kettle.
Add the cabbage, potatoes, leeks, cut up carrots, salt and pepper and 2 tablespoons of the chopped parsley.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce the heat, cover, and simmer until the vegetables are tender, 30 minutes.
Arrange the beef on a warmed serving platter and surround it with the cooked vegetables.
Ladle broth over the beef and vegetables.
Sprinkle with remaining 2 tablespoons chopped parsley.
Serve with the Horseradish Cream Sauce.

title: italian venison
directions: Brown meat.
Add water to roast in crock-pot.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook 4 to 5 hours on high or 8 hours on low.
When cooked, shred meat and add seasonings to broth.
Serve on hoagie buns.
Use broth for dipping.

title: sweet and zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Brush on meat several times during the last 15 minutes of grilling time.

title: french toast
directions: Beat eggs and cream together. Add nutmeg. Cut bread 1-inch thick. Soak bread in cream mixture on both sides.
Place in hot oven at 375°.
Turn once. Remove and sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients with your hands, just until combined. Add raisins.
Bake in round cake pan sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Keep in a large container. Boil water and add 1/4 cup of the mixture to the water and you will have a delicious cup of hot chocolate.

title: clam dip
directions: Rub a glass mixing bowl well with garlic.
Drain clams, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine clams, cream cheese, liquid and seasonings.
Mix well and chill.

title: coolime salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in boiling water.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat the cheese until smooth.
Stir buttermilk vinegar, horseradish, pepper, paprika and cheese into Jell-O; chill until very thick.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 1-quart mold.
Makes about 4 cups or 8 side salads.

title: refrigerated peach pie
directions: Bake pie shell first.
Double the ingredients if you want to make 2 pies.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and jello in saucepan. Add water and cook on stove until mixture boils.
Let boil 1 minute; set aside.
Spread peaches out evenly in baked pie shell. Pour mixture over peaches.
Refrigerate.
Serve when completely jelled.
Top with Cool Whip when serving.

title: bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12 (2 1/2-inch) muffin pan cups. In a shallow baking pan, toast bran flakes in oven for 5 minutes; cool.
In medium bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; stir in bran flakes.
In mixer bowl, beat egg at low speed.
Beat in brown sugar, then molasses.
Beat in milk and salad oil.
Add all dry ingredients at once; stir until moistened. Spoon into prepared cups, filling each until about three-quarters full.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan; place on wire rack.
Serve warm.

title: sweet potato apple bake
directions: Cut unpared sweet potatoes in 1/2's or 1/3's and cook until done and soft. Peel and mash in large bowl with butter. Add dash of salt. Add honey and mash. Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste. Should be creamy in consistency. Peel, core and 1/4 apples; cut into 1/4-inch slices. Place in medium size pan and sprinkle with sugar (no water). Place over medium heat just a few minutes so slices turn limp. Place 1/2 sweet potatoes in casserole. Cover with 1/2 the apples. Add dash of cinnamon. Cover with remaining sweet potatoes. Place remaining apple slices on top, forming a "round" design. Add dash of cinnamon and nutmeg again and dribble thin coating of honey on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Prepare chili seasoning mix according to package directions, using ground beef, oil, tomatoes, kidney beans and water.
Cook lasagna noodles.
Alternate noodles, meat sauce, cottage cheese and grated cheese in baking dish, making 3 layers, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake in 375° oven 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: won't last long cake
directions: Do not beat.
Just stir ingredients together until well blended.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
No icing is needed.

title: roast chicken in a pot
directions: Seasoned chicken well with salt and pepper.
Heat the olive oil over high heat in a Dutch over and brown chicken well on all sides.
Remove from the pan.
Add the onions, carrots, celery, and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper; add almost to the top of the chicken and cover.
Bring to a boil.
Preheat the oven to 400°.
Place pot into oven for 45 minutes.
Remove cover and bake 30 minutes more.
Correct broth to taste.
Serve in a large bowl.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients very well.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lady locks
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick and cool. While cooling, cream shortening, butter or oleo and confectioners sugar. When creamed, add vanilla and marshmallow cream. Add cooled paste and mix well.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine in large bowl the flour and sugar. In a saucepan, bring to a boil the oleo, cocoa and water. Pour over dry mixture. Add the buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and eggs. Beat well and pour into a greased and floured baking pan. Bake in 400° oven 25 to 30 minutes. Five minutes before cake is done, start making the following frosting.

title: apple tart with almonds
directions: Place the flour, salt, sugar and butter in a bowl and mix to a fine crumb texture.
Gradually mix in 1/4 cup ice water.
The dough should hold together but not be sticky.
Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate for at least a half hour.
On a floured board, roll dough into a circle and line a 9- inch pan with the dough, prick the bottom with a fork.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: one hour rolls
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm.
Add shortening.
Mix yeast and sugar in a cup and pour in a little warm milk to dissolve.
Add to other liquid mixture.
Add dry ingredients.
Knead and roll into biscuits.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown (15 to 20 minutes).

title: mozzarella crostini
directions: Heat broiler.
Arrange bread slices on baking sheet.
Cut slices of Mozzarella cheese (1 for each slice of bread and place on each).

title: vegetarian chili for 12
directions: Soak beans overnight.
In morning, drain off water and place beans in heavy pot with 6 cups water, 2 cloves crushed garlic and 1 diced onion.
Cover, bring to boil, simmer in 10 cups water 2 hours.
In separate pan, saute vegetables in oil until tender. Add to cooked beans.
Add canned tomatoes and seasonings.
Add chili powder to taste.
Simmer several hours.
Great for crock-pot.

title: stir-in-pan chocolate cake
directions: Sift all ingredients into greased and floured cake pan.
Mix the liquid ingredients together and pour over dry ingredients. Stir with fork until most of the lumps are gone.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Heat soup, but do not boil.
Mix gelatin in hot water, add to soup.
Place cream cheese in bowl and add soup mixture.
Beat until smooth and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2-quart mold.
Chill until set.
Serve with crackers.

title: custard pie
directions: Scald milk.
Beat egg yolks slightly, add sugar and salt. Stir constantly while adding hot milk.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks and fold into milk mixture.
Put into crust and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 425 degrees for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 25 minutes.

title: apple zucchini bread
directions: In large bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt (all by hand).
Beat eggs separately.
Mix eggs, oil, sugars and vanilla and add to dry ingredients.
Stir in zucchini, apples and nuts.
Mixture will be stiff.
Spoon into 3 greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pans or 1 large angel food tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix with soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, salt and pepper.
Place in buttered casserole and top with cheese and crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crostoli (bow ties)
directions: Place flour, sugar and salt in large bowl.
Beat eggs, oil and vanilla well.
Add to flour mixture and stir until well mixed. Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth.
Roll out dough to paper thinness.
Cut into strips 3/4-inch wide and long enough to tie in a loose bow.
Fry in deep fat and drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except French fried onion rings.
Add onion rings on top.
Heat 1 hour in greased casserole at 350°.

title: dill pickles
directions: Select cucumbers, 2 or 3 inches in length; scrub well.
Layer in jars the cucumbers, layer of dill and a few mustard seed.
Place bay leaf on top of each jar.
Bring the vinegar, water and salt to a boil; pour boiling hot mixture over pickles and seal.
Before sealing, you may add garlic for flavor or pinch of alum for crisper pickles.

title: double chocolate drops
directions: Melt half of the chocolate pieces.
Blend Fluffo, sugar, egg and melted chocolate.
Stir in combined dry ingredients alternately with the water.
Stir in nuts and remaining chocolate pieces.
Drop batter from a teaspoon onto baking sheet and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in greased bread tins.
Will make 2 loaves.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Make a syrup by boiling sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Add tea and fruit juices.
Mix with water.
Chill, then add ginger ale before serving.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Marinate chicken breasts in this sauce for several hours or overnight.
Remove chicken from marinade and grill, basting with reserved marinade.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Layer the vegetables in the order listed in a deep bowl. Do not toss. Spread mayonnaise evenly over top. Sprinkle with sugar, then cheese and bacon bits. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Toss before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
