Dip breasts in melted oleo, then in crumb mixture.
Coat chicken heavily.
Place breasts in baking dish and bake 30 to 35 minutes uncovered at 350°.
I prefer plain bread crumbs.
Recipe may be halved easily to serve fewer people. Delicious and easy!

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Fry, drain and crumble sausage.
Slightly beat eggs.
Cube bread (1 1/2-inch cubes).
Combine all and pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan; refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: prune cake
directions: Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: all at once spaghetti
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add onion and cook until soft; crumble in beef in chunks.
Stir and fry until it loses its red color. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour in tomato sauce, canned tomatoes and water and bring to a boil.
Break spaghetti in desired lengths, sprinkle in a little at a time, stirring it into sauce and keeping it separated.
Cover tightly.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Stir as needed.
Serve with cheese.
Makes 4 big servings.

title: laulau
directions: Wash Ti leaves and taro tops or fresh spinach.
Cut fish in cubes and soak for 4 hours.
Cut pork in chunks so you will have 1 pound for each laulau.
Be sure your Ti leaves are large.
For each laulau, put 2 Ti leaves in a triangle, then on this, put taro tops, about 6 or 8 leaves.
On this, put your pork and fish, then roll this up tightly and tie with string.
Cook laulau 3 hours in steamer.
Cover tightly so steam does not escape.
Makes 12.

title: jello cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly margarine, sugar, jello, eggs and vanilla. Stir in dry ingredients.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Roll to about 1/4 inch thick on a flour dusted board.
Cut or shape as desired.
Bake 5 minutes on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: egg quiche
directions: In a blender mix the eggs, Bisquick, milk and dried onions, then stir in bacon and cheese. Grease quiche pan and pour mixture into pan. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and press out excess water.
Combine all the ingredients and stir well.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: grandmere's crepes
directions: Lightly coat pan with oil, or rub bottom of pan with small piece of salt pork.
Mix ingredients, adding milk to desired consistency.
Pour moderate amount of mixture into middle of pan. Pick up pan; roll to allow mixture to spread to as large as desired.
Turn after top of crepe is bubbled.
Serve with syrup or roll fruits into it.

title: orange banana shake
directions: Combine soft drink mix, milk and water in blender container. Cover; blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Add banana and ice cubes.
Cover and blend for 30 seconds longer, or until smooth. Serve at once.
Makes 1 2/3 cups or 2 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of salted water until tender; drain and mash.
Add margarine, cheese, egg, onion, milk and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs.
Put into buttered baking dish and sprinkle top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 425°.

title: potato popover
directions: Beat egg until very light.
Add potatoes, milk, salt, flour and baking powder.
Make mixture stiff so it drops into deep fat.
If not crowd in pan, they will turn over themselves.
Serve hot.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package.
Drain while browning ground meat. Drain fat. Mix sauces and meat to simmering.
Mix spaghetti, sauce and cheese in large baking or glass dish.
Layer sausage slices on top with slices of American or cheese food. Bake until cheese melts or brown as desired.
Serves 8.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Serve on hot dogs in buns.
This is enough for one package of 10 hot dogs.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Cook and stir constantly until thick as desired.
Put in hot pint jars and seal.
Makes 4 to 5 pints.

title: nell's pecan pie
directions: Brown in iron skillet the stick of butter.
Mix other ingredients and add the butter.
Pour into prepared pie shell and bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce oven to 325° and bake for 40 more minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: In a medium-saucepan, combine sugar and 1/4 cup water.
Bring to boiling.
Add rhubarb.
Reduce heat, stirring constantly until tender.
Repeat procedure for strawberries.
Mix together.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter (optional).
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Adjust top crust.
Seal and flute edge.
Trim off excess pastry after pressing down firmly on edge.
Make holes in top crust.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or more.

title: basic yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve dry yeast in very warm water; add milk which has been cooled to lukewarm, sugar and salt.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes; add butter or margarine and egg and mix well.
Stir in flour and beat with spoon until dough forms a ball.
Brush top of dough with melted margarine and cover with a towel.
Set bowl in warm water until dough is light and spongy, about 20 to 25 minutes.
Turn out onto floured cloth or board; knead a minute or so.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400°
for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 16 average rolls.

title: chicken cacciatore with artichoke hearts
directions: Drain liquid from artichoke hearts into large skillet; add olive oil and heat.
Dredge chicken with flour and brown in oil mixture.
Remove chicken from oil and place in large casserole.
In skillet, saute garlic 2 to 3 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts, tomatoes, salt, oregano, basil, pepper and mushrooms.
When heated and thoroughly mixed, pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add sherry; stir and return to oven for 10 minutes.

title: maryland crab bisque
directions: In
saucepan,
melt
butter and saute celery until soft. Stir in
sauce mix and gradually add half and half and chicken broth. Add
sherry.
Stir over low heat until the soup bubbles and thickens slightly.
Add crab meat.
Simmer 1 to 2 minutes. Serve in bowls topped with celery leaves.

title: pork chops and mushrooms
directions: Bake or pressure cook pork chops until tender.
Cook chopped pepper, onions and mushrooms until tender.
Cook cream of mushroom soup according to directions.
Add pork chops, onions, peppers and mushrooms to cream of mushroom.
Season to taste.

title: sausage dibari
directions: In baking dish, add hot sausage and all other ingredients and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: unfried french fries(healthy recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cut potatoes into matchstick-size fries. Spray baking sheet well with 3 sprays of vegetable spray.
Combine lightly beaten egg whites and Cajun spice in a bowl.
Add potatoes and mix until coated.
Pour coated potatoes onto prepared baking sheet and spread out in a single layer, leaving a little space between.
Place baking sheet on middle rack of oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until fries are crispy.
Turn them every 6 to 8 minutes with spatula so they brown evenly.
Serve immediately.

title: orange salad
directions: Heat water.
Add jello and add frozen orange juice.
Best to add ice cream and oranges when partially set. Set.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil cocoa, milk, vanilla and butter in medium saucepan.
Add confectioners sugar.
Mix until smooth and pour over warm cake immediately after coming out of oven.
Top with 3/4 cup chopped nuts (optional).
Cool on rack before cutting.

title: chicken
directions: Put a 100 pound chicken in oven for 50 minutes at 500°.
Take it out; put sauce on it and eat it.

title: cocoa pan cake
directions: Let cocoa and hot water stand.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2 pan for 45 minutes at 350°.
Ice while hot.

title: forrest's favorite vanilla cupcakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together until creamy.
Put in cupcake paper cups and place in muffin tins.

title: cheesy apple crisps
directions: In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, cinnamon and lemon juice. In a second bowl, combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Using pastry blender, cut in margarine until coarse texture.
Spoon apples into 6 (6-ounce) cups and top with crumb mixture.
Place cups in a baking pan and bake in 375° oven for 18 minutes.
Remove and top with 1/2 cheese slice each and return for 1 to 2 minutes until melted.

title: ham dip
directions: Gradually add the mayonnaise to the cream cheese, blending until smooth.
Add the deviled ham, pimiento, onion, Worcestershire sauce and pepper and mix well.
Serve with chips.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Mix soup, vinegar, sugar, oil, salt and pepper.
Add vegetables and marinate 8 hours.
(Carrots are the only vegetable cooked.)

title: no-bake cookies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar well.
Add oleo and milk; boil for 2 minutes only.
Stir in remaining ingredients immediately.
Stir just enough to mix well and drop by tablespoons onto wax paper.

title: superbowl sandwich
directions: Cut off ends of French bread and set aside.
Hollow out the center of loaf with a long serrated bread knife, leaving a 1/2-inch shell.
Put bread in food processor and process to make coarse crumbs.
Cook sausage, beef and onion in skillet until brown; drain well.
Add 1 cup of reserved bread crumbs, cheese, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.

title: low-fat prune bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan and dust with flour.
In saucepan, mix puree, juice and orange peel.
Bring just to boiling and remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine dry ingredients and blend.
Add prune mixture.
Fold in egg whites.
Add pecans. Spread in loaf pan.
Bake about 50 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn out on rack to cool completely.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Make 2 small holes and 1 big hole in dry ingredients.
Put the oil in the big hole and vinegar and vanilla in the small holes. Add cold water.
Stir, but do not beat.
Bake at 350°.

title: just like fried ice cream
directions: Make 4 (1/2 cup) scoops of ice cream.
Place in shallow pan. Cover and store in freezer until firm.
In small bowl mix together cereal, coarsely crushed and butter.
Roll firm ice cream in cereal mixture.
To serve, stir together honey and cinnamon.
Place ice cream on plate and drizzle with honey and cinnamon mixture.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water, margarine and sugar to a full boil.
Add flour all at once.
Stir vigorously with wooden spoon until a thick smooth ball forms and mixture pulls away from sides of pan. Cook about 5 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously after each addition.
Paste will be shiny and smooth.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoons onto greased cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 40 minutes or until light and golden.
Cool on wire rack.
Make a slit in side of puffs with a sharp knife.
Fill with custard/pudding.
Dust with sifted powdered sugar.
May also be filled with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover play surface with waxed paper.
Shape into whatever animal or object you like (mice are cute!).
You can decorate them with little candies if desired. Refrigerate to firm, or eat right away.

title: louisiana blue ribbon peach cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions in 2 (8-inch) round pans.
Cool.
Divide to make 4 layers.
In a saucepan, combine peaches, water, sugar and cornstarch and cook until thick.
Set aside and allow to cool.
On the first cake layer, spread 1/4 of the peach mixture, then spread 1/4 cup sour cream.
Repeat for remaining layers.
Refrigerate.
Garnish slices with mint sprigs. This cake is best made a day ahead to let the flavors mingle.

title: cheese and artichoke dip
directions: Cut up artichokes to less than 1/4 size.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: country-style barbecued ribs or oven baked
directions: Cook ribs, covered, in enough boiling salted water to cover, 45 to 60 minutes or until tender. Drain. Cook onion, garlic and celery in hot oil until tender. Stir in tomato sauce, next 5 ingredients, 1/2 cup water, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Grill ribs over slow coals about 45 minutes or until done. Turn every 15 minutes. Brush with sauce until coated. Serves 6.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat slowly until mixed well.
Pour into a 9-inch pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter for 3 minutes.
Stir in flour until well blended.
Stir in slowly the stock or stock substitute.
When the sauce is smooth and boiling, add milk.
Heat soup but do not boil. Add and stir until melted the grated cheese.
Add salt and paprika.
Yield:
3 cups.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl, cream together shortening and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift together flour and soda; add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add oatmeal and nuts; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate (375°) oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: "special rolls"
directions: Mix yeast in 1/3 water.
Mix flour and salt; put in large bowl.
Add 1 1/4 cups water to yeast.
Add all of it to flour and salt.
Mix well; turn out on floured surface.
Knead until elastic.
Let rise in bowl until 3 times its size (4 to 5 hours). Pat down, fold and turn and let rise again 1 1/2 hours.
Shape in 3-inch balls.
Let rise until 2 1/2 times original size (2 to 2 1/2 hours).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: bread custard pudding
directions: Combine the crumbs and milk; bring to boiling point.
Add the butter and stir into the egg and sugar, beaten until light in the baking dish.
Add vanilla.
Place baking dish in a pan of hot water and bake at 350° until a knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes (raisins can be added 1 cup).

title: sausage bread
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix Bisquick, milk, beaten egg and salt. Add sausage to mixture, then cheeses and egg whites. Mixture will be thick. Spread into a greased 11 x 5 or 8 x 8 pan. Bake at 400° for approximately 25 minutes. This may be prepared ahead of time and refrigerated or frozen and baked when needed. Good for Christmas morning breakfast. Serves 9 to 12. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: snicker bar cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Pour half of mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
This is the crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with butter and milk.
Pour over baked crust.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel mixture.
Spread remaining batter over top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°, then 10 minutes at 325°.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients and store in a tightly covered container. Use 1/3 cup mix to 8 ounces hot water.
Makes 54 cups or 3 1/2 gallons of drink.

title: oktoberfest ribs
directions: Layer ingredients into a large Dutch oven in this order: sauerkraut, onions, apples, brown sugar (sprinkle evenly over) and ribs.
If using caraway seed, bury them evenly in the sauerkraut layer.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat, cover and simmer gently for 2 to 3 hours, until ribs are very tender.

title: peanut butter chews
directions: Mix peanut butter, corn syrup, dry milk and sugar well.
Press 1/2 inch thick into a pan.
Cut into squares.
Chill before serving.

title: rosemary's seafood dip
directions: Flake crabmeat and cut shrimp into small pieces.
Mix crabmeat, shrimp and cream cheese together; spread into shallow pie plate.
Top with cocktail sauce to taste.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in the 1/2 cup hot water.
Mix with meat, crumbs, seasoning and egg.
Shape in 8 flat patties.
Beat milk and soup together and set aside.
Bake in preheated 350° oven until lightly browned (about 15 minutes).
Cover with soup and milk mixture.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Stirring constantly, continue boiling for 7 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips and all remaining ingredients.
Pour into flat baking dish. Cool and slice.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Beat together and spread over cream cheese layer and cover with Cool Whip.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Drain potatoes and mix all ingredients with a mixer.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple in 13 x 9-inch pan; top with pie filling. Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Chop butter into pats and place on top of mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potatoes supreme
directions: Cook potatoes in salted, boiling water until tender; drain and refrigerate.
Grate potatoes coarsely.
Mix in remaining ingredients and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Put in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: topsy turvy cupcakes
directions: You will need cupcake liners.

title: chocolate lover's cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except the grated chocolate and chips.
Beat at least 5 minutes.
Save 3 tablespoons of grated chocolate for top of finished cake.
Stir in gently the grated chocolate and chocolate chips.
Bake 55 minutes to 1 hour at 350° in an ungreased tube pan (may be lightly sprayed with Pam). Sprinkle the 3 tablespoons of grated chocolate on warm cake. Enjoy!

title: victorian cherry blossoms
directions: In 1-quart saucepan, mix gelatin and 1 cup skim milk.
Let stand 1 minute.
Add sugar.
Stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in remaining milk, almond extract and vanilla extract.

title: corn oysters(complement to hot slaw)
directions: Add egg to corn, then the flour and seasonings. Drop by spoonfuls on hot well-greased griddle and fry.

title: oven pancakes
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat Bisquick, sugar, eggs, milk, syrup and 1/2 cup of Cheddar cheese with hand beater until smooth.
Pour into dish.
Bake uncovered until pick comes out clean, 10 to 15 minutes at 425°.
Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese (3 to 5 minutes).
Serve with maple syrup.

title: chicken salad
directions: Bake chicken until done.
Add all ingredients; mix well. Chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: white chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream butter; add sugar and vanilla.
Add egg yolks and melted chocolate. Alternate the flour, buttermilk, nuts and coconut.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in three 9-inch pans or oblong pan at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done.
Ice with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: twenty-four hour salad(this salad must be started the day before serving.)
directions: Beat the yolks well.
Slowly add lemon juice, then the cream. Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add gelatin soaked in cold water.
Let cool.
Fold in 1 pint of whipped cream or Cool Whip and combine with the fruit mixture.
Chill overnight.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken paprika
directions: Flour skinned breasts. Brown thoroughly and fast. Add onions, chopped, 15 minutes. Add paprika. Place on water, bouillon cubes and sour cream. Cover and simmer 40 minutes. Serve over cooked Amish noodles.

title: baked radiatore with salmon and white cheddar sauce
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Meanwhile, grate the Cheddar.
Dice the bell peppers.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Add pasta to boiling water; cook until al dente, 10 to 12 minutes, or according to package directions.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Simmer all ingredients (except ham) for 10 minutes.
Add ham and simmer an additional 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Sauce makes approximately 1 cup.

title: walnut pops
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll in balls.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar when you remove from oven.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
To bacon fat (1/3 cup) add onions. Cook until yellow.
Add flour, sugar, salt and pepper to bacon fat gradually.
Then add hot water and vinegar.
Cook and stir until it starts to boil, then let it boil for 1 minute.
Add crushed bacon and pour it over diced, peeled potatoes.
Salad can be put into crock-pot for serving and keeping hot.

title: crumb topped fish filets
directions: Mix margarine, tarragon, parsley, onion, salt and nutmeg. Place fish in a lightly greased baking pan.
Pour on half the margarine mixture.
Mix remaining margarine mixture with bread crumbs. Sprinkle over fish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until fish flakes with a fork.

title: carrots (julians)(60 calories per serving)
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Sprinkle each with salt, pepper and a bit of sugar.
Cover tops with a thick layer of buttered crumbs to which you have added finely cut chives.
Bake for 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: sunday scramble
directions: Beat the eggs with a fork.
Add the salt, mustard and shrimp. Crumble the matzo and add to the mixture.
Scramble in butter.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cut vegetables up and mix together.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and be sure they are well mixed. Put into a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Check bread after 25 minutes as ovens vary.
Very good frozen and reheated.

title: shredded carrot salad
directions: Wash and peel carrots.
Grate using large holes of a hand grater or the grating disc of a food processor.
Put into large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed.
Toss until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: karen's untossed salad
directions: Wash and cut spinach/romaine lettuce into bite size pieces. Press onto bottom of large flat bottom bowl. Season with 1 teaspoon each salt, sugar and pepper. Crumble crispy bacon over top. Chop eggs and spread over top. Add head lettuce in bite sized pieces. Drain thawed frozen peas and spread on top. Slice onion into rings or chop onion into not too small pieces and layer over peas. Top with remaining salt, sugar and pepper. Mix Miracle Whip and sour cream. Spread over top. Top with grated Swiss cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 1 day before serving. Serves 10.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Mix last three ingredients. Pour over chicken; cover and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until chicken is done.

title: lasagne rounds
directions: Brown hamburger; add onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Blend in tomato juice, paste, water, sugar, salt and bay leaf.
Simmer, uncovered, 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Blend cottage cheese and egg with 3/4 of the Parmesan and Mozzarella cheese.
Season to taste with salt and pepper; set aside.

title: french-vanilla homemade ice cream
directions: Measure all ingredients.
Mix flour, sugar, salt and eggs. Add scalded milk gradually and cook in a double boiler until thick.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Add cream and vanilla.
Strain into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Beat eggs lightly in a large bowl.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and pepper; blend.
Add cooled, melted butter, chilies and cheese and mix just to blended.
Turn into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan (at this point, you may refrigerate until ready to bake). Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then at 350° for 40 minutes.
Check with knife for doneness.
When removed from oven, let stand for a few minutes.
Cut into squares for serving. Serve warm.

title: tv hash
directions: Mix cereal, pretzels and peanuts in a large roasting pan. Combine butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over.
Cover; bake in a 225° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Sift and store.
Use 1/2 a cup to 1 cup hot boiling water.

title: green rice
directions: Mix all together and pour in casserole dish and bake covered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Grease and flour a Bundt pan or spring-form with tube attachment.
Cream butter and powdered sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and flour.
Mix well.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in oven.
Frost cake, if desired.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Combine ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: coconut seafoam candy
directions: Combine sugar, water and syrup.
Let boil until it will form a hard ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add slowly to egg whites, continually stirring.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Stir well until stiff.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: corn dogs
directions: Fill deep pan with 2 inches oil and heat over medium heat. Oil should warm for approximately 20 minutes.
Mix all dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add water slowly until mixture is thick but not pasty.
Roll hot dogs with sticks in batter.
Dip in hot oil for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Beat the cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar, mixing well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Place a vanilla wafer in paper cups in muffin pan.
Spoon in cream cheese mixture over wafer filled cups, filling cups full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Leave in muffin pan and chill overnight.
Top with pie filling before serving.

title: mostaccioli
directions: Heat bacon, beef and onion in hot oil.
When meat is brown, add seasonings, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 1/2 hour. Water may be added if sauce gets too thick.
Remove bay leaf. Cook noodles according to package directions.
Pour sauce over top of noodles.
Top with Parmesan cheese and Mozzarella cheese.

title: english toffee cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar well; add egg yolk, cinnamon and vanilla.
Spread in large flat pan sprayed with Pam.
Spread unbeaten egg white on top.
Drain off excess.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts sprinkled and pressed on top.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes. Do not overcook.
Cut while hot.
Leave in pan until cool.

title: tina's apple-asparagus salad
directions: Cut apples into small wedges and add a small amount of lemon juice to prevent browning.
Set aside and chill.
Cook fresh asparagus until crisp and drain water.
Chop when cool into 1-inch pieces.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Thaw corn, to separate grains, in large mixing bowl. Thoroughly mix dry ingredients, add them to corn to mix.
In separate bowl beat eggs slightly, add milk and beat mixing well. Stir egg mixture into corn mix.
Put margarine in 2-quart baking dish to melt.
Pour pudding mixture into dish with melted butter and mix.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 45 minutes stirring halfway through.

title: powdered spiced tea
directions: Mix together and store until ready to use.
When ready to drink, add 2 teaspoons of mixture to 1 cup of boiling water.

title: corn cob jelly
directions: Boil corn cobs in water; strain juice.
Boil together sugar and juice and add lemon juice.
Boil hard one minute, then add one bottle Certo.
Pour in jars and seal.

title: easy baked fish
directions: Mix dry ingredients; coat fish.
Melt a small amount of butter or oil in a shallow baking dish.
Arrange fish in dish; bake at 450° for about 15 minutes.

title: lemon cream bread
directions: Cut cream cheese in 1/4-inch cubes and refrigerate.
Sift flour, etc.
Cream shortening.
Add eggs.
Alternate water and dry ingredients.
Fold in cream cheese, nuts and rind.

title: cherry shortcake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar and beat some more.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Add to eggs and sugar and mix some more. Add vanilla and fold in cherries.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased dish about 45 minutes at 325°.

title: tamale pie
directions: Saute in skillet using small amount of water the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer all ingredients together in covered skillet for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Add up to 3/4 cup water if too thick.
Put in baking dish to warm over.

title: cheesy cheese torte
directions: Mix crackers and butter or margarine together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.

title: spinach meat balls
directions: Defrost spinach and drain.
Combine spinach, onion, garlic, beef, cheese, crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Form into golf ball size balls.

title: josie dragseth's buns
directions: Soak yeast with water and 1 teaspoon of the sugar.
Add yeast mixture to the scalded milk.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, salt and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, a little at a time, beating well.

title: kimchee shrimp
directions: Devein and shell shrimp.
Heat 1/2 cup water, 1/2 block butter and
garlic
salt.
Add shrimp; cook until shrimp turn orange. Place
cooked
shrimp
in
colander;
rinse with cool water.
Let stand for 2 minutes, until water is drained.
Put shrimp in a large bowl; pour kimchee base over.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: ham appetizers
directions: Remove tortillas from refrigerator.
Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise, onions and olives. Spread thin layer of mixture on tortilla.
Arrange 4 slices of ham over mixture.
Tightly roll up tortilla.
Wrap individually in plastic wrap.
Place in refrigerator at least 3 hours or overnight.

title: scotch toffies
directions: Pour melted margarine over rolled oats.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pack down firmly into well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° (300° in glass) for about 25 minutes until mixture is a rich brown color and bubbling. Remove from oven; cool slightly in pan, then cut into squares and remove.
(If toffies harden before they are cut, reheat slightly.) Makes 24 squares.

title: margarita punch
directions: In
4-quart non-metal container, combine lemonade, limeade, powdered sugar, egg whites and crushed ice. Mix well.
Cover and freeze, stirring occasionally.
Remove container from freezer 30 minutes before serving.
Spoon 2 cups slush mixture into blender. Add 1 cup Club soda. Blend until frothy.

title: ham hocks and black-eyed peas
directions: Wash peas; soak in water overnight.
Drain
and rinse peas. In 5-quart Dutch oven, combine peas, 4 cups water and remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer 5 hours or until peas are tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mushrooms parmesan
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Place in baking dish which has been brushed with 1 tablespoon olive oil.
Sprinkle with parsley, garlic, oregano, 1/2 of bread crumbs and grated cheese.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour balance of oil over this.
Sprinkle with balance of bread crumbs.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until tender.
Add 1/4 cup water if mushrooms become too dry and bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot.
Serves 6.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place in 3-quart bowl.
Microwave at High speed for 2 minutes. Stir until blended.
Cover; chill for 1 hour.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: mom's rhubarb pie(mom is eva chapman)
directions: Mix all together.
Place in a two crust pie shell.
Bake at 425° for about 1 hour.

title: tex-mex ground turkey potato boats(makes 4 servings)
directions: Slice potatoes lengthwise in half.
Scoop out center of each potato to within 1/4 inch of potato skin.
Reserve potato for other use.
In medium skillet, over medium-high heat, combine turkey, onion and garlic.
Cook and stir 5 minutes or until turkey is no longer pink; drain if necessary.
Add tomatoes with juice, chili powder, oregano, cumin, crushed red pepper and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes or until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Spoon turkey mixture evenly into potato shells and sprinkle with cheese.
Place shells in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: betty's golden chicken nuggets
directions: Cut chicken into 1 inch pieces.
Dip chicken into flour mixture.
Drop into hot oil and cook until brown.
Delicious!

title: beef and avocados deluxe
directions: Arrange in a casserole the layers of avocados, beef and onion, then repeat.
Mix other ingredients and warm in saucepan; pour over top.
Marinate several hours.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In a large skillet, combine pineapple syrup, water, vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch, brown sugar and salt; mix until smooth. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer until clear and thickened.
Add meat strips and remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Serve over hot cooked rice.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill crock-pot full of apples and add other ingredients.
Cook on low for 12 hours.
Mix with portable mixer until smooth.
Turn crock-pot on high and cook 2 more hours.
Put into jars.
Makes about 3 1/2 pints.

title: scrambled egg casserole
directions: Fry sausage.
Whisk eggs. Add milk, mustard, cheese and cooked sausage. Put bread in casserole dish.
Put sausage-egg combination over bread cubes.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.
Serve with fresh fruit and danish.

title: chicken broccoli stuffing bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, stir soup until smooth. Gradually add milk.
Add stuffing, chicken, broccoli and celery; mix well.
Spread mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 35 minutes; top with cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: baked new potatoes
directions: Place the potato slices in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Cover with the cheese. Sprinkle with bacon. Pour butter over the top and season with salt. Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Drain macaroni after cooking in boiling water until done, about 7 minutes. Drain well and add salt, Worcestershire sauce and salad oil.
Stir in onion, celery, relish and pimento.
In a separate container, combine mayo, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Stir into salad and add cheese.
Chill before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: yellow rice
directions: Mix together bacon, bell pepper, onions and tomatoes.
Cook in bacon drippings for five minutes.
Add rest of ingredients (rice, coloring, salt and black pepper).
Cover with 1 quart of water. Stir together.
Cook until done.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together.
Set aside for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: sopaipillas
directions: Then use your imagination and add nuts or raisins, chocolate chips, bananas, etc.
Grease two loaf pans.
Divide batter into loaf pans (about 1 1/2 cups each).
Sprinkle each loaf with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!!!!!!

title: double peanut drops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth and creamy.
Stir in egg and vanilla. Combine flour and baking powder.
Add to margarine mixture; mix well.
Stir in cereal, peanut butter chips and peanuts.

title: sweet-sour broccoli salad
directions: In a bowl, combine the broccoli, peanuts, raisins and onion.

title: irish bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients, then add everything, except raisins. Mix well.
Add raisins.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: homemade hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Add mix to either hot water or hot milk.
Use 2 heaping tablespoons for cup or 3 heaping tablespoons for large mug.
Add marshmallows for an extra flavor.

title: food processor thousand island dressing
directions: Combine the egg, mustard, salt and vinegar in the bowl of the food processor fitted with steel blade.
Pulse just to blend. With the processor running, very slowly add the oil until the mixture emulsifies (or thickens). Add the catsup, onion, and pickle relish.
Pulse again just to blend.
Stir in heavy cream. If the dressing seems to be too thick, thin it with a little water or cream.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Mix together meat, soups, noodles and milk.
Sprinkle crushed potato chips over top.
Bake approximately 45 minutes at 350°. Use a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together except almonds.
Put in buttered casserole. Sprinkle almonds on top, then sprinkle corn flakes on top.
(Crush by hand.)
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese cornbread
directions: Defrost the broccoli and squeeze out water.
Mix together the cornbread mix, melted butter, onion, eggs and melted Cheez Whiz in a large bowl; mix well.
Add defrosted and drained broccoli; mix all together.
Pour into a greased large black skillet.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Mix together and put in a lightly greased 8 x 10-inch or 9 x 12-inch pan.
Let set overnight.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350° (glass pan at 325°). Let sit for 9 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla thoroughly.
Add soda and salt to flour (not sifted).
Stir to blend.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in candies.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserve 3 tablespoons of the juice. Combine sugar and flour, slowly stir in juice, then add cheese and pineapple. Mix well and put in greased one quart casserole. Combine margarine, crackers and a little grated cheese, sprinkle on top of casserole and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with Wheat Thins or crackers.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strip's alcoholic drink
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a bucket.
Serve over ice. Very refreshing!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onions in butter and broccoli for a few minutes.
Add cooked rice, soup and cheese mix and pour into a casserole dish. Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast according to yeast directions.
In separate bowl, mix sugar and melted butter. Combine all ingredients.
Place in a tight bowl in refrigerator as dough is better when thoroughly cold or made the night before.
Grease muffin tins.
Spoon in dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Makes 24 rolls.
Leftover dough can be kept in refrigerator for 3-4 days.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion.
Add one package dry taco mix and a little water.

title: lebanese stuffed squash
directions: Preparation of Squash:
Trim stem and blossom ends of squash. Wash squash; cut necks off squash, cutting necks into 1-inch pieces.
Bulb end of squash will be stuffed.
Core bulb end of squash or use in another recipe.
Squash core more easily when they are at room temperature.
To core squash, use a vegetable/apple corer.
Try not to puncture holes in squash while coring.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients; stir well.
Spoon into a greased, shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir and bake an additional 15 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cherry loaf cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions using required butter and eggs, but reducing water to 1/2 cup.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; spoon cherry pie filling over, folding evenly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake springs back when pressed lightly in center.
Sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, vanilla, coconut and condensed milk. Shape into balls or spread in baking dish. Chill until set. Melt together 1/2 cake paraffin and chocolate chips, stir well until combined. Dip balls into chocolate mixture covering completely; cool on wax paper.

title: shrimp scampi with wine
directions: Remove shells, if desired.
Place shrimp in one layer in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with onion and garlic.
Drizzle with wine. Dot with butter, sprinkle with parsley.
Broil turning once until done 4 to 5 minutes, depending on size of shrimp.
Shrimp should be pinkish when done.
Remove to platter and garnish with lemon.

title: sweet-n-sour meat loaf
directions: Mix all together well. Form in loaf and sprinkle with garlic salt on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, Crisco and oleo.
Beat the eggs, one at a time, and add to mixture.
Combine the flour and salt.
Add the salt-flour mixture alternately with the milk.
Fold in the flavoring by hand.
Bake at 350° in greased tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes, starting in a cold oven!
Do not open door while baking.
Remove from pan immediately.

title: 100 dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, brown sugar and butter 10 minutes.
Remove.
Add bits; stir.
Add marshmallow, nuts and vanilla.
Put in buttered pan (9 x 11-inch).

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs, milk and vanilla. Add soda and enough flour for a soft dough. Roll batter with rolling pin until dough is about 1/4-inch thick. Cut with biscuit cutter. Cut out center with thimble. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: chocolate dream pie
directions: Blend cookies and place in bottom of deep dish pie pan for crust.
Make chocolate pudding and chill 1/2 hour.
Fold marshmallows and cherries into pudding.
(Save 1 cherry for top.) Fold in 1/2 container Cool Whip.
Pour over crust.
Top with rest of Cool Whip, saving 1 tablespoon for center.
Sprinkle top with nuts and grated candy bar.
Put tablespoon of Cool Whip in center with one cherry.
Keep chilled until serving.

title: fudge sundae pie
directions: Put cream, semi-sweet chocolate pieces, miniature marshmallows and salt into a pot.
Stir over low heat until chocolate and marshmallows melt completely and mixture thickens (let cool).

title: hot clam dip
directions: Drain clams, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Beat cream cheese until smooth; add reserved liquid and next 3 ingredients.
Blend well. Stir in clams and 2 tablespoons green onions.
Spoon into a small shallow baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Brown the pork chops on both sides and arrange in a shallow 13 x 9-inch pan.
Lightly mix the bread cubes with the onions, butter, 1/4 cup water and the poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Combine the soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over the chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: layered cake
directions: Spray a 13-inch oblong cake pan with Pam.
Layer ingredients in order.
Make sure margarine is spaced over the top pretty evenly.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is fast and good served with ice cream while warm if possible.
I get better results if I spread layers rather than just dumping in ingredients.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and salt. Add boiling water and stir until shortening is dissolved. Add cold water. Dissolve yeast in 1/3 cup warm water. Add eggs to shortening mixture. Stir in yeast. Gradually add flour until fairly stiff (leaves side of bowl). Divide dough into 2 separate bowls (greased).
Cover with towel and refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour or more before shaping in rolls (you can knead 2 minutes or so).
Put butter on your hands before kneading.
Pinch off small portion of dough. Shape into small balls.
Place on greased baking sheet or pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until nicely browned.
Rolls can be frozen. Take out of freezer and let stand until rolls reach room temperature before baking.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, margarine and vanilla.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add coconut and pecans.
Cool until thick enough to spread; beat occasionally.

title: rich butter cake(1940)
directions: Cream the oil and sugar gradually.
Beat yolks until thick and add together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with milk; beat until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: buttermilk pound cake 1
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add gradually, alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chinese new year rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet or wok over medium heat.
Add chicken, cook and stir until lightly brown.
Add remaining ingredients, cook and stir until heated through.

title: cauliflower-vegetable casserole
directions: Wash cauliflower and break into flowerets.
Place all vegetables in a 2-quart covered casserole.
Melt the margarine in saucepan.
Add flour and stir.
Add the milk and cook until thickened. Remove from heat and add cheese and stir until melted. Pour over the vegetables. Cover and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water and drain.
In saucepan, melt butter and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add 2 cups milk. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add 1/4 cup chopped onions and 8 ounces cheese (cubed).
Stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: apple cider pheasant
directions: Put pheasant in pan and combine the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 350° until tender, basting often.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add brown sugar and 1/2 cup milk. Boil 5 minutes.
To that add 1 1/2 cups milk mixed with egg yolks, flour, salt and vanilla.
Cook until thick.
Pour into pie shell. Top with egg whites.
Brown for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: panchos hot dip
directions: Place everything except oil in the blender. Press chop 3 or 4 times. Add oil and heat until hot. Do not boil.

title: apple squares
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Beat in sugars, egg and vanilla. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture with chopped apple and nuts.
Spread in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a mix of sugar and cinnamon (about 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon or less).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or when top springs back.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry ground chuck.
Add onions, drain and add tomato sauce, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Steam buns and top with barbecue.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Spread chicken and veggies in dish.
Mix next four ingredients.
Pour over chicken and veggies.
Mix together baking mix, milk and margarine; pour on top.
Bake at 450° for 40 minutes in 2-quart dish.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix powdered sugar and peanut butter together to coarse meal consistency.
Mix and cook next 7 ingredients, over low heat to pudding consistency.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine beans, milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 can of onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and bake for 5 minutes more.

title: mom's sweet chili
directions: Saute the onions in 1 tablespoon of butter.
Add hamburg; fry and drain.
In a large pot add onions and hamburg mixture.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then simmer 1 to 2 hours or all day.

title: apricot salad
directions: Heat pineapple (juice included) enough to dissolve Jell-O. Cool to lukewarm.
Add buttermilk and stir thoroughly.
Add Cool Whip.
Whip and stir thoroughly.
Refrigerate.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Pack cucumbers and onions in large jar with a good lid.
Heat remaining ingredients over low heat, stirring frequently.
Do not overcook.
Pour mixture over pickles and onions and seal with the lid.
Store in the refrigerator for a few days.

title: ida lee sheffield's meat loaf
directions: Mix. Put 1/2 meat mixture, 1 pan.
Put on 1/8 pound mild Cheddar cheese, cut in strips and 2 large dill pickles, sliced. Put rest of mixture on.
Pour on 1 can tomato juice.
Cook 1 hour.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon baking mix and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup baking mix with brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is pea size.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: drop cheese biscuits
directions: Add enough water to the mix until smooth.
Add grated cheese. Spray cookie sheet with Pam and drop biscuits by tablespoons onto sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana-nut bread(twix cake and bread)
directions: Cream sugar, salt and butter thoroughly in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time, until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and nutmeg.
Combine bananas and milk.
Add parts of dry and liquid ingredients alternately to creamed ingredients, blending well after each addition.
Add nuts; mix briefly.
Turn into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
Turn out on cooling rack; wrap in plastic or foil when cool.

title: one bowl chocolate fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate and milk in large bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted. Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Spread in foil-lined 8-inch square pan.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.

title: classic apple pie
directions: Mix flour and lemon zest eogether with whisk in a medium bowl.
With pastry cutter or 2 knives, cut in butter until dough resembles coarse meal.
Add ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time, and blend until dough can be gathered into a ball.
Divide dough in half, flatten into disks, and wrap tightly in plastic wrap. Refrigerate 1 hour or until firm.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown the egg noodles in the Crisco in a heavy-gauge saucepan over low heat.
Add the rice, chicken broth and butter.
Bring to a boil.
Stir until butter is melted.
Turn heat to low.
Cover with a lid.
Cook about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add salt as needed.

title: lemon pecan oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda and salt in a bowl.
Add butter, sugar, egg and lemon rind.
Beat until smooth (about 2 minutes). Fold in pecans and rolled oats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: nellie's fresh coconut cake
directions: Cook cake as directed on box.
Split layer of cake and cool. Spoon first filling and then second filling between each layer, except for the top layer.
Put icing on top and sides, then your 1 bag of frozen coconut on top and sides.

title: amish coconut cream cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
While cake is hot, punch holes in cake.
Pour Eagle Brand milk and cream of coconut over top. Cool.
Spread with Cool Whip and top with flaked coconut.
This is moist and delicious!

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In large bowl, put peanut butter and blend in melted butter. Add Rice Krispies and powdered sugar; mix well with hands until all ingredients are blended.
Roll in balls.
Melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and the paraffin.
Roll balls in chocolate chips and the paraffin and set to dry on a waxed paper-lined cookie sheet.
Makes about 40 to 43 balls.

title: tri-tip dinner for 4
directions: Roll Tri-Tip in Pappy's seasoning.
Light the coals and let them get hot.
Take Tri-Tip and Pappy's seasoning and season as desired.
Put meat on the grill and close lid.
Wrap potatoes separately in foil and put in oven at 350° to 400°.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes, depending on size of potatoes.
Get large pot.
Boil water and put corn in.
Cut up lettuce, tomatoes and shredded cheese.
Combine and put in refrigerator to chill.
Tri-Tip need to cook 30 minutes on 1 side, 30 minutes on the other side (lid closed).
When Tri-Tip is done, cut up slices as desired.
Set table.
Butter corn.
Take out potatoes and salad.
Enjoy dinner, seasoning as desired.

title: pineapple-cheese-pecan salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into saucepan.
Layer cheese, pineapple and pecans in large bowl.
Beat egg, flour, sugar and salt together.
Add this mixture to pineapple juice and cook slowly, stirring constantly, until it thickens (over medium heat).
Pour over layers and mix.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: crabmeat ball
directions: Mold into ball.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: ho ho cake
directions: Bake cake mix in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Cool.

title: rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm potato water.
Add remaining water.
Mix in ingredients and knead until smooth.

title: chocolate caramel nut bar
directions: Melt caramels with 1/2 cup milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Combine remaining milk, mix and butter.
Mix well; press half of cake mixture into bottom of greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Sprinkle 1 cup walnuts (chopped) and chocolate pieces over crust.
Top with teaspoonful of remaining cake mixture. Press gently into caramel mixture.
Sprinkle with rest of walnuts, pressing lightly into top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Refrigerate.
Cut into bars to serve.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: freezer oatmeal pancakes
directions: Turn oats into deep bowl.
Stir in milk.
Let stand until milk is absorbed, about 1/2 hour.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt; stir in brown sugar and mix well.
Sprinkle flour mixture over top of oats.
Add melted butter and eggs; stir just until combined.
Do not overbeat.
Cook on hot griddle.

title: beer batter for fish
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks with oil.
Add flour and beer to mix.
Beat well.
Beat egg whites and add to mix, beating well. Coat fillet with flour.
Dip in batter and fry in deep hot fat (340°) until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: bertha's ginger cookies(this is a pre-civil war family recipe)
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, molasses and lard.
Dissolve in the hot water the soda, cocoa, ginger and salt.
Add enough flour to thicken; it usually takes about 5 cups.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
When cool, cover with boiled icing.

title: peanut-marshmallow treats
directions: Spread peanut butter on crackers.
Top with marshmallows. Place on cookie sheet and broil in oven about 3 minutes.
Serve warm and enjoy!
Serves 2.

title: baked savory pork chops
directions: In medium-size bowl, combine ketchup, water and brown sugar; blend well.
Arrange pork chops, single layered, in a baking dish. Place a lemon slice on top of each chop.
Pour sauce over all. Bake at 350° for 1 hour (maybe more depending on the thickness of the chops).
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix sugars, vanilla and eggs well.
Add oil, then zucchini and mix.
Stir in dry ingredients and nuts.
Do not overbeat.
Put in 2 greased and floured loaf pans and bake in 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Makes 2 medium or 1 large and 1 small loaf.

title: barbecued spareribs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine, stir in remaining ingredients.
Let simmer for a few minutes.
Parboil
ribs
30 minutes.
Dip ribs in sauce and place in baking
pan.
Bake
at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Baste with sauce.

title: violet's salad
directions: Mix all together except cookies. Before serving, crush cookies and add 2/3 to the salad.
Garnish with remaining crushed cookies.

title: sour cream potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onion in 3 cups water until tender. Add milk, bouillon cubes and margarine.
Mix flour with sour cream and add to the soup.
Stir constantly until thickened.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Serves 8-10.

title: spiced cider
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes. Add lemon juice and orange juice. Serve.

title: champagne punch
directions: Put all ingredients into large punch bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Add ice.
Serve chilled.

title: zesty franks
directions: For Sauce:
In a small saucepan, combine beer and cornstarch, then stir in barbecue sauce, apple jelly and hot pepper sauce. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Then cook and stir for 2 minutes more.

title: oriental stir-fry chicken
directions: Heat oil in wok. Add garlic and ginger. Cook chicken breast until done, then add vegetables. Cook until vegetables are tender to your preference, stirring continuously. Add soy sauce and serve.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake per instructions on box.
Prepare pudding per instructions on box.
Cool cake.
Punch holes all over cake. Spread pudding on top.

title: pecan crispies
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Combine flour, salt and soda.
Mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Great for Christmas!

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Combine butter, egg, Sucaryl and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is great for those who want to find their waistline.

title: homestead salad
directions: Cook and drain mixed vegetables.
Add to celery, green pepper, onion and red beans in large mixing bowl.
Cook mustard, sugar, salt, flour and vinegar, stirring, until thick.
Cool.
Pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate.
Keeps a week.
Freezes well.

title: hobo pie
directions: Brown hamburger in pan with onion until onion is cooked. Place in 5-quart oval Corning dish.
Make sure you drain fat. Put vegetables over meat.
Peel potatoes and place in water.
Boil until done.
Make mashed potatoes.
Scoop over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or 45 minutes until potatoes are a little golden brown.
Serve.

title: summer sausage
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well and chill 8 hours or overnight. Shape meat into 5 logs.
Wrap each log in one layer of cheesecloth.
Place on a rack in a shallow baking pan and bake at 200° for 6 hours.
Chill sausage 8 hours or overnight.
Store in refrigerator.

title: mozzarella dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 10 minutes on High in microwave or 20 minutes in 350° oven, until hot and melted. Stir and serve with crackers.

title: icebox cake
directions: Whip heavy cream until it stands in peaks when beater is lifted up.
Have your favorite deep casserole ready and spoon a layer of whipped cream into bottom of casserole dish.
Then place a layer of cookies on top of cream and thereafter a layer of cookies and a layer of cream until cookies are used up.
Last layer should be a layer of cream.

title: tuna cheese ball
directions: Rinse tuna in colander and drain.
Put softened cream cheese in a large bowl.
Add tuna, chopped onion and chopped celery.
Mix well with hands.
Pat into a ball and coat with chili powder or chopped dried parsley.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling water for approximately 5 minutes. Drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream. Stir in carrots, stuffing mix and butter. Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 17 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. Spoon vegetable mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining stuffing mixture over vegetables. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and cocoa.
Mix well.
Add the slightly beaten egg, milk and vanilla. Do not heat.

title: surprise carrot cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and egg, mixing until well blended.
Set aside.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Stir in flour.
Add water and cook until thick.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix gently and cover with bread crumbs dotted with butter.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: mom's spuds
directions: Mix together.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat marinade
directions: Marinate 2 hours at least.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling and pineapple, juice and all, in a 13 x 9-inch pan; spread evenly over bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over fruit.
Pour melted margarine over mixture in pan. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour until golden brown.

title: polish reuben casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion and mustard in bowl.
Blend well. Spread sauerkraut in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with uncooked noodles. Spoon soup mixture evenly over top.
Top with sausage, then cheese.

title: cheeseburger macaroni
directions: Boil macaroni until tender.
While macaroni is still hot, cut up cheese and put it in pan with macaroni.
Cover the pan and let the cheese melt.
Pour cooked ground beef over macaroni.

title: kraut vinegar
directions: Boil and pour over tightly-packed cabbage. Seal tightly.

title: baked chicken and corn bread dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chicken; mix well.
Pour one-half of dressing into a greased baking dish.
Remove chicken from bone.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Add remaining dressing. Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: meal on the grill
directions: Divide hamburger into 4 hamburger patties and place on tinfoil. Slice potatoes and put 1 sliced whole potato on top of patty.
Put peas in circle on outside of patty.
Cover everything with the foil and put on the grill, 10 to 15 minutes on each side.

title: rice cheese bake
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl; toss gently to mix.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and garlic
directions: In a skillet, combine the oil, garlic, parsley, bay leaf and cayenne pepper.
Simmer for 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not burn!
Add chicken broth, shrimp, wine, lemon juice and a few drops of Kitchen Bouquet.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Thicken with a cornstarch and water mixture to a gravy consistency.

title: sausage bean casserole
directions: Saute onion, bell pepper and sausage.
Combine beans, sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate butter crunch(almond roca)
directions: Line 15x10x1 inch jelly roll pan with foil, extending edges over sides of pan.
Generously grease both the foil and a narrow metal spatula with butter.

title: twice-baked garlic sweet potatoes
directions: Remover outer covering from garlic; do not peel or separate cloves.
Wrap garlic in aluminum foil coated with cooking spray. Place garlic and sweet potatoes on a baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes; let cool 10 minutes.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark and chocolate chips in microwave or on stove; stir often.
Add peanuts and stir until blended.
Drop by tablespoons onto waxed paper.
(May butter wax paper, if you prefer.)
Refrigerate until set.

title: slow cooker turkey and dressing
directions: Coat inside of a 4-quart slow-cooker with cooking spray.
Add stuffing mix, onion, celery, and cranberries.
Combine broth and melted butter.
Pour over stuffing and stir gently.
Remove string from turkey breast; rinse turkey breast.
Place turkey in slow cooker on top of stuffing.
Combine salt, pepper, and thyme; sprinkle over turkey.
Cover and cook on HIGH 1 hour. Reduce to LOW and cook 5 to 6 hours or until a meat thermometer inserted in turkey registers 170°.

title: southwestern salsa dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave. Add salsa. Stir well.
Best if made a day ahead and refrigerated overnight.
Stir and serve with chips.

title: pineapple carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Gradually add jello mixture to sour cream until well blended.
Chill until mixture begins to set.
Stir in pineapple, grated carrots and nuts.
Pour into lightly oiled 2-quart mold.
Chill at least 4 hours.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: carrot cake
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350° in angel food pan.

title: country chicken casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken and set aside.
Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Stir in everything but bread crumbs.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 375° until it bubbles.
You may use 2 cans deboned chicken instead of a whole chicken.

title: famous fried fish
directions: Soak fish covered with buttermilk with lemon slice in refrigerator in covered container for 2 hours (to remove fishy taste).
Drain milk from fish; cut fillets into triangle.
Roll in plain flour.
Let dry on toweling.
Combine pancake mix (dry) with club soda.
Mix to consistency of buttermilk; dip floured fillets in mix.
Fry in hot oil 4 minutes each side.
Drain on toweling. Arrange 1 layer on cookie sheet.
Keep warm in 250° oven until all pieces have been fried.

title: homemade cereal
directions: Bring milk to a boil over medium heat.
Add rice and sugar and cook an additional 5 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add green pepper and onion; cook until onion is transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Place mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish (covered).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello in boiling water.
Add cranberry sauce, cut into small pieces, stirring until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients and refrigerate in large bowl or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Stir occasionally so fruit and nuts are well mixed.
Make the day before needed to properly set.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Simmer for about 1 hour.

title: reese's mini cakes
directions: Cream first 6 ingredients together.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spray tart pans well with Pam.
Put tablespoon of dough in the bottom of the pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Put mini Reese's cup in immediately after removing from the oven. Allow to set before removing from pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers into crumbs.
Add baking powder to crumbs.
In a mixing bowl mix butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each.
Alternate dry ingredients with milk; mix well.
Add coconut and pecans.
Pour in tube pan and bake 1 1/2 hours in 300° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well.
Bake in loaf pans at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: escalloped sweet potato and apple casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes well.
Peel and slice.
Core and slice apples. Arrange potatoes and apples in alternate layers in buttered casserole dish, sprinkling each layer of potatoes with salt and each layer of apples with brown sugar.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° until both potatoes and apples are very tender and flavors are well blended (about 45 minutes).

title: italian meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in a loaf pan; bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Drain.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cappi's corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl that you can put in the microwave.
Microwave for about a minute, then stir.
Repeat until all ingredients are mixed together and is hot.
Very good.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When done, remove from oven.
While hot, punch lots of holes in top with handle of wooden spoon.
Mix condensed sweetened milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over hot cake; let cool.
Cover with Cool Whip and Angel Flake coconut.

title: easy chocolate mousse pie
directions: Prepare graham cracker crust; set aside.
Beat cream cheese and cocoa in large mixer bowl until fluffy and well blended.
Gradually add confectioners sugar; blend well.
Stir in vanilla.
Whip the cream until stiff; fold into cheese mixture.
Pour into cooled crust; chill until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Yields 8 servings.

title: gourmet pecans
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla, in saucepan and bring to a boil. Boil until almost dry. Add the vanilla. It will be dry. Pour out onto buttered wax paper.

title: super nut bars
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and pat in shallow pan.
Beat egg and spread all over.
Then sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar over this and lastly the nuts.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: company pickles(bread and butter)
directions: Wash cucumbers, cover whole cucumbers with boiling water and allow to stand until next morning. Then drain. Repeat this procedure the next 3 mornings.

title: applesauce, chocolate chip, peanut butter cookies
directions: Beat well the margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add and beat applesauce and peanut butter.
Mix together flour, salt and soda and add to mixture.
With a wooden spoon, stir in oats, chocolate chips and nuts.
Add extra flour, if needed (depends on the applesauce).
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together and roll into 3 or 4 balls.
Mix 1/2 cup chopped pecans.
Sprinkle paprika and chili powder on pecans. Roll cheese balls in mixture.

title: pistachio pudding dessert
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and margarine well.
Pat in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Beat the powdered sugar and cream cheese well.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip and beat.
Spread on cooled first layer.

title: christmas cheer punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice.
Pour into punch bowl.
Add remaining fruit juices and ginger ale.
Float small scoops of sherbet on top.
To serve, ladle into punch bowl as needed.

title: lazy man's beef stew
directions: Put all the ingredients in a deep baking dish.
Season to taste.
Add soup; after soup has been added to the ingredients, rinse one can with water, adding the water to the stew.
Place stew in a 375° oven for about 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until tender.

title: vegetable lasagna
directions: Cook vegetables and garlic in oil until tender.
Stir in pasta sauce and oregano.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Combine cottage cheese and Parmesan.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer 1/2 of each of noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella.
Repeat layering. Top with chopped parsley.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover; bake 15 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes in a large, shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients in a jar; cover and shake well.
Pour over tomato slices.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Serves 8.

title: toffee bars
directions: In a large bowl measure sugar and butter; mix until soft.
Add all other ingredients including egg yolk only.
Pat evenly in a 5 x 11-inch pan.
In a cup with fork, beat egg white slightly. Brush over top of dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Pat down lightly. Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients until light.
Mix together remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Spread in ungreased pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: potato delights
directions: Thaw potatoes; melt margarine into chicken soup and onions. Add 1/2 of the grated cheese.
Stir potatoes into this mixture and put in large baking dish for 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Remove cover and sprinkle remaining cheese on top and bake for 15 minutes longer.
Combine corn flakes with a little butter and spread over top when done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix ham and pork together with their juices.
In a mixer, combine eggs, sugar, bread crumbs and milk; blend well.
Add meat into the mixture, working in with hands.
Shape into loaf. Decorate top with half pineapple slices and cherries.
Bake in baking dish at 300° for 2 1/2 hours or longer.
Baste often with 1/2 cup pineapple juice.
Serves 12.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix together Coke, mustard, catsup and Tabasco sauce.
Pour over raw chicken that has been seasoned.
Cook on top of stove in a skillet with the lid on until tender.

title: banana split fondue
directions: Break candy into pieces.
Place pieces of candy and milk in fondue saucepan.
Heat directly over medium flame, stirring occasionally, until chocolate melts.
Spear marshmallows and bananas with fondue forks or long picks, and hold cherries by the stems when dipping into melted chocolate; place on wax paper.
If chocolate mixture gets too thick, stir in 1 or more tablespoons of milk.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: the churros(and chocolate for churro dunking)
directions: Place the chocolate and half the milk in a pan and heat, stirring, until the chocolate has melted. Dissolve the cornstarch in the remaining milk and whisk into the chocolate with the sugar. Cook on low heat, whisking constantly, until the chocolate is thickened, about five minutes. Add extra cornstarch if it doesn't start to thicken after 5 minutes. Remove and whisk smooth. Pour and server in cups or bowls for dunking churros. Do not pour over churros, but use the mix for dunking churros after every bite. Served warm.

title: thimble cookies
directions: Sift together the flour and salt.
Cream the butter and gradually add brown sugar; cream well.
Blend in unbeaten egg yolk and vanilla.
Add the dry ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white and then into finely chopped pecans.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and make a thumbprint in the center of the cookie; use floured thumb or thimble.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(I use a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 35 minutes.)

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix together in large roaster.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Stir often.
Cool and freeze.

title: cranberry orange bread
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, orange peel, orange juice and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir.
Fold in cranberries and walnuts.
Bake at 350° in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan for 60 minutes.
Wrap and store overnight.

title: waldorf boats
directions: Combine apples, nuts and raisins.
Stir in lemon juice and mayonnaise.
Spoon into celery.
Chill.

title: tillie's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, milk and syrup in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until it forms a soft ball dropped in cup of cold water.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat with a spoon until thick enough to spread in buttered dish.
When cool, cut in 1-inch squares.

title: abracadabra parfait(makes 6 servings)
directions: Finely roll 13 cookies.
Scoop 1/3 cup chocolate ice cream into each of 6 (8-ounce) parfait glasses.
Layer each with 1 tablespoon fudge sauce and 1 tablespoon cookie crumbs.
Top with 1/3 cup vanilla ice cream, remaining fudge sauce and cookie crumbs.
Freeze until serving time.
To serve, garnish with whipped topping and remaining cookies.

title: corned beef soup
directions: In a large pot boil fordhooks until almost done.
Add tomatoes and return to boil.
Add potatoes, onion and carrots and boil gently until vegetables are nearly done.
Add corned beef.
Add water along with salt and pepper to desired consistency and taste. Simmer over low heat, adding corn about 15 minutes before serving.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook mashed potatoes as you desire (about 6 servings).
Brown the ground beef and season to taste.
In a medium to large casserole dish, layer beef, potatoes and shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is golden brown (about 20 minutes).

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: In deep bowl, mix shortening, salt and sugar.
Pour boiling water over this.
Stir until dissolved and cool.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Add to first mixture.
Add egg and beat.
Add flour to make a stiff dough.
Refrigerate, covered, overnight.

title: orange coconut bread
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix together the slightly beaten egg, orange rind, orange juice, melted shortening and coconut.
Add this mixture to flour mixture and stir just enough to moisten.
Place in greased and floured pan and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: coffee punch
directions: Scald milk. Add coffee, sugar, spices. Chill put ice cream which has been scooped into small pieces into punch bowl.
Add coffee and milk mixture and almond extract. Stir to mix. Yield 12 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Put tortillas into pan of hot enchilada sauce.
Take out and put a small amount of meat that has been prepared.
Add a small amount of grated cheese.
Roll up; put into a pan and pour enchilada sauce over this.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Put in oven and cook at 325° for about 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Add applesauce and mix well.
Stir dry ingredients (flour, spices, baking powder, salt and cocoa).
Add soda water alternately with dry ingredients.
Bake 1 hour at 350° if using Bundt pan.

title: marinated grilled vegetables
directions: Cut all vegetables into bite-sized pieces and put into large bowl.
Dice garlic (powder can be substituted for fresh garlic). Pour salad dressing over vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours or overnight.
Put vegetables on skewers and grill.
Nice side dish for steaks, chops or burgers.

title: hunters stew
directions: Brown meat and onions in large pan.
When meat is browned, add 3 to 4 cups water and all other ingredients.
Cover and cook slowly until potatoes are done.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly; shape into 2 loaves. Put into pans. Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium-size bowl.
Pour into a 9 x 13 pan and bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: chinese pork chops
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Season chops well with salt and brown on both sides in oil.
Place chops in baking dish; cover with onions. Combine soy sauce, orange and lemon juices, mushrooms, ginger and garlic powder; pour over chops.
Cover and bake 35 minutes.
Add green pepper, chestnuts and lemon slices.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes longer.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken (pressure cooker is best) until tender with salt to taste.
Remove chicken; debone.
(Extra chicken is ready for chicken salad.)
Bring broth to a rolling boil in pressure cooker or heavy large container.
Season to taste with salt.
Add dumplings, one at a time.
Stir often or shake pan to keep separate while cooking.
(Takes very short time to cook.
Almost done by time last dumplings are added.
Will have a "glossy" look.)
Add about 2 cups chopped chicken and black pepper to taste.
Serve immediately.
The more you use this recipe the better your dumplings will be.
The dumplings absorb some of your broth.
You may not need to use all of one batch.
You do not want them to be dry.
Leave "soupy".
The secret is to use lots of flour and roll paper thin.
Great for fat restricted diets. You can use less oil and still have good dumplings.

title: apple crunch
directions: Pour sugar and cinnamon over apples in baking dish.
Mix next 5 ingredients.
Mix melted margarine into dry ingredients; then sprinkle over apples. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, or until browned.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in an oblong dish or pan (9 x 13-inch), greased, in order they are listed.
Do not stir anything.
Just pour each on top of the other.
Do not drain pineapple.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: snow peak devil's food cake
directions: Sift fine the flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in mixing bowl.
Drop in shortening.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat with mixer.
Add eggs and beat well.
Pour in a 10-inch prepared square cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup of chocolate chips on top of batter. Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top of batter.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: strawberry cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add eggs and mix until blended.
Pour into crust and bake at 350 degrees for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool and refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.
Spread sour cream over cheesecake.
Top with strawberries, stem side down and drizzle with jelly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: taco soup
directions: Saute first 3 ingredients.
