Add remaining.
Simmer together until flavors mix well.
Crock-pot is good! Serves 12.

title: congealed german sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water and then cold water.
Add drained sauerkraut and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce with mayo.

title: pluck it cake
directions: Coat biscuit pieces with 3/4 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.
Mix 1 cup sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, water and margarine together.
Use to make syrup.
Bring to boil.
In Pam-sprayed Bundt pan, put in 1/2 of coated biscuit pieces.
Pour half of syrup over biscuits.
Put in remaining biscuit pieces. Pour remaining syrup.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Turn onto serving tray and enjoy.

title: marzetti special(serves 25 to 30)
directions: Brown meats, chopped celery, onions and green pepper.
Add small amount of water and cook until tender.
Add vegetables and seasonings to noodles (which have been cooked in salt water about 20 minutes).
Add 2/3 of cheese.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle remaining 1/3 of cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots until almost tender.
Saute onions in margarine.
Layer carrots in a 2-quart, buttered casserole alternately with sliced Velveeta.
Pour onions and margarine over carrots.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into ball; shape.
Roll in chopped pecans (optional).
Serve with small, round crackers.

title: cinnamon acorn squash rings
directions: Place squash in an ungreased jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until tender and well browned.
Serves 6 at 124 calories each serving.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn chowder
directions: Simmer water, onions, celery, potatoes and parsley until half cooked (about 10 minutes).
Add milk and bring soup just to the boiling point, but do not boil.
Add corn and seasonings.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat.
Add cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Add baking powder and milk.
Bake in three 9-inch round pans at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in heavy skillet until brown. Drain off fat.
Add other ingredients.
Pour in casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine eggs with next 7 ingredients.
Fold in crabmeat and shape into cakes.
Coat with additional crumbs.
Refrigerate one hour, or until ready to cook.
Saute in 1/2 butter/1/2 margarine 3 to 4 minutes per side or until delicately browned.
(Backfin or lump crabmeat is best.)

title: grandma's chicken
directions: Rinse and season cut up chicken. Place in 9 x 13 baking dish. Put sliced onions on top. In saucepan, heat soup, milk, butter and seasonings until butter melts. Pour over chicken and onions. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Stir sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Microwave on High 4 minutes. Stir in nuts.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes until light brown. Add butter and vanilla.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes. Add soda until light and foamy.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and spread.

title: cold corn salad
directions: Mix and let stand 2 hours in refrigerator.
Serve cold.

title: hot, sweet and sour owens sausage balls
directions: Combine sausage, bread crumbs, chopped onion, egg and 1 tablespoon of soy sauce thoroughly and form into balls about the size of a walnut.
Set aside.
Saute chopped bell pepper in margarine for about 1 minute; add orange juice, Cointreau, marmalade and vinegar.
Continue to cook until sauce is quite thick.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: fudge nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Melt chocolate and butter together.
Beat eggs and sugar together until light and fluffy.
Should form soft peaks.
Stir in chocolate and vanilla. Mix in flour, salt and nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan. Do not overbake.

title: chicken-cabbage bake
directions: Arrange cabbage in baking dish.
Put chicken on top.
Add onion rings, water, consomme, salt, nutmeg and pepper.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover; up temperature to 375° for 15 minutes, until brown.
Serves 4.

title: party meat balls
directions: Mix meat, soup mix, crackers and egg.
Form small balls. Brown in margarine.
Melt ketchup and jellies together in slow cooker or electric skillet and add meatballs.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with small biscuits or alone.
These are great at parties and the men love 'em!

title: "put it in the pot roast"
directions: Line large casserole with aluminum foil (leave enough overlap to close and seal).
Place roast in casserole.
Do not salt and pepper.
Mix mushroom and onion soups together.
Sprinkle Worcestershire sauce on roast.
Pour soup mixture over roast and seal the foil.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.

title: golden party punch
directions: Combine fruit juices.
Pour over ice cubes or ice ring, adding ginger ale just before serving.
Serves 50 to 60.

title: sunday brunch frittata
directions: Heat bacon at medium heat in heavy saucepan. Add garlic and onion and cook under low heat until it browns. Add spinach and cook until it wilts. Combine eggs in a large bowl; stir well. Add wine, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons cheese. Add spinach and bacon mixture. Heat oil in a medium nonstick skillet over low heat. Add egg mixture and cook 15 minutes or until set (DO NOT STIR). Sprinkle top with remaining Parmesan cheese. Broil for 3 minutes until top is set.

title: apple crunch cake
directions: Mix all ingredients (except apples) well, then stir in apples. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cheese ball
directions: In mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add sugars, beat until combined then add vanilla and stir in chocolate chips.
Place cream cheese mixture on wax paper or a plate and shape into a ball.
refrigerate for at least 1 hour. right before serving roll cheese ball in pecans.
Serve with graham crackers.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, chicken, ginger and dried red pepper in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes.
Put 2 tablespoons oil in large skillet or wok over high heat.
Add chicken mixture. Stir-fry until chicken is no longer pink.
Remove chicken.
Put 1 teaspoon oil in skillet.
Add onions and carrots.
Stir-fry until crisp tender.
Add snow peas, mushrooms, green pepper and green onion.
Stir-fry until crisp tender.
Add chicken; stir-fry until heated thoroughly.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate applesauce cake
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar together.
Add the applesauce and all dry ingredients.
Bake in greased floured pan for about 1 hour in a 350°
oven.

title: snack mix
directions: In a a large bowl that is sprayed with Pam, combine Rice Chex, Wheat Chex, Cheerios, peanuts and pretzels.
Stir in melted white chocolate.
Stir well.
Then add M&M candy.
Spread on waxed paper to dry.
Break into pieces.
This can also be frozen. Enjoy!

title: applesauce oat muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Line 12 medium muffin cups with paper baking cups. Combine oats, flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Add combined applesauce, oil, egg whites and vanilla; mix just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fill muffin cups almost full.
Bake 18 to 22 minutes.

title: wine cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and beat for 2 minutes on high speed.
Pour batter in oiled angel food cake pan. Sprinkle top with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Remove from oven and immediately drizzle with glaze.

title: rum toddy
directions: Combine boiling water, rum and Hot Buttered Drink Mix in a mug. Stir well.
Garnish with cinnamon stick if desired.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown
the
ground beef and drain well.
Layer the beef in bottom of
casserole
dish.
Sprinkle the chopped onions on top of beef.
Drain the Mexicorn and vegetables, reserving the liquids. Layer the Mexicorn
on the top of the onions and the vegetables on top of
the Mexicorn.
Pour about 1/4 cup of the reserved liquids on
top
of the mixed vegetable layer.
Next, spread on the mushroom
soup.
Cover
the top of the casserole with the Tater Tots.
Bake at 400° until bubbling.

title: peanut-butter crisscross cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Have cookie sheets ready.
Mix flour and baking soda.

title: barbecue mix and sauce
directions: Mix all together.
Rub oil on meat and then sprinkle with this mixture.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Mix margarine, cream cheese, water or cream, vanilla and salt. Slowly add confectioners sugar.
Mix on high speed until creamy and spreadable.
Will frost one 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: chewy macaroons
directions: Bake at 350° until light brown. Remove from pan with spatula dipped in water.

title: oatmeal coconut pecan cookies
directions: Combine shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix well.
Do not use a mixer.
Add flour, salt, soda and oats.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and place on slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven. Makes about 6 or 7 dozen.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Grind tomatoes, onions and peppers fine.
Cover with boiling water and boil 15 minutes.
Drain well.
Put vinegar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice together.
Bring to a boil; strain out spices. Add salt, mustard seed and sugar to vinegar mixture.
Add to vegetables.
Boil 20 minutes.
Put into hot, sterilized jars; seal and process in water bath.

title: corn bake
directions: Saute the onion and green pepper in the margarine.
Mix together vegetables.
Add the eggs and Jiffy corn mix. Mix to this, sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in 2-quart casserole. Top with rest of cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl beat eggs until foamy. Beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Add melted butter. Stir in chocolate bits and nuts.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 1 hour.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: lemon-garlic chicken breasts
directions: Combine lemon juice and garlic powder. Marinate or brush on each piece of chicken, coating thoroughly. Shake off excess and sprinkle with lemon pepper. Cook in 1 tablespoon of oil until browned and tender. Serve on bed of wild rice.

title: lemon angel cake
directions: Heat cake in oven until warm through.
Boil 1/2 cup sugar and juice of 3 lemons for 5 minutes.
Stick holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon and pour mix over cake.

title: pronto pups (corn dogs)
directions: Wash wieners in hot water to remove oil.
Dry thoroughly. Combine all ingredients to make batter.
Using a fork or stick for a handle, roll wiener in batter and drop into hot oil.

title: fried wontons
directions: Mix crab meat and cream cheese.
Put into wraps.
Pinch ends of wraps together and baste edges with egg whites.
Deep fry until light brown in real hot grease!!!

title: red beans and rice - louisiana style
directions: Cook beans in a large pot.
Add all ingredients except sausage and rice.
Simmer until beans are tender and slightly thickened. Slice the sausage into 1/2-inch thick slices.
Put into beans and cook for another 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked rice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs; add cottage cheese and frozen broccoli.
Stir in dry cornmeal mix.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: dirty rice
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cook cream of mushroom soup (do not add but 1/2 can water).
Cook Minute rice.
Mix all ingredients together.
Should be creamy, not runny.
Can be served by itself as a main dish.

title: broccoli bake
directions: 1. Mix first five ingredients. Put in large casserole dish and cover with stuffing.
2. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: iced brownies deluxe
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate in double boiler; set aside. Combine eggs and sugar beating well. Add flour and baking powder after sifting together, mix well. Add chocolate mixture, pecans and vanilla. Pour into 2 grease 9x13x2 pans and bake at 325° for 20 min.
Remove brownies from oven and cover top with marshmallows. Return to oven for 5 min. or until marshmallows melt.
Ice while warm.
Yield 6 dz.

title: cottage pudding
directions: Sift together
the
flour,
salt and baking powder.
Add the sugar and
mix
to
a stiff batter with the egg, shortening and milk.
Bake
in a shallow, greased dish about half an hour. Serve hot with sauce.

title: red velvet cake and icing
directions: Grease four cake pans. Sprinkle with flour. Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Make a paste of cocoa and vinegar. Add to butter mixture. Sift salt, soda and flour together. Add to mixture, alternating with buttermilk. Add vanilla and coloring. Bake layers at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pecan ritz pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Fold in crackers and pecans.
Pour into a well-buttered dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Top with 1/2 pint whipping cream whipped stiff with 2 tablespoons sugar.

title: mexican chalupas
directions: Separate and rinse beans.
Bring pinto beans to a full rolling boil and drain water off.
Add new water and stew meat.
Boil for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat shreds easily.

title: wild rice chicken supreme
directions: Prepare rice as directed.
Spoon into a shallow ovenproof serving dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons of butter in saucepan and saute chopped onion until tender.
Remove from heat and blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Quickly stir a small amount of sauce mixture into slightly beaten egg yolk, then return egg to the sauce.
Add diced, cooked chicken, pimiento and lemon juice.
Heat thoroughly.
Pour over rice.
Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: veggie bars
directions: Press the rolls into a 10 x 15-inch ungreased pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise, dressing mix, dill weed and garlic powder well.
Spread mixture on cooled crust.
Top with the vegetables, cut up fine, and the grated cheese.
Press lightly so veggies stick.
(You can also use mushrooms, onions, tomatoes, etc.)

title: fake fillets
directions: Mix
thoroughly
all
ingredients.
Shape
meat mixture into 1-inch thick patties. Wrap bacon around each one.
Fasten with toothpicks.
Broil each side at least 5 minutes.

title: quick chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients in a 1 gallon container of ice cream freezer.
Add milk to reach fill line.
Freeze in ice cream freezer until thick.
Store in freezer a short time, if needed for added thickness.

title: frozen popsicles
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into molds.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: orange cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine cream cheese, butter and orange peel.
Beat until light.
Gradually add sugar.
If necessary, add orange juice to make of spreading consistency.

title: hermits
directions: Mix thoroughly the shortening, brown sugar and eggs. Stir in cold coffee.

title: chicken and vegetable bake
directions: Mix all ingredients in Dutch oven.
Cook over medium gas flame 30 minutes or until heated through, stirring occasionally. Serves a crowd!

title: homemade applesauce
directions: Choose the tartest apples in season.
Wash and section, leaving stems and core in for flavor.
Cook in a heavy saucepan with a little water in bottom until mushy.
Run apples through colander.
Add sugar to taste and lemon juice if needed for tartness.
Great fun with younger children and delicious as well.

title: valdena's poppy seed dressing(special diet)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Store in a pint jar.
Makes 16 servings, 1 tablespoon per serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the meat, celery, onion, tomato soup, milk, catsup, bread crumbs and the beaten eggs thoroughly.
Season to taste.
Put in a loaf pan.
Top the loaf with 1 tablespoon melted butter and 2 tablespoons tomato soup.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: roskamp's famous mint dessert
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and mix with butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan to form bottom crust.
Cover with softened ice cream. Top with jar of hot fudge (not heated.)
Cover with Cool Whip. Store in freezer until ready to serve.

title: drunken wieners
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; simmer 1 hour.
Add the hot dogs; simmer 2 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.
Reheat to serve.

title: bloody mary mix
directions: In a blender, combine first 4 ingredients together. Blend until smooth. Season the mixture to taste with the Worcestershire sauce, hot sauce, salt and pepper.
Store the mixture in a nonreactive container. Refrigerate the mixture for at least 6 hours before serving. Yield: About 1 quart.

title: the big bad wolf's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with shortening.
Melt margarine and chocolate in a large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the sugar, flour, baking powder, vanilla and nuts.
Add the eggs and beat well with an eggbeater.
Pour the batter into pan.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Remove the pan from oven and place it on a rack.
When brownies are cool, cut them in squares.
Makes 16 brownies.

title: lemon pudding cake(makes its own pudding)
directions: In a medium size bowl, beat egg yolks until thick.
Add lemon juice, lemon peel and melted butter.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; add alternately with milk, beating constantly.
In separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Set dish in a pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes, or until lightly browned. Serve warm topped with Cool Whip.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: orange glazed pork chops
directions: Stir stuffing crumbs, vegetable seasoning packet and 1 1/2 c. hot water, oranges and 1/4 c. oleo just until moistened; set aside.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Then add eggs and flour. Stir in vanilla flavoring. Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° until light brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts and cube bread.
Place into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Cook and drain sausage.
Alternate sausage and cheese, making four layers.
Mix eggs and milk together.
Pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: double chocolate fantasy bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl beat cake mix, oil and egg on medium speed until crumbly.
Add nuts.
Reserving 1 1/2 cups crumb mixture, press remainder firmly in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in frying pan.
Slice potatoes into casserole, alternating with a mixture of soup and milk.
Season with salt and pepper.
Lay pork chops on top of potatoes.
Add small amount of water to frying pan.
Pour over casserole.
Bake 45 minutes, covered, at 375°, then uncovered, for 15 minutes or until pork chops are done.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine dressing, potatoes, celery, onion and bacon.
Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Serve hot.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter with shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk. Add vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: new england clam quiche
directions: Bake shell at 400° for 8 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Reduce oven temperature to 325°.

title: impossible ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400.
Grease pie plate, 10 X 1 1/2.
Sprinkle ham, cheese and onions in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth 15 second in blender on high.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes our clean. 35-40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: dago's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Cover tightly and leave in refrigerator until ready to use.
Pinch off walnut size balls and let rise.
You can use this as you want.
Keep tightly covered in refrigerator.
Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: corn pancakes
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Whisk together the milk, egg and butter.
Stir in corn.
Stir in flour mixture until well moistened.
Do not beat.
Add more milk if too thick.
Bake on hot griddle, using 1/3 cup batter per pancake.
Makes 6 pancakes.

title: italian meat rolls
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into 4 (4-inch long) rolls.
Dip each roll in egg, dredge in corn flake crumbs.
Place on rack.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until done.

title: pudding pie
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk into bowl.
Mix for approximately 1 minute.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate for 1 hour to chill. Spread Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Now it is ready to serve.

title: golden snacking bars*
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan melt butter in oven.
Combine crumbs, cocoa and sugar.
Sprinkle over melted butter. Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Sprinkle with peanut butter chips then raisins.
Top with nuts; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool. Cut into bars.
Makes about 36 bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: scalloped corn and ham
directions: Combine all ingredients except ham.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish.
Place ham in circle around edge.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, or until set.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crock pot chili
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and pepper; drain.
Place in large crock pot.
Add remaining ingredients except cloves and bay leaves; mix well.
Place cloves and bay leaves on top of chili. Cook in crock pot overnight on low.
Before serving, remove cloves and bay leaves.
Serves 6.

title: summer squash or zucchini pancakes
directions: Everyone who hates sweet potatoes, still loves this casserole...... including me!

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and chop potatoes, leave in water until ready to use.

title: kiwi ice
directions: Place the fruit in a blender container or food processor. Cover and process until smooth. Gradually add fruit to the Marshmallow Creme in a large bowl.
Mix with an electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in water and juice.
Pour into 6 or 8 individual cups with tight fitting lids.
Place in the freezer until completely solid.
Pack in an insulated cooler for traveling and serve with spoons.

title: irish raisin soda bread
directions: Melt butter. Add buttermilk and eggs. Add dry ingredients. Mix well with spoon. Add raisins. Grease and flour 2 loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until lite golden or toothpick comes out clean.

title: quick cake
directions: Add all ingredients except eggs.
Beat for 2 minutes; add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes and pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Can use loaf pan or pound cake pan.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil on medium until hot.
Add chicken and onion, stirring continuously until chicken is cooked (about 2 minutes).
Add peas and carrots, rice and pepper.
Stir until heated.
Add garlic salt, soy sauce and egg, stirring quickly until egg is cooked.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in
casserole
covering with chopped eggs. Mix soup and water.
Pour
over
chicken.
Mix
flour, milk and margarine.
Pour over chicken
mixture.
Pour
broth over this. Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at
350° until crust rises to top and is golden brown.
(You can
add English peas, grated carrot and onion to chicken mixture, if you like.)

title: spanish noodle casserole
directions: Boil noodles 5 minutes.
Cook chopped onion and bell pepper in 2 tablespoons bacon grease until tender and brown.
Add meat and cook until it loses red color.
Turn off heat.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add corn and tomato paste.
Mix well.
Add grated cheese and stir in cooked noodles.
Save some cheese to sprinkle on top.
Cook for about 45 minutes in oven at 325°.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine shortening and peanut butter until blended.
Blend in sugars; add egg, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine remaining dry ingredients; shape dough into balls. Roll in sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each cookie immediately with kiss.

title: moist pound cake
directions: Separate eggs, whip the whites and add 6 tablespoons of the sugar.
Place this mixture in refrigerator until rest of cake is mixed.
Cream the butter; add gradually remainder of sugar and beat until light.
Add yolks 2 at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and cream alternately; beat well.
Beat in egg whites and pour batter in greased, floured cake pans and bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 300°.
Makes 2 medium size cakes.

title: pineapple sponge cake
directions: Separate eggs.
Let stand until room temperature.
Use 10-inch ungreased tube pan.

title: bean pot supper
directions: Fry sausage until done and browned.
Remove from skillet. Break in small pieces in a bowl.
Combine sweet pepper, hot peppers and onions.
Place this in the skillet without draining sausage grease.
Fry until onion is clear.
Combine beans and sausage back in pan and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: sammy's favorite cheesecake
directions: Chill milk until very cold.
Dissolve Jell-O in water and set aside.
Cream juice, 1 cup sugar and cream cheese until smooth. Add Jell-O mixture and cool.
Whip chilled milk until stiff.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Prepare crust by mixing graham cracker crumbs, 1/2 cup sugar and melted margarine, then pressing into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour filling into crust and chill.

title: seasoned oysterettes
directions: Put oysterettes in a large bowl and stir in dressing mix. Add oil slowly all over top of crackers (not just in one spot), while stirring.
Mix well.

title: venison pemmican
directions: Cut fat into small chunks and melt in skillet.
Grind jerky fine and pour hot fat over.
Mix until the consistency of sausage. Chop dried fruit finely and add.
Pack pemmican in plastic or other airtight container after shaping into rolls or balls.

title: cowboy stew
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add beans and onion and simmer about 10 minutes until onion is done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° until done. Let pie get deep brown on top or it will be runny!

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Boil broccoli until almost cooked (10 to 12 minutes).
Drain. Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2-quart dish.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and butter until crumbly; sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown (about 20 minutes) at 400°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: italian beef
directions: Put meat in Dutch oven; add rest of ingredients on top, except peppers and 2 cups water.
Cover and cook 2 hours over low flame, turning occasionally.
Take meat out and cool; slice thin.
Remove garlic and bay leaves.
Add the sliced green peppers and 2 cups water.
Simmer for 1/2 hour.
Put meat in and simmer another 1/2 hour.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together oleo and sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add salad oil, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Form into balls and roll in sugar.
Flatten with a glass.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese and cream cheese in saucepan or in a microwave.
Add diced chilies and chili without beans.
Heat until warm, stirring occasionally.
Serve in a fondue pot.

title: cooked pimento cheese
directions: Heat cheese and milk in double boiler until cheese melts.
Mix and add other ingredients.
Cook 20 to 30 minutes.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana split cake(refrigerate)
directions: Mix graham crackers, 1 stick oleo and 1/2 cup powdered sugar. Line bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish; set aside.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Serve with chunky salsa.

title: green beans caesar
directions: Heat green beans in water; bring to a boil and cook for 5 minutes, then cover and cook for another 15 minutes (or until beans start to get tender).
Drain water.
In ungreased casserole dish, put beans, oil, vinegar, onion, garlic, salt and pepper. Mix breadcrumbs, cheese and margarine together and sprinkle on top of beans.
Sprinkle with paprika for color.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: three fruit rice salad(sugar-free)
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Add mint, poppy seed and orange peel.
Mix well.
Stir dressing into rice.
Cover and chill several hours.
To serve, stir in fruits.
Makes 2 servings.

title: red hot cinnamon pickles
directions: Peel, core and cut up cucumbers. Soak cucumbers in 1 cup lime and 1 gallon water for 24 hours. Wash thoroughly. Soak cucumbers in ice water for 3 hours. Pour off water and mix 1 cup vinegar, food coloring and 1 tablespoon alum. Pour over cucumbers and add enough water to cover; simmer 2 hours. Cool. Pour off. Bring 2 cups water and red hots to a boil; cook until candy is melted. Pour syrup over cucumbers and let stand 24 hours. Pour syrup off and bring to boil again. Pack cucumbers in sterilized jars; pour boiling syrup over cucumbers to cover and seal jars.

title: crock salad
directions: Pour tap water over first 5 ingredients to cover.
Add salt to taste, about 5 teaspoons.
Let set 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soup and sour cream.
Spread half the mixture in a 9x13 pan.
Top with raw chicken, swiss cheese slices and remaining soup mixture.
Sprinkle with dressing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. May be frozen.

title: light pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°; spray an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan with Pam or Baker's Joy.
In a mixing bowl or food processor, blend the pumpkin puree, 3/4 cup of the brown sugar, vanilla and oil; mix until well combined.
Drain the raisins and stir in.

title: broccoli topped tuna bake
directions: Prepare macaroni according to directions.
Drain.
Reserve 1/2 cup Cheez Whiz.
In large bowl, combine soup, milk and remaining Cheez Whiz; stir in macaroni, tuna and pepper.
Pour in 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Stir.
Arrange broccoli in spoke fashion on top of macaroni mixture.
Top with reserved Cheez Whiz.
Bake 5 minutes or until hot.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fabulous make-ahead salad
directions: Layer in order using 1/2 cup of cheese per layer.
Pour salad dressing over top.
Garnish with grated cheese and egg slices. Keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: chicken casserole(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Debone chicken, if desired.
Place in baking dish.
Lay one slice of cheese over each breast. Sprinkle croutons over cheese. Mix sherry and soup together and pour over cheese slices.
Melt margarine and pour over all. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice and Sprite in punch bowl.
Float sherbet on top.
Stir and serve.

title: ham roll
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and onion and small amount of pickle juice until it is spreadable.
Spread mixture on sliced ham, dot with sweet pickles, roll up like a jelly roll.
Chill for several hours and slice.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions on box.
Mix sugar, sour cream and coconut; set 1 cup of this mixture aside.
Ice cake layers with coconut mixture.

title: anita's antipasto
directions: Line edge of platter with salami slices.
Cover large platter with lettuce.
Roll each slice of ham and arrange amongst lettuce. Cut Provolone cheese in strips, putting partially under lettuce leaves like rolled ham.
Slice hard-boiled eggs in half, arranging on lettuce.
Then place chunks of tuna.
All other ingredients are just placed on top of each other.
Place shrimp on very top.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Mash peaches and mix all ingredients.
Pour into freezer container.
Yields 1 gallon.

title: salad slaw
directions: Chop up lettuce.
Dice tomatoes and add to lettuce.
Add Miracle Whip.
Mix well and enjoy.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: In small bowl, stir together cocoa and boiling water until smooth; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round pans.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad(must prepare ahead)
directions: Place broccoli and cauliflower in a large bowl.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over broccoli-cauliflower mixture and refrigerate overnight.
Mix in crumbled bacon before serving.

title: chilliquilles
directions: Put in 3 qt. greased casserole in layers: tortillas, chicken, soup, cheese ending with soup. Add the olives and chilies to the soup. Sprinkle the top with one can chile salsa and a little cheese. Bake at 350 degrees for half an hour.

title: butterscotch peanut candy
directions: Melt butterscotch in a double boiler.
Add peanut butter and blend in double boiler until smooth and creamy.
Pour mixture into candy mold.
(Baker's Kitchen on Hull Street sells molds shaped like peanuts.)
Place in freezer until hardened (about 10 minutes).
Turn mold upside-down and tap it on counter.
Candy should fall out, if not, return it to freezer for a few minutes.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Cover bowl and chill in refrigerator.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put soup bone in pot of water.
Add salt, pepper, thyme, parsley and tomatoes.
Cook and simmer for approximately 2 hours. Add other vegetables and cook for another hour, then add 1 large bag of frozen mixed vegetables.
Cook for about 30 minutes. Serve with loaf of fresh baked bread and enjoy.

title: german pot roast
directions: Heat
to
boiling point.
Pour over 4 pounds top round. Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Next day, brown meat.
Add marinade and simmer
for
2 hours.
Add celery, carrots, onions, lemon and potato; cook until tender.	Remove meat and vegetables to platter. Crush
10 gingersnaps.
Add to pan juices to thicken gravy.
Pour over meat and vegetables.

title: pudding cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.
Make pudding mix according to directions, adding softened cream cheese to the pudding.
When the cake is baked, punch it full of holes with a fork and pour the can of pineapple over it.
Spread the pudding and cream cheese mixture over the pineapple.
Add coconut to the Cool Whip and spread over the pudding mixture.
Cool for 24 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli tops in bite size pieces; discard stems.
Chop tomato, mix with broccoli and mushrooms.
Add dressing and mix well.
Let set for a few hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: hungarian potato fritters
directions: Grate potatoes on grater using small holes on grater.
Take off water, if any.
Add egg, salt and milk and mix.
Add flour, enough to hold batter together.
Put enough oil in skillet so it covers potatoes partly.
Use 2 tablespoons of batter (or more if you like them thicker).
Fry slowly on one side until brown and turn over and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Put salt on, if you like.
Serve with sour cream on top.

title: birds nest pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pie plate.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Combine rest of ingredients and mix well.
Pour over rhubarb.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Invert onto serving plate.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix all together.
Cook in microwave about 10 minutes.

title: lemon cream pie
directions: Bake the pie crust first.
Heat the milk.
Add next four ingredients as in making custard.
Pour this (boiling) upon the whites (beaten light and mixed with three tablespoons of sugar). Pour into the crust and brown slightly in a hot oven.

title: diet or reg. cheesecake
directions: For crust, mix together sugar, flour crushed graham crackers and oleo.
Line bottom of 9 x 12 pam.
In a blender, combine yolks, both milks, 1 c. sugar, egg whites. If too much at one time, do half at one time.
Pour on top of crust.
Bake 10 mins. at 375°, then bake at 325° for 40 mins.
Should be light brown.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cut up circus peanuts and dissolve in jello.
Drain pineapple and add the liquid to cold water to make 2 cups; add to first mixture.
Let stand until partially set, then add whipped Dream Whip and crushed pineapple. Refrigerate until set.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together until it's at a boil that can't be stirred down.
Take off stove and add peanut butter.
Pour over corn flakes.
Spoon out on waxed paper or cookie sheet.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Arrange stalks in greased baking dish.
Place chicken on top.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour this mixture over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Then sprinkle bread crumbs over this.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh banana cake
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt, then cream the shortening until soft and smooth.
Gradually add sugar, creaming very well until fluffy. Beat in flavoring, slightly beaten eggs and banana.
Add flour alternately with milk, beating until smooth after each addition. Put into greased pans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cool, then ice.

title: peanut butter temptations
directions: Form dough into 1-inch balls.
Bake in ungreased 1 1/2-inch muffin tins at 375° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned. Press peanut butter cups in the center of warm cookies.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking dish, arrange chicken.
In small bowl, combine all other ingredients.
Brush over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes until chicken is done.

title: gulf grill
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Marinate in the lime juice for 1/2 hour.
In your blender, process the garlic cloves, the jalapenos and 3/4 cup cilantro leaves; add the beer.
When everything is well chopped, stir in the melted butter.
Mash the avocado.
Stir the mashed avocado with sour cream and 1 tablespoon of cilantro.
Mix until the ingredients are smooth.
Thread your shrimp on skewers. Brush with the beer mixture.
Grill.
Turn once.
Brush with more of the beer batter and cook until done.
Dip in avocado sauce hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients, adding pecans last.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan (unbaked).
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Then reduce heat to 350°, about 45 minutes, until knife comes out clean.

title: grandma ferry's molasses cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
You may add cinnamon and ginger. Place soda in hot water.
Add cream of tartar, flour and salt. Roll out.
Bake at 375° to 400°.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Dice the tomatoes and peppers; add the cabbage and onion.
Put mixture into bowl.
Add the salt and just enough water to cover. Soak overnight.
Drain the next morning.
Bring to a boil the 3 cups water, sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, tomatoes, peppers, cabbage and onion.
Boil 3 minutes.
Add to containers and seal.
Makes about 13 pint jars.

title: peach crisp
directions: Slice peaches.
Put in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle some sugar on top.
Sift flour, sugar, salt and baking powder together. Add egg.
Pinch into crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Serve warm with cream.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon.
Mix salmon and bread crumbs.
Combine remaining ingredients except oil.
Stir into salmon mixture.
Form into about twelve 1-inch balls.
Heat oil about 1 inch deep in skillet. Spoon balls into hot oil; brown well on all sides.
Makes 4 servings.

title: summer blush
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Blend on high until smooth. Serve immediately.
Yield: 3 1/2 cups.

title: caramel french toast(good for christmas morn!)
directions: Combine sugar, butter and corn syrup in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat until sauce thickens, stirring constantly. Pour syrup mixture in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place 6 slices of bread on top of syrup mixture.
Top with remaining 6 slices of bread.
Combine eggs, milk, vanilla and salt, stirring until blended.
Pour over bread.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° until light golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: diabetic cookies
directions: Mix the applesauce, margarine, eggs, vanilla and brown sugar. Add oatmeal, cinnamon, allspice, flour, baking soda, salt, raisins and nuts and mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet and bake for 15 minutes at 375°.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Hull and slice 1 cup of berries.
Arrange along sides of a clear straight sided 1 1/2 quart glass bowl or dish.
Place remaining berries in food processor or blender, add sugar, cover and blend to puree.
In mixer bowl, beat pudding that has been made with cream cheese.
Place half of the cake cubes in the bottom of the dish; top with one half of the sliced bananas and pour half of the pureed berries over them.
Top all this with half of the pudding mixture.
Repeat with remaining cake cubes, berries, bananas and pudding.
Cover the top with Cool Whip and refrigerate for 1 hour or overnight.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, cook and stir onion in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, then chicken broth. Stir and cook until smooth and thickened.
Remove from heat; add sour cream.
Set aside.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients in a very large pan until potatoes are done but still firm.
In a second large pan, melt margarine; stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk and cook over low heat until hot.
Stir in the cheese.
When it is melted, pour the milk mixture into the pan of potatoes and water.
Stir.
Makes about 1 gallon.
Great reheated, too.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix
cream
of	wheat,	flour, sugar, baking powder and salt well.
Add milk, oil, egg and food coloring.
Stir gently and don't overbeat it, gals!
Grease your pan and bake at 425° until the top is golden brown.
It's crispy and crunchy.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean the mushrooms and remove stems. Rinse, drain and dry shrimp. Combine all ingredients except Romano cheese. Fill mushroom caps with mix and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover and chill for 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease an 11 x 7-inch pan. Bake mushrooms at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and top with Durkee onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine melted oleo, onion, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Combine broccoli and rice.
Combine two mixtures into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: theresa shea's seventh heaven pineapple pudding
directions: Make pudding with milk according to directions.
Soften gelatin in cold water.
Stir into hot pudding.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Continue beating while adding sugar, a teaspoon at a time. Pour into 2-quart mixing bowl.
Chill 6 to 8 hours.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Combine ingredients.
Add more chicken broth, if needed.
Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cinnamon swirl raisin bread pudding
directions: Tear bread into
2-inch
pieces. Drop into large mixing bowl and pour milk
over.
Toss	gently until bread is coated. Let bread soak about 15
minutes.
In
a small bowl, beat eggs together with sugar until
mixture is light yellow, smooth and thick. Add vanilla.
Pour
mixture	over milk-soaked bread and gently, but thoroughly,
mix
together
until
bread is evenly coated with egg mixture.
Put
into a buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish (uncovered), and
place dish in another pan with 1 to 2
inches
of water.
Place these dishes in preheated 350° oven and bake until set.
A knife inserted into center should come out clean, about 1 hour.

title: broccoli and mushroom salad
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix the sugar, spices, oil and vinegar together and toss over the vegetables.
Marinate overnight for best flavor. Stir before serving.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Combine butter and water in a medium saucepan over low heat. Cook until butter melts.
Combine remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Add butter mixture; beat until smooth.
Yields about 1 1/2 cups.

title: seasoned oyster crackers
directions: Crust: Pat 1 large and 1 small pkg. of crescent rolls out onto a large cookie sheet or crescent roll pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 370°.
Cool.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in medium-size saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until color turns darker.
Remove from heat; add vanilla. Stir, then immediately add peanut butter and Fluff, stirring until mixed.
Pour into small square buttered pan.

title: mushroom and spinach medley
directions: Melt butter in pan; add spinach, sliced mushrooms, and nutmeg; salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook over low heat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Transfer the vegetables to a serving dish and drizzle sour cream over on top.
Serve at once while still hot.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Cook meat and drain; set aside.
In a large bowl, mix cheese, soup, onion and green chilies.
Stir in meat and mix well.
Soften tortillas one at a time in hot oil.
Put layer of meat in a large casserole dish; layer 3 or 4 tortillas, the another layer of meat and so on, ending with meat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. Just before removing from oven sprinkle with grated cheese and let melt.
Makes 8 servings.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix together just before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat 2 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Sift together flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and baking powder.
Whisk together oil, eggs, vanilla, sugar and rind in large bowl.
Stir in flour mixture, zucchini, walnuts and raisins.
Divide into prepared pans.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: love's a cookin'(from lorraine's kitchen wall)
directions: Sift together sweetness with consideration and kindness. Blend in equal amounts of the Spices of Life and mix well with generous amounts of love.
Bake until savory, approximately a lifetime.

title: strawberry jello
directions: Mix all ingredients except sour cream.
Pour 1/2 into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put in freezer for 20 minutes.
Spread with sour cream.
Top with rest of Jell-O.
Refrigerate.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in casserole dish.
Add lemon juice.
Melt butter. Add flour, sugar, oatmeal and spices.
Place crumbly mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: banana nut bread(makes 1 loaf)
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix eggs, margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add mashed bananas.
In another bowl, mix the flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup over popped corn in a large shallow pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 250°, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool on wax paper.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs and beat well. Sift flour once, then measure and add soda, baking powder, salt and spices and sift again.
Add dry ingredients and milk at same time; beat well.
Last, add nuts and prunes.

title: dimples
directions: Put 1/2 of a twist in each well of a mini-muffin pan.
Bake 8 minutes, at 375 degrees.
Make a hole in the center of each "mini-muffin" and add 1 tsp. cream cheese, 1 1/2 tsp. heated chili, 1/2 tsp. onions and 1 tsp. cheese to each.
Return to oven for 3-5 minutes.
Yield:

title: mock margaritas
directions: Mix Crystal Light, honey and egg whites.
Add ice and mix well.
Chill in freezer for 30 minutes. When ready to serve, place 2 cups of mixture in blender.
Add 1 cup of club soda.
Blend and pour.
Garnish with lime slices.

title: hot and sour soup
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg and green onions and bring to boil over high heat.
Stir constantly in one direction. Gradually pour egg into boiling soup.
Remove from heat and garnish with onion greens.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and salt.
Beat thoroughly until light and fluffy.
Stir soda into milk.
Add flour and milk alternately and beat well.
Add mashed bananas, nuts and vanilla.

title: "way to go" snacks(child-approved)
directions: Have children spread cream cheese or peanut butter onto a rectangular cracker.
Gently press half of a red grape, a small circular piece of American cheese and half of a green grape onto the cream cheese.
Makes traffic lights.

title: coffee cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and eggs.
Fold in flour, sour cream, vanilla, baking powder and salt.

title: strawberry mousse
directions: Combine all ingredients in food processor or blender.
Blend until smooth and thick!
Pour into 6 serving cups and freeze until ready to serve (at least 15 to 20 minutes freezer time before serving).

title: martha's company casserole(low-fat version)
directions: Early in the day, cook noodles as package directs; drain. Saute beef until browned (using a little margarine, if necessary). Remove from heat; add tomato sauce.
Combine cheeses, sour cream, scallions and green pepper.
Spread 1/2 of cooked noodles in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture.
Top with remaining noodles.
Pour melted margarine over noodles (optional), then tomato-meat sauce.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Combine margarine, oil, chocolate and water in a saucepan and heat until chocolate is melted.
Cool to lukewarm.
Combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt, milk, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl; add chocolate mixture.
Pour into a greased and floured 12 x 8-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until done. Five minutes before cake is done, prepare frosting.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; cool and stir in pie filling and pineapple.
Chill until jelled.

title: pecan date cookies
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla. Add the eggs, one at a time.
Sift together the flour, salt and soda. Add to the creamed mixture.
Stir in pecans and chopped dates.
Cover with wax paper and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Drop by tablespoons about 2-inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Remove immediately from the baking sheet and cool on wire racks.
Makes 8 dozen.

title: punch for a party
directions: Mix 2 packs of pink lemonade Kool-Aid and sweeten as directed. Add punch.
Just before ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: cocoa party cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Sift together cocoa, flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake in three 9-inch round pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; one 13 x 9 x 2 1/4-inch pan, bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: sopaipillas
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Gradually add water, stirring with a fork.
The dough will be crumbly.

title: filled cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients with mixer and then with hands until batter forms a ball.
Roll out on confectioners sugar and cut into small circles.
Put one on top of other and mesh ends with fork tines.
Fill with preserves.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in 1/4-inch thick slices.
Place in a small baking dish.
Mix butter and oil, then brush over potatoes.
Pour remaining over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes or until potatoes are done and brown at the edge.
Serve with Salisbury Steaks, toss green salad and (no water) pound cake and ice cream as dessert.

title: russian salad
directions: On low heat, cook the first 4 ingredients until dissolved, stirring constantly. Cool, then add the remaining ingredients. Stir well.
Pour into an oblong baking dish.
Cool in the refrigerator until mixture congeals.
Serve by cutting into squares.
This congealed salad is so rich and yummy!

title: pizza for one
directions: Place 2 tortillas, one directly on top of the other.
Spread pizza sauce or spaghetti sauce to approximately 1/2 inch of edge. Place pepperoni or desired meat.
Then sprinkle bell pepper and onions.
Spread cheese on top.
Bake for 10 minutes in 350° oven.

title: sugar-free chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar substitute until light and fluffy (do not use liquid sweetener in this recipe).
Add egg and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape dough into a roll (1 1/2 inches in diameter). Wrap in waxed paper and chill for several hours or overnight. Slice dough into 1 1/2-inch thick rounds.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut beef into bite size chunks; arrange in Pyrex dish.
Cover with vegetables.
Sprinkle with sugar, tapioca and salt.
Pour on tomato juice.
Cover with foil and bake for 5 hours at 250°.

title: simple syrup
directions: Bring to a boil.
Set aside in a container; use as needed. Refrigerate.

title: cream cheese muffins
directions: Melt butter in custard cup.
Add vanilla.
Mix in another bowl sugar, cinnamon and almond extract.
Cut cheese into 10 cubes. Flatten biscuits into 3-inch circles.
Dip a cheese cube into butter and roll in sugar mixture.
Place in center of biscuit. Pull edges together and seal to form a mushroom shape.
Holding sealed edges, dip top of roll into butter then sugar.
Place roll, sealed side down, in muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes. Remove immediately.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat for about 5 minutes but do not boil.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla and shredded zucchini.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, stirring until well blended.
Stir in chopped nuts.
Pour into two greased and lightly floured 9 x 5-inch pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.

title: trifle
directions: Cut frozen pound cake into bite sized pieces.
Place in bottom of glass trifle bowl.
Heat Hershey's fudge sauce according to directions on jar.
In small bowl, mix heated sauce with
Kahlua if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and let chill.
Form into a ball and roll in about 1/2 cup of chopped nuts.
Will freeze!

title: brazilian black bean soup
directions: Rinse the beans after they have soaked.
Cook them in saucepan with water or stock and salt.
Saute onions, garlic, carrot and celery.
Add 3 1/2 cups water or stock and soaked, rinsed, drained beans.
Bring to boil.
Simmer.
When beans are cooked (about 1 1/2 hours), add coriander and cumin, then add white wine, black pepper, hot chili peppers, lemon juice and orange.
Let simmer for another 1/2 hour.
More chili peppers will spice this up.
Serve with quesadillas, tortillas fried on a griddle with grated cheese inside and salsa, a fresh green salad and fruit.
Serves 8.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper.
Drain excess fat.
Salt to taste.
Place in baking dish; add macaroni and soups and mix well. Cover with cheese and bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: sate for pork or chicken(spicy)
directions: Blend together in a medium bowl the peanut butter, red pepper, garlic, honey and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Let stand at least one hour.
Will keep for months in the refrigerator.

title: candy apple pie
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 1/2 cups apple juice, candies, food coloring, vanilla extract, lemon juice and apples.
Bring to a boil, then simmer just until apples are tender, about 10 to 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Combine remaining 1/4 cup juice and cornstarch.
Stir into apple mixture and continue to cook until thickened, about 2 minutes.
Then cook for another 2 to 3 minutes; add butter.
Remove from heat; cool to room temperature.
Spread apple filling over bottom of pie crust.
Chill for several hours or until holds its shape.
Before serving, combine whipped topping and cinnamon.
Top each slice with a dollop of the mixture. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: special rice krispies bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Add peanut butter.
Add vanilla.
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chips together in a double boiler.
Spread on top of bars.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl; mix well.
Chill, tightly covered, until serving time.
Serve with tortilla chips or spicy hot wings.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: pudim de leite condensado(condensed milk pudding)
directions: In blender, mix the condensed milk and milk.
Add eggs and mix well.
Make a sauce with the sugar and water.
Add the water to the sugar in a saucepan until melted and brown.
Put sauce in a tube pan or Bundt cake pan.
Pour in the milk/egg mixture.
Cook in a hot oven at 425° for 40 minutes over a pan of water.
Remove from the pan only when completely cooled.
It's good to put into the refrigerator first.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Wash, oil
and
wrap
potatoes
in
foil.
Bake at 450° until tender.
Remove
foil
and cut out top of potato.
Scoop out inside of potato and put in mixer bowl.
Cream potato with butter, salt
and
pepper, then chives, onions and sour cream. Put back into potato shell.
Bake at 325° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese and bacon, if desired, on top of potato and let cheese melt.
Then serve hot.

title: fried cheese sticks (mozzarella)
directions: IMPORTANT:
Fried cheese sounds difficult;
it's not! Simply remember to chill cheese before breading and before frying to prevent cheese from melting before it turns brown.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Sift flour.
Mix in brown sugar.
Add melted margarine and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 400°.
Let cool.
Cream together cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust.
Top with pie filling. Refrigerate.
Any flavor pie filling may be used.

title: boiled water soup
directions: Pour water in saucepan.
Turn large stove burner on high. Place pan on heat.
When water boils, turn off heat.
Use while hot.

title: new england boiled dinner(mother's version)
directions: Simmer pork chops until done in enough water to fill the pot at least one-third full.
Season with salt and pepper.
When the chops are done, remove them.
Simmer the onions and cabbage in the liquid until tender.
Return the pork chops to the pot until they are heated back.
Adding some margarine at the end adds a little more flavor.

title: basic shrimp creole
directions: Heat bacon grease. Saute finely chopped onions and peppers until tender.
Remove and drain grease back into skillet. Add flour and let brown.

title: arthritis help
directions: Mix and drink 2 ounces daily.
Good for clearing out the arteries too.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 3 tablespoons of juice.
Combine sugar and flour.
Stir in juice.
Add cheese and pineapple and mix well.
Pour mixture into a greased 1-quart casserole dish. Combine melted margarine and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients well with hand mixer.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes 8 mini loaves or 2 large loaves.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and pepper in oil.
Add chicken and mix well.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste and 2 cans of water.
Add remaining ingredients and season.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour.
Serve over spaghetti.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Prepare linguine.
Heat broccoli pieces to boiling.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes until broccoli is tender-crisp.
While broccoli is cooking, in 12-inch skillet, heat oil; cook mushrooms, onion and carrot, stirring frequently.
Add red pepper; cook until tender. In 2 cup measuring cup with fork, mix evaporated milk, bouillon and cornstarch.
Into vegetable mixture in skillet, add evaporated milk mixture.
Heat to boiling.
Add parsley, grated cheese and broccoli.
Pour over linguine and toss to coat well.
Makes 6 servings; about 355 calories, 7 g. fat, 4 mg. cholesterol and 615 mg. sodium.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil on medium heat all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
This is especially good on grilled chicken.
May add 1 chopped onion.

title: savory baked ham salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise, milk, mustard, salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese. Spoon into 1 1/2 quart casserole and bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with reserved cheese and continue baking until cheese is melted.

title: travis house cookies(a butterscotch meringue cookie)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease baking sheet well.
Beat egg white until stiff peaks form; gradually add brown sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat in salt and flour.
Stir in chopped pecans.
Drop batter by teaspoonful 2 inches apart on baking sheet.
Bake approximately 15 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from pan.
May be doubled.
They will melt in your mouth.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Add butter, lemon rind, lemon juice and egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick.
Cool.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into baked pie shell and chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with whipped cream and 2 tablespoons chopped nuts if desired.

title: "puppy chow"
directions: In large bowl, microwave chocolate chips and butter 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate melts.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cereal and stir gently until coated.
Place sugar in large plastic bag and add cereal mixture.
Shake until thoroughly coated. Serve.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease shallow baking dish. Cook spinach in small amount of boiling water until just tender. Drain.
Squeeze to remove liquid.
Chop coarsely.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Melt 1/2 stick oleo in baking dish. Combine all other ingredients. Pour mixture over oleo in pan. Bake at 400° until done.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: Bring margarine, sugar, syrup and salt to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil five minutes without stirring.
Take from burner and add soda and vanilla.
Stir well and pour over popcorn which is in large baking pan or bottom of roaster.
Mix well and bake in 250° oven for one hour.
Stir and mix well every 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Mix sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Stir in flour. Mix in nuts and chocolate chips.
Spread dough in pan.
Bake until light brown, 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars about 2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Roll into balls.
Dip one side in sugar.
Put on a cookie sheet and press down with a fork.
Bake at 350° to 400° about 10 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Beat egg lightly and add mayo, mustard, salt, Tabasco, Worcestershire and lemon juice.
In another bowl, lightly combine crab meat, bread, green pepper and parsley.
Pour sauce over crab meat mixture and lightly toss.
Form into cakes (squeeze extra moisture from cakes) and pan fry to crisp brown in mixture of butter and oil.
Makes 7 to 8 cakes.
Serves 2.

title: german refrigerator pickles
directions: Heat vinegar, sugar, salt, turmeric, celery seed and dry mustard until sugar dissolves, then cool.
Slice cucumbers thin and chop 1 cup onions and pour solutions over cucumbers and pack in gallon glass jar.
Refrigerate overnight.
Enjoy.

title: crab dip
directions: Chop crab meat.
Cover cream cheese with crab meat.
Pour on cocktail sauce and serve with crackers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies (including icing centers), in food processor or blender until mixture resembles dirt.
Set aside.
Cream the cream cheese.
Mix the pudding mixes and milk 1 to 2 minutes until well blended.
Fold pudding mixture into cream cheese with a rubber spatula.
Fold in whipped topping.

title: chocolate crunchies
directions: You will need foil or wax paper.

title: pineapple drop doughnuts
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Stir until smooth.
Heat 3 to 4 inches of oil to 375°.
Drop in 5 or 6 doughnuts at a time.
Cook about 1 minute or until golden on one side.
Turn and cook on other side, about 1 minute.
Drain well on paper towel.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Yields 3 dozen.

title: bread pot(good for parties)
directions: Combine 1 cup cooked ham, cream cheese and sour cream.
Stir in 1 cup diced ham, green onions, green chiles and Worcestershire sauce.
Put all in bread shell.
Put top on bread.
Double wrap securely in foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chicken-cheese lasagne
directions: Heat margarine in 2-quart saucepan over low heat until melted; add garlic.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and broth.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese, 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese, the onion, basil, oregano and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until Mozzarella cheese is melted.

title: fantastic banana cake
directions: Bake cake in 2 layers according to package directions.
Cool completely.
Whip cream; fold in vanilla and sugar.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of maple syrup on both sides of layers.
Cover lightly with whipped cream.
Slice bananas on cake.
Cover with whipped cream.
Repeat with second layer.
Chill for several hours.
Will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; stir in flour and cocoa.
Add sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Serve over hot biscuits.

title: shrimp with coconut milk(ginataang hipon)
directions: Saute ginger and shrimp.
Add coconut milk and let it simmer for about 5 minutes.
Lastly, add pepper and green beans.
Cover and let it boil until vegetable is cooked.
Do not overcook vegetables.

title: vegi pie
directions: You can use any vegetables.

title: waldorf red cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until very fluffy.
Make paste of cocoa and red color and add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour and salt together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Mix soda and vinegar and add with the vanilla.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round layer pans.
Bake approximately 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: pineapple chicken
directions: Place chicken in a greased 8x9 inch pan.
Mix remaining ingredients except almonds.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil, sprinkle almonds on top and continue to bake uncovered another 10 to 15 minutes.
Can be doubled, increase time by 15 minutes.

title: rhubarb cookies
directions: Mix well the sugar, eggs, shortening and rhubarb; add the rest of the ingredients.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Bake until done at 375°.

title: punch
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add desired amount of ginger ale just before serving.
Makes about 4 gallons.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat slowly together with onions and celery.
Add the can of tomato sauce or tomato soup.
Let simmer for 10 minutes. Lastly, add Worcestershire sauce, mustard, vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Cook, simmering, for 1/2 hour.

title: veal schnitzel
directions: Place cutlets between sheets of wax paper; flatten to 1/8-inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Combine eggs, salt and pepper; beat well.
Dredge cutlets in flour; dip in egg mixture and coat with bread crumbs.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat; add cutlets and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Turn cutlets and top with cheese.
Cover and cook an additional 3 to 4 minutes. Sprinkle with parsley flakes, if desired.
Garnish with lemon twists and fresh parsley.

title: cheese-nut ball
directions: Mix in bowl or food processor.
Shape into a large ball or individual balls.
May be rolled in chopped walnuts.
Chill and serve with good, unsalted crackers.

title: sirloin tips
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13 pan the uncooked meat on bottom.
Mix together soup and mushrooms and pour over meat.
Sprinkle dry soup mix on top.
Pour soda over all.
Cover and bake at 300° for 3 hours.

title: rigatoni with artichoke sauce
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Meanwhile, slice artichoke hearts thinly.
In large saucepan, heat oil and saute garlic for 2 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts, tomatoes, parsley and pepper flakes.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Drain rigatoni and place in serving dish.
Top pasta with artichoke sauce and sprinkle with cheese and black pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: southern liver and onions
directions: Cut liver into squares.
Salt and pepper liver, then flour. Let vegetable oil get hot before putting liver into frying pan. Brown liver on both sides.
Slice onion; put on top of liver, then put a lid on top of pan.
Let simmer until onion is done.
After onion is done, add 1 1/2 cups water.
Let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: picadillo
directions: In a 4 or 5-quart flameproof casserole, cook meat in oil over medium-high heat, stirring to break up lumps, until browned, 5 to 7 minutes.
(If using beef, drain off excess fat.)
Add garlic, onion and green pepper.
Cook, stirring often, until onion is tender, about 3 minutes.
Stir in all remaining ingredients except almonds. Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot, garnished with almonds.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a mixing bowl.
Stir until well mixed.
Spoon into graham cracker pie crusts.
Chill overnight.

title: spanish rice
directions: Saute onion and peppers.
Brown meat in oil.
Add sauce, water and seasonings.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in cheese and rice. Cover.
Cook on stove on low heat for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot
water and let dissolve.
Add strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Pour
half of the mixture into 12 x 8-inch or 13
x
9-inch
Pyrex
dish.
Chill
until firm. Spread sour cream
over
firm
Jell-O.	Gently	pour remaining mixture over sour cream.
Chill until ready to serve, preferably overnight.

title: beef tips in wine sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients. Pour in oven-proof baking dish and bake at 300° to 325° for 3 1/2 hours. Add pepper to taste and stir.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangle pan at 350°.
Cool 1 hour.
Mix jello as directed.
Chill 20 minutes (you want jello runny).
With round tip wooden spoon, poke holes in cake.
Pour jello over cake.
Use all of the jello.
Spread Cool Whip over entire cake.
Chill for hour.
Cut and serve.

title: baked bean and sausage casserole
directions: Cook lima beans 10 min. Drain, mix with other beans. Place sausage in a skillet; add small amount of water. cover and simmer 5 min. Drain; pan fry until brown. Don't prick. Cut each sausage into 2 or 3 pieces. Heat oven to 400°. Mix sausage, ham and beans. Combine seasonings, tomato sauce, catsup, brown sugar and onion; add to beans. Pour into 3 qt. baking dish. Bake uncovered 1 hour. 10-12 servings.

title: spaghetti naturele
directions: Cook spaghetti as instructed on package.
Just before draining pasta, add vegetables; drain immediately.
In medium pan, heat sauce.
Place spaghetti and vegetables on large platter.
Pour on sauce and add cheese; toss well.
Serve 6.

title: pepsi-cola salad
directions: Drain juice from cherries and pineapple.
Bring to a boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Set aside.

title: crown jewel dessert
directions: Prepare 3 flavors separately using 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water for each.
Pour each into 8-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
Mix pineapple juice and sugar.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Dissolve lemon Jell-O in hot juice, then add 1/2 cup cold water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Prepare whipped topping mix and blend with lemon Jell-O.
Cut the 3 flavors of Jell-O into 1/2-inch cubes and fold into cream.
Pour into pan. Chill 5 hours.

title: lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix according to box. Pour into Bundt pan and cool.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Spray pie pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix pineapple, sugar, flour and juice well.
Spread in pie plate.
Top with cheese.
Mix crackers and butter, then spread on top.
Bake for 25 minutes, or until bubbly on bottom and golden brown on top.
Delicious!!

title: light peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, syrup and water in heavy saucepan. Boil to hard ball stage, 252°.
Stir in peanuts and continue to cook to 300°. Remove from heat. Add salt and soda. Stir vigorously to keep mixture from boiling over when adding soda.
Stir only until blended.
Pour quickly onto a lightly buttered cookie sheet. Crack into pieces when cool.

title: layered salad
directions: Begin with lettuce in bottom of large bowl.
Continue with remaining vegetables in order listed.
Mix dressing, sour cream and mayo.
Spread over top.
Sprinkle bacon bits and cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours.
You can use any vegetables, any amount.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: Break noodles in half and cook. Butter baking dish. Drain noodles and mix all together with ingredients. Top with cheese and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients to soft ball stage (230°), then add butter and peanuts.
Cook to hard crack stage, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and soda.
Pour on greased surface.
As it cools, pull from edges to desired thickness and cut off.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute celery, onion and garlic in salad oil.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce and all seasonings.
Simmer covered for 1/2 hours. Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes (simmer). Serve over rice.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: spicy ginger-garlic chicken
directions: In small bowl, combine garlic, ginger root, salt, red pepper, black pepper, cinnamon and cardamom.
Stir in catsup, vinegar and water.
Brush both sides of each chicken breast with garlic mixture.
Place chicken in a shallow baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for 45 to 55 minutes or until no longer pink. Makes 8 servings.

title: cream of spinach soup
directions: Steam until tender the carrot, onion, potato and garlic.
Puree in own water.
Steam spinach in 1 cup of water and then puree. Make a roux by whisking flour and butter.
Keep stirring briskly and add 2 cups milk in mixture slowly.
Cook over low heat, stirring until thickened.
Add spinach puree to the roux, along with salt and pepper.
Now add first mixture (carrots, etc.) to second.
Stir until thick over low heat.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: cheese roll
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Add all ingredients to softened cream cheese and mix together.
Form desired shape (roll or ball).
Roll in chopped nuts when chilled firmly enough to hold shape.
Continue to chill until serving time.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: old fashioned fruit cake
directions: Measure all ingredients except fruit and nuts into a large mixing bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in fruit and nuts.
Spread mixture evenly into pans.
Bake in muffin cups at 275° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: strawberry sauce
directions: In pan, mix sugar, water and lemon juice.
Stir over medium heat until sugar dissolves and mixture just comes to a boil.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Mix in strawberries, heating through, but do not cook. Makes about 2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together soups and milk.
Layer chicken in large dish and pour soup mixture over chicken.
Add stuffing on top.
Pour 3 cups chicken broth over ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes in 350° oven.
If using metal pan, bake for 1 hour.
Good for freezing.

title: tuna salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients and add sour cream and mayonnaise. Refrigerate and just before serving, toss with 6 ounces of Chinese noodles.

title: ko-ko nut tort
directions: Mix flour, powdered sugar, 1/2 cup chopped nuts and oleo as a pie crust.
Pat in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat the cream cheese and powdered sugar until light.
Fold in 8 ounces of Cool Whip and pour over crust.
Mix coconut pudding with milk.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Spread 4 1/2 ounce carton of Cool Whip over all.
Sprinkle with coconut and a few nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and 1/3 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and Cool Whip.
Put into pie crust and top with your favorite pie filling.
Refrigerate until ready to use. You can also use chocolate Cool Whip and a chocolate pie crust.

title: cuke-yogurt salad
directions: Combine cucumbers and radishes.
Stir together yogurt, honey, lemon juice and salt.
Combine veggies with dressing.
Sprinkle with mint.
Serves 4 with 76 calories per serving.

title: hamburg and rice soup
directions: Put hamburg and rice in water on stove.
Cook until rice is done, then put corn and tomatoes in.
Heat until hot, then serve.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, beaten egg yolks, vanilla, milk and margarine.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie crust; cover with beaten egg whites.
Brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and 1/4 cup catsup.
Place in loaf pan. Spread remaining catsup on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes.

title: deer hash
directions: Cook rice and boil potatoes.
Set aside.
Brown the meat in a skillet.
Add potatoes, rice, bell pepper, onion, stewed tomatoes and plenty of Worcestershire sauce.
Let all fully cook.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and pour over other ingredients.
Chill.

title: broccoli-ramen slaw
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and let stand overnight. Mix beef Ramen noodle seasoning with vegetable oil, vinegar and sugar. One-half hour before serving, crumble up noodles. Add to slaw mixture and stir. Stir the dressing mixture well and add to slaw.

title: fruit punch
directions: Chill and combine apple juice, pineapple juice, Seven-Up and cranberry juice.
Add ice ring made of cranberry juice and fruit cocktail.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch or 10 x 1/3-inch.
Beat
all
ingredients
until
smooth.
Beat 1 minute in blender on high or 2 minutes hand beaten.
Pour into plate. Bake until
knife
inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 55 minutes.
High
altitude over to 375°.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.

title: potato with kale
