directions: Scrub and steam until tender the potatoes.
In a large bowl, mash potatoes with oil and salt.
Steam onion just until soft. Wash kale, allowing water to cling to leaves.
Place kale in pan with onion and continue steaming, covered, until the kale is wilted.
Chop fine and mix with potatoes.
Place the mixture in an oven dish and bake at 350° to warm through and blend flavors.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, sugars and spices. Add pumpkin, eggs, oil and water to dry ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured bread pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 large loaves.

title: crunch tote cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased and floured 13 x 9 pan.
Spoon half of pineapple over batter.
Add remaining batter and top with remaining pineapple. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Combine coconut, brown sugar, pecans and margarine.
Spread over baked cake.
Broil until topping is lightly browned and bubbly.

title: friendship tea
directions: Place ingredients in a large airtight jar.
Shake until evenly distributed.
Store on shelf.

title: clam fritters
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add eggs, clam juice and milk.
Stir well to make a batter.
Stir in chopped clams and drop by spoonfuls onto a hot greased griddle.
Cook about 5 minutes each side or until golden.

title: four layer chocolate dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, pecans and butter.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: chicken chalupas
directions: Combine
soup,	onions, sour cream, chilies, olives and all but 2 cups of the grated cheese.
Set aside 2 1/2 cups of this mixture.
Combine
chicken	with
remaining
mix.
Fill tortillas with chicken mixture, roll and place seam side down in
large casserole
dish.
Spread remaining mix over top and sprinkle with rest of cheese.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: frosting over hot cake
directions: Put holes in cake with fork, then pour mixture over hot cake or yellow cake.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs and Crisco oil.
Sift in all dry ingredients. Add buttermilk, chopped nuts and prunes.
Bake 1 hour and 25 minutes at 335° to 350°.

title: sticky buns
directions: Heavily butter 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle pecans over bottom of pan. Tear one loaf of thawed bread into small pieces and place over bottom of pan on pecans.
Combine pudding, brown sugar, butter, milk and cinnamon in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and pour over bread pieces.
Bread up second loaf of thawed bread into pieces and arrange on sauce over first layer.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Flip pan to serve with the pecans on top.
Yields 12 servings.

title: low-fat low sodium rice casserole
directions: Stir rice, soup, water and mushrooms together in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Makes 8 servings.

title: deluxe chocolate marshmallow bars
directions: In mixing bowl, cream the butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and beat again.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add nuts and spread in jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over and return to oven for 3 to 4 minutes or until melted.
Using a knife dipped in water, spread marshmallows evenly over crust.
Cool.

title: oreo ice cream dessert
directions: Mix the crushed Oreos and melted oleo.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Put the softened ice cream on the layer of cookies.
Freeze.
Combine and cook the powdered sugar, 1/2 stick oleo, chocolate chips and evaporated milk for 5 minutes, until smooth.
Add nuts on top of the ice cream, if desired, then the fudge sauce, then the whipped cream.
Add more nuts and 2 cups crushed Oreos on top.
Freeze.

title: pot roast
directions: You will need a Brown-in-Bag.

title: perked wassail
directions: Combine sugar and juices in automatic percolator.
Place the spices in the basket.
Allow to go through cycle.
Strain.
Serve hot from pot.

title: punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: scalloped asparagus
directions: Drain asparagus and mushrooms and save the liquid.
Make white sauce from butter, flour, salt and liquid.
Cook until thick.
Place asparagus, mushrooms and sliced eggs in baking dish. Cover with white sauce.
Melt butter and toss with crushed Kellogg's K (not too fine).
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Lightly grease 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan; set aside.
In mixing bowl, stir together oats, flour, soda, cinnamon, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
In large bowl, cream margarine and 3/4 cup sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add oat mixture and applesauce alternately to creamed mixture, beating until smooth after each addition.
Pour batter into pan and sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and cinnamon.
Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes or until pick comes clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: cuchinta
directions: Mix 4 ingredients.
Stir in and add lye.
Pour into greased muffin tins.
Steam 12 to 15 minutes.

title: peppy potato salad
directions: Soak mustard and celery seeds in vinegar several hours or overnight.
Combined seed mixture with salt and green onions.
Add potatoes and mix lightly.
Add mayonnaise and eggs.
Toss to mix. Chill thoroughly.

title: dirt cake(no bake)
directions: You will need 1 flowerpot and 1 bunch of flowers (sterilized).

title: cream of cucumber soup
directions: Cook cucumbers in butter over low heat for 10 minutes. Gradually add chicken stock, stirring constantly.
Add scalded milk and thinly sliced onion; simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Pour into blender in small amounts; blend well. Add cream and seasonings.
Chill.
Garnish with chives.

title: chocolate carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan. In large bowl, with mixer at low speed, beat first 10 ingredients just until blended, scraping bowl with spatula.
Increase to high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in carrots and coconut.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake cake as directed on package in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Remove from oven and while hot punch holes in cake using a drinking straw.
Mix condensed milk and cream of coconut and pour over cake.
Cool.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate.

title: pennsylvania dutch cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage in salted boiling water for 7 minutes.
Fry bacon and remove from pan.
Add sugar and flour to bacon fat; blend. Add water, vinegar and seasoning (1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper).
Cook until thick.
Add onion, bacon and cabbage.
Heat through and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and cornstarch together.
Add to egg yolks, then add milk.
Cook on top of stove until it thickens.
Add 2 teaspoons butter and vanilla.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: virgie's chicken salad
directions: In large pot add chicken, salt, pepper, quarter cut onion, celery stalks, and garlic.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer until chicken is done.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream first 3
ingredients
well; add eggs.
Beat until creamy, then add
remaining
ingredients. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Great with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: christmas decorations(confectioners glue recipe)
directions: Blend in small mixer bowl.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Yield:
3/4 cup.

title: cut glass cake
directions: Dissolve packages of Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups hot water (each package).
Put in separate pans.
(I use cake pans.)
Let stand until firm.
Cut top to bottom, side to side, about 1-inch apart. Scoop into Cool Whip.
Dissolve the Knox gelatine in pineapple juice over medium heat; let cool.
Fold ingredients into Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust.
Let set 24 hours.

title: baked chicken supreme
directions: Combine lemon juice, celery salt, garlic, sour cream, Worcestershire, salt, paprika and pepper.
Marinate chicken in mixture overnight in refrigerator, making sure to coat each piece well.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Remove chicken from sour cream mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange chicken in a single layer, in a shallow pan.
Spoon butter over chicken and bake 45 minutes.
Baste again with melted butter, and return chicken to oven for an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: copper pennies(carrots)
directions: Salt and pepper to taste; beat until blended.
Bring to a boil and pour over vegetables.
Good!

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: Place rhubarb in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle flour and sugar over mixture.

title: almond crescents
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Beat margarine and almond extract until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add combined flour and salt. Mix well.
Stir in oats and almonds.
Shape to form crescents. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 to 18 minutes or until light golden brown.
Sift powdered sugar over warm crescents.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken breasts supreme
directions: Remove skin and season with salt, pepper, paprika.
Melt butter, brown chicken over medium heat.
Place in single layer in 10-inch casserole.
Combine soup, milk, cheese, onion and Worcestershire sauce in small saucepan, cut mushrooms in small pieces and add.
Cook over low heat until heated and cheese is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Blend.
Pour over chicken breasts.
Cover tightly.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Uncover and baste with sauce.
Bake 30 minutes longer or until tender, uncovered, basting occasionally.
Serve with mashed potatoes or fluffy rice using the mushroom sauce as gravy.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: crust mustard chicken
directions: Spray Pam into baking dish.
Rub olive oil over chicken.
Mix together mustard, wine and tarragon.
Spread over chicken. Sprinkle bread crumbs over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Form into a loaf and place in loaf pan.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Baste with extra pineapple juice.

title: summer pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the noodles, oranges, apple, celery and chicken.
In small bowl, mix the mayonnaise, cream, lemon juice and sugar to make the dressing.
Combine dressing with other ingredients.
Toss lightly so all pieces are coated; refrigerate 1 hour.
Toast almonds in a small pan in a 300° oven for 10 minutes, or until they just begin to turn brown.
Set aside.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves; top with the toasted almonds.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned egg custard pie
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks with sugar.
Beat until it is lemon colored.
Stir in scalded milk slowly.
Add salt, vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.
Reduce to 350° and bake until firm.

title: applesauce
directions: Cut peeled apples into quarters.
Heat apples and water to boiling over medium heat; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally to break up apples, until tender, 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; boil and stir 1 minute.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: paprikaois chicken
directions: Brown onion and bell peppers. Add salt, garlic powder and black pepper to onion.
Add paprika.
Add chicken.
Fry a few minutes. Add tomatoes and a small amount of water.
Cook on high for a few minutes, then turn on low until done.

title: easy banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mash bananas with fork.
Pour into greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Add salt, pepper and butter.
Add cracker crumbs, half of the cheese, milk and eggs. Stir until blended.
Pour in casserole dish and cover with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken breasts wellington
directions: About 2 1/2 to 3 hours before serving, remove skin from chicken.
Sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon seasoned salt and dash of seasoned pepper.
Refrigerate.
Cook rice as label directs for drier rice, but add orange peel.
Cool.
Beat 2 egg whites until soft peaks form.
Fold into rice mixture.
Unwrap 1 can dinner rolls.
On floured surface, lightly knead half of dough into a ball; roll into 10-inch circle.
Repeat process, making 6 circles. Preheat oven to 375°.
Remove chicken breasts from refrigerator. Place each, flesh side down, in center of each dough circle. Spoon about 1/2 cup prepared rice mixture onto each breast half and fold.
Bring dough up over stuffed breast; moisten edges with water and press to seal edges together.
Place seam side down on large cookie sheet.
Slightly beat egg yolks with 1 tablespoon water; brush over dough.
Bake, uncovered, 45 to 50 minutes or until a cake tester can be inserted easily in breast.
If dough browns too quickly, cover loosely with foil.

title: mini meat loaves
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt, pepper, sage and thyme.
Shape firmly into 6 mini meat loaves or meatballs.
In skillet, browm loaves in small amount of oil.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining soup.
Cover and cook over low heat about 20 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with white rice, mashed or parsleyed potatoes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix all together.
Add Miracle Whip, mustard and some olive juice to make salad hold together.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: chili rice casserole
directions: Stir chilies and sour cream together.
Butter casserole dish. Starting with cooked rice, layer rice, sour cream mixture and slices of Jack cheese until casserole dish is full, ending with rice.
(I usually have 3 rice layers total.)
Salt and pepper to taste and top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake until heated through and cheese is melted at 350°, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Form balls.
Place in pan. Bring next 4 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over ham balls. Bake 1 more hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening until mixture is like small peas.
Add buttermilk (more for moister biscuits; less for drier biscuits).
Mix until mixture comes away from sides of bowl. (Should require very little mixing.)
Knead a little and shape into biscuits.
Bake at 450° for approximately 12 to 20 minutes. Remove from oven and butter top of biscuits.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Have oleo and cheese at room temperature; mix well.
Add flour, other dry ingredients and Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls and flatten on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown on bottom.
Do not overbake.

title: chicken casserole iii
directions: Cook noodles. Cook chicken with celery until done. Combine milk, soup, cheese, salt and pepper. Line casserole with noodles. Stir together cooked chicken with vegetables and soup mixture; pour over noodles. Top with almonds and bread crumbs. Bake until heated through.

title: sunday pot roast
directions: Place roast on large sheet of aluminum foil in baking pan or in a roasting pan with a lid.
Sprinkle soup mix over roast. Spread canned soup over all.
Seal foil securely or if using roasting pan, place lid on pan.
Bake at 300°
for 4 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli and chicken in a utility dish.
Cover with cheese slices.
Mix together evaporated milk and soup.
Pour over broccoli, chicken and cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with onion rings and bake 15 minutes more.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and milk, stirring well.
Spoon sauce evenly over chicken and sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle butter over crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: tuna and spinach quiche
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat next 2 ingredients.
Mix milk and tuna mixture.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350 for 50 minutes or until dry.

title: cup of dirt
directions: Prepare pudding according to package instructions.
Crush Oreo cookies and put into the bottom of cups.
Add chocolate pudding in alternating layers with cookies.
Finish with Oreo cookies.
Add Gummy worm to the top.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients good.
Put in a tube pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: brown and serve rolls
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Work in shortening with hands.
Mix yeast and warm water. Add buttermilk.
Add liquid to dry ingredients. Work with hands into soft ball. Grease top and cover.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out on a floured board and cut about 1/4-inch thick.
Roll in butter (melted).
Fold over.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 250° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Wrap and freeze. Thaw and bake at 450°.

title: swedish cole slaw
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; set aside.
Bring last 3 ingredients to a boil and pour over cabbage mixture while hot. Let this all get cold, then stir well.
Cover and put in refrigerator.
Will keep for days.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: no bake stuffed peppers
directions: Cut up green peppers and parboil 10 minutes.
Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Add green peppers.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Measure cereal into a large bowl and set aside.
In a saucepan, over low heat, melt the chocolate chips, peanut butter, and butter until it can be stirred smoothly.
Stir in vanilla. Pour chocolate mixture over cereal and stir gently until evenly coated.
Pour into a large plastic (Zip-lock) bag.
Add powdered sugar to the bag and seal.
Shake bag until chocolate covered Chex are covered with powdered sugar.
Spread on waxed paper to cool. Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken rosemary
directions: Pound chicken in 1/2 inch thickness.
In medium skillet, over medium heat, brown chicken on both sides in margarine and oil. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Stir in onion, garlic, rosemary and cinnamon.
Cook and stir until onion is soft.
Blend in juice and marmalade.
Spoon over chicken.
Cover; bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in carrots; cover.
Simmer 5 minutes or until carrots are tender-crisp and chicken is tender.

title: crock-pot supper
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Put in crock-pot.
Pour soups over steak.
Do not dilute soups.
Stir slightly to mix.
Cook until meat is cooked through and tender, usually 5 to 6 hours (or overnight).

title: spinach casserole
directions: Brown meat with chopped onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Add spinach and mushrooms to skillet and cook for 20 minutes.
Mix soup, sour cream, garlic salt and 6 ounces Mozzarella cheese.
Add mixture to meat and spinach and put in a baking dish.
Sprinkle additional cheese on top.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut up 1 package of beef fine and mix all the ingredients. Cover with package of beef slices.
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: stuffed mushrooms with bacon and olives
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Coarsely chop stems and set aside.
Cook bacon in heavy large skillet over medium heat until crisp.
Using tongs, transfer bacon to paper towels and drain. Pour off all but 1 tablespoon drippings from skillet. Add chopped mushroom stems, garlic and rosemary.
Saute over medium heat until tender, about 10 minutes.
Crumble bacon and add to skillet. Add olives and stir to combine.
Mix cream cheese in medium bowl until smooth. Add mushroom mixture and stir to blend. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Lightly brush rounded side of mushroom caps with oil.
Place rounded side down on large baking sheet. Spoon filling into caps, mounding in center.
(Can be prepared 1 day ahead.
Cover stuffed mushrooms with plastic and chill.)
Preheat oven to 375°. Bake stuffed mushrooms until heated through, about 20 minutes.
Transfer mushrooms to platter and serve.
Makes 18 appetizers.

title: hearty beef 'n vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Arrange frozen potatoes in bottom and up sides of 8 x 12-inch baking dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
In medium skillet, brown ground beef, leaving in large chunks.
Drain well.
Layer beef, broccoli and 1/2 can French fried onions and the tomato in potato shell (I do not layer, I mix all together and then put on potato shell).
In small bowl combine soup, milk, 1/2 cup cheese and seasonings; pour evenly over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes or until heated through.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, 1 to 3 minutes or until onions are golden brown.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: diabetic fruit salad
directions: Drain all fruit except pineapple.
Mix fruit; sprinkle pudding (dry) over fruit.
Stir lightly.
Refrigerate well.
Keep several days.
One serving equals 1 fruit or 1 fat.

title: pineapple cake with optional icing
directions: Mix first seven ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
With an electric mixer, mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on cool cake.

title: smokehouse spaghetti
directions: Fry bacon, beef and onions; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic salt, mushrooms and juice.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti; drain.
Stir spaghetti into sauce.
Place 1/2 of spaghetti mixture in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with half of the cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground beef or
turkey until brown, then drain and set aside.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll rounded teaspoonfuls of dough into balls.
Makes about 100 balls.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.
Serve warm.
Excellent for breakfast or appetizers.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup milk.
Whip pudding and 1 1/4 cup milk until smooth.
Combine and pour into pie shell; top with whipped cream.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Remove dark skin and bones from salmon.
Flake with fork.
Add cracker crumbs, margarine, tomato juice, onions, paprika and salt to salmon.
Mix well.
Separate egg yolks to salmon mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into well-greased 1-quart casserole dish and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jack's salmon croquettes
directions: Drain salmon; place in mixing bowl. Flake fish and remove any skin and bones.
Using coarse side of grater, grate onion and potato into bowl. Add flour, egg and pepper.
Blend well, then shape into small oval croquettes.
Roll each croquette in cracker meat (flour may be substituted).
Place on a platter and chill in the refrigerator until well chilled.
Place oil in a deep heavy frying pan; fill to about 3-inches from top brim.
Heat oil to about 375° (test oil with a cube of bread that will brown in 30 seconds).
Add croquettes, a few at a time, and fry until golden brown (2 to 3 minutes). Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: shrimp-artichoke casserole
directions: Arrange artichoke hearts in greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish. Slice mushrooms; saute sliced mushrooms in 2 tablespoons margarine for 6 minutes.
Spread shrimp over artichokes.
Add mushrooms to baking dish.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour and salt.
Add milk all at once.
Cook quickly, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat.
Mix Worcestershire sauce with sherry and white sauce; pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and paprika.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
Garnish with parsley.
Serves 4.

title: lemon bars
directions: Combine butter, flour and powdered sugar. Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Set aside.

title: funky chicken
directions: Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Pour dressing over mixture and top with preserves.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: swedish baked potatoes
directions: Use peeled or unpeeled potatoes.
Slice at 1/4 inch intervals about 3/4 of the way through so the potato remains whole and fans out.
Place in buttered dish.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons butter over potatoes.
Combine salt and celery salt; sprinkle over potatoes. Bake uncovered in hot oven (425°) for 3 minutes.
Combine crumbs and onions; sprinkle over potatoes.
Drizzle with remaining butter and bake 20 minutes longer and sprinkle on the cheese.
Baste with butter in the dish and bake 10 minutes longer or until tender.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cut small chunks of beef.
Dredge beef in flour, salt and pepper; brown beef in oil.
Drain.
Add 3 cups water, the bouillon cubes, tomato paste and mustard.
Simmer until meat is tender (about 1 hour).
Add sliced mushrooms; simmer until mushrooms are tender.
Right before serving, add the sour cream.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Debone chicken. Cook spaghetti in broth. Add Velveeta cheese and rest of ingredients and bake until it bubbles. Add grated cheese on top. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato gooey bars
directions: Melt margarine.
Add cake mix and egg.
Blend and press in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Boil 2 minutes.
Butter soda crackers and add them broken up to sugar water.
Combine spices and juice.
Bake until done at 350°.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, cream shortening with sugars until creamy.
Mix in eggs and vanilla.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend cheeses well.
Add onions, pepper, lemon juice and nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into rolls.
Chill 30 minutes.
Roll in chili powder.
Chill until firm.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: baked chicken parmesan
directions: In a paper bag, place seasonings, cheese, parsley and crumbs; coat chicken by shaking a few pieces at a time in the bag.
Oil a shallow roasting pan; pour in the water and arrange chicken pieces. Sprinkle chicken with oil and melted margarine and bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Pour wine over chicken.
Lower oven heat to 325°; cover pan and bake 15 minutes longer.
Remove foil; raise oven heat to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer.
Yield:
4 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburg; drain fat.
Mix in taco seasoning.
Set aside. Chop lettuce, tomatoes and cheese (keep separate).

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli.
Partially drain and add margarine, soup and cheese.
Cook until melted.
Add cooked rice into mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: green rice
directions: Cook rice and broccoli.
Combine all ingredients in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Simmer over low heat until hot, stirring often.	Pour into mugs and serve.

title: christmas potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices to measure 8 cups. Combine potato slices, onions and 1/2 teaspoon salt in a large Dutch oven.
Add water to cover.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Drain and set aside.
Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add flour; stir until smooth. Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in 3/4 teaspoon salt and the next 3 ingredients. Spoon potato mixture into a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over potato mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix together all the ingredients.
Refrigerate about one hour until easy to handle.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
These are good hot or cold.
Add a few tablespoons of mustard to 1/2 cup of mayonnaise or plain yogurt for a great dip.

title: mandlebrot(israel cookie)
directions: Cream margarine, then add sugar and mix well.
Add eggs to the cream mixture and mix well.
Add the liquid and almond extract. Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to cream mixture.
Stir or use hands to blend well and form a cookie dough.
Divide into 3 balls.
Roll each into a log.
Place onto lightly floured cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 375° or until top cracks and is slightly brown.
Take out of oven.
Slice each log diagonally and return to oven to toast 7 to 10 minutes more.
Remove from oven and sift with powdered sugar.
These make a good coffee dunker.
One half cup of chopped nuts are optional.

title: amish style chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles and drain.
In a large skillet, melt butter and cook mushrooms until tender.
Blend in flour.
Gradually add broth, milk, pimento, salt and pepper, stirring constantly until sauce is thickened.
In greased 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine noodles, chicken and sauce; top with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: golden squash bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut the squash in 1 inch cubes and place in a large bowl.
Toss with onions, garlic, salt and pepper, and olive oil.
Place in baking dish and bake until tender.
Stir once or twice.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.
Stir in basil and serve. Serves 4-6.

title: kentucky baked chicken
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Dredge moist chicken pieces in flour mixture.
Place skin side up in greased pan.
Be careful not to let the pieces touch!
Pour melted butter over all.
For extra crispy, flour again, then pour more butter over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Drain salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons liquid; flake into small pieces.
In medium sized bowl, combine salmon and all ingredients. Place in prepared loaf pan or shape into loaf on greased baking sheet.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm.
(Salmon patties).
Prepare salmon mixture as stated.
Shape into eight 1 inch thick patties. In large skillet over medium heat, heat 2 tablespoons butter or oil.
Pan-fry patties on both sides until golden brown.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix together.
Stir in 1/2 cup of mayonnaise or Miracle Whip. Chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: granola
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Mix all dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add oil and water; mix thoroughly.
Mixture will be crumbly.
More water can be added for bigger pieces.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours, stirring every 30 minutes.
To keep edges from getting too brown, store in airtight container.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter or oleo, oil, sugar and powdered sugar together. Add beaten eggs.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add dry mixture to creamed mixture, then add vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls; flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake about 8 minutes in 350° oven until golden brown.

title: spicy pecans
directions: Mix nuts with other ingredients.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Good for gift giving.

title: almond bark snack
directions: Sift together 3 cups hard work, 4 cups faith in God and 1 cup understanding.
Add 1/2 cup each of self control and discipline. Mix together with 1/2 cup thoughtfulness, 1/2 cup justice and 1/2 cup consideration.
To this, add:
good thoughts, kind words and kind deeds.
Add seasoning:
Tears of joy.
Last fold in 1/2 cup sacrifice, 1 1/2 cups forgiveness, 2 1/2 cups patience and 1 chapter or more of scripture.
Top with 1/4 cup friendship, laughter and good times.
One cup well beaten faults, 3 cups love to sweeten and flavor with prayer.
Simmer in good natured pan, in the heart of kindness.
Keep, cook and serve daily throughout a lifetime.

title: seashell pasta salad
directions: Cook and drain pasta shells.
Cook shrimp.
In a small bowl, combine yogurt, lemon juice, honey, garlic, bouillon and thyme; mix well.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, combine remaining ingredients and shells.
Add yogurt mixture; mix well.
Chill thoroughly.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: peanut butter hard tack(tastes like inside of clark bars)
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients to 300° on candy thermometer; while cooking syrup, grease iron skillet with butter and sprinkle with salt.
Add peanut butter to skillet.
Two people need to work together; one pours syrup mixture into peanut butter slowly, while the other stirs the mixture well.
Mixture will be stiff.
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.
Cut at once into pieces.
Roll into confectioners sugar.

title: chicken-bacon wraps
directions: Wrap 1 slice bacon around each chicken breast.
Put in small cake pan.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with garlic, salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° covered.
Serve with baked potatoes.
Use sauce for gravy.

title: old-fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Mix all together (except nuts and vanilla).
Bring to a rolling boil and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Let cool about 5 minutes; add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion, using medium grater and mix.
Add unbeaten eggs.
Stir until blended.
Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Put enough Crisco in skillet to make about 1/2-inch when melted.
When very hot, spoon in about 1/4 cup potato mixture.
Pat them lightly with a spoon to spread to desired thickness.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Makes 12.

title: grandma's banana pudding
directions: Mix milk, vanilla pudding and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, bananas and vanilla wafers in any type bowl.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.

title: perfect crepes
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Bake in Teflon pan or crepe pan.
Makes a very thin pancake type fritter.
Turn over to cook both sides.
Serve with strawberries and sour cream, maple syrup or whatever flicks your switch.

title: wilted lettuce
directions: Pick fresh lettuce leaves.
Wash carefully and chop about 4 cups of it into a large bowl.
Add 3 or 4 finely chopped young onions and tops and toss mixture lightly.
Fry fat; remove from grease on paper towel.
Let drain.
To fat grease, add 1 teaspoon salt and 2 teaspoons vinegar; stir well.
Heat and pour immediately over lettuce to coat all leaves.
Serve with cornbread and fatback meat.

title: broccoli with lemon and onions
directions: Microwave fresh broccoli pieces on High for 8 to 10 minutes in a 2-quart casserole with 1/2 cup of water.
Cover.
Stir after half the time.
Microwave frozen broccoli spears on High for 8 to 12 minutes in a 2-quart casserole with 1/2 cup of water.
Cover. Stir after half the time.
Combine onion, separated into slices, and butter in small dish.
Microwave on High about 2 1/2 to 5 minutes or until tender.
Stir in lemon juice, lemon peel, salt and pepper.
Drain broccoli.
Spoon lemon butter mixture over top. Sprinkle with Toasted Almonds.
Serves 4.

title: croissants
directions: In large bowl, sprinkle yeast over warm water to soften.
Stir in 1 cup flour, milk, egg, sugar, melted butter and salt.
Beat to make smooth batter.
Set aside.

title: mini cherry cheese cakes
directions: Soften cream cheese; add eggs and beat well.
Add sugar.
Put vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup cake liner.
Fill with cheese mixture 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and top with pie filling.

title: fajitas
directions: Cut meat, onion and peppers into thin strips.
Combine remaining ingredients and add meat, onion and peppers.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Take meat strips out of marinade with tongs.
Grill or broil meat slowly.
Drain marinade and saute peppers and onion in 1 ounce olive oil until crisp-tender.
Serve with 10-inch flour tortillas, sour cream, shredded cheese and picante sauce.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add milk and cook.
Stir over medium heat until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add grated cheese and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Place sliced potatoes in greased casserole.
Add hot cheese sauce.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, under cover, and bake 30 minutes more or until potatoes are done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cheddar apple pizza
directions: Arrange apples in a single layer in a circular pattern to completely cover pastry. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine brown sugar, walnuts, cinnamon and nutmeg and sprinkle over cheese. Cut butter into small pieces and dot top.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Pull apart cookies, scrape icing out, put in Ziploc bag and roll with rolling pin to crush.
Mix pudding and milk.
Refrigerate 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese and Cool Whip with electric mixer. Add pudding.
Assemble by layering cookie crumbs, then pudding and repeat, ending with cookies.

title: peachy cream cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add sweetened condensed milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and extract.
Spread 1/2 filling into pie crust.
Arrange slices of peaches on top of first layer.
Add other 1/2 filling. Garnish with remaining peaches.
(If you choose to also use the cherries, you would then put the cherries on top of the slices of peaches.)
Chill 2 hours.

title: country chicken pie
directions: Boil one fryer; debone and dice.
To broth, add next 3 ingredients.
Add chicken bouillon if a stronger broth is needed. Cook only until vegetables are tender (onions can be added to these vegetables if you choose).
Mix next 3 ingredients into a paste. Add to broth; add diced chicken.

title: millie's marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Drain and cool.
Cut other vegetables and mix with cooled vegetables.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Marinate for at least 12 hours.
Will keep 2 weeks or longer in refrigerator.

title: mediterranean green beans
directions: In a large bowl, whisk the vinegar, mustard, garlic, oregano and pepper.
Add the beans and toss to coat.

title: tea
directions: Make tea in boiling water.
Let steep 15 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients with tea.
Serve over ice.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cover bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with bread cubes.
Cover with browned sausage which has been drained well. Mix remaining ingredients well and pour over bread and sausage.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together sugar, butter, eggs and water.
Gradually add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, salt and vanilla.
Fold in apples, nuts and raisins.
Pour in pans.
Bake at 350° until tester comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: california dip
directions: Mix bean dip and refried beans; spread over a large round plate.
Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over bean mixture.
Spread avocados over this.
Spread Jack and Colby cheese next.
Top with olives, green onions and tomato. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: chicken and pepper trio
directions: Place the chicken in an 8-inch square baking dish. Add 1/2 of the Italian dressing and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour. Heat a large grill pan over high heat until hot. Put chicken in the pan, discarding the marinade; cook 2 to 4 minutes on each side, until meat is no longer pink. Remove chicken; set aside. Add peppers to the pan and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice. Return chicken to the pan, letting it get hot through and through.

title: chocolate cherry thumbprints
directions: Beat sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips, melted.
Mix well.
Stir in oats, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Place 1-inch balls on cookie sheet (ungreased).
Press deep thumbprints in center.
Place cherries in prints.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Drizzle with remaining chocolate chips, melted.

title: orange and pepper pork
directions: Mix all marinade ingredients in a glass bowl.
Cut pork into cubes and submerge in marinade.
Cover and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Skewer and broil, turning once; baste with remaining marinade.
Serve with rice (optional).

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix melted margarine, flour and chopped nuts.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° about 10 minutes or until brown.
Let crust cool.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions and drain. Blend flour, salt, mustard and milk.
Heat, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens a little and is smooth.
Add cheese and heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Combine sauce and macaroni in 2-quart dish and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix lime juice and powdered sugar until well blended; set aside.
Place dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, oil, orange juice, vanilla and lemon extract.
Beat until well blended. Pour batter into greased 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until done.
Remove from oven and let stand in pan 15 minutes. Prick cake all over with a fork.
Drizzle thoroughly with lime juice, mixed with powdered sugar.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add beaten eggs.
Add milk and corn; stir well.
In a 1-quart casserole dish melt the margarine. Turn the dish so the margarine greases the sides, then stir the margarine into the corn mixture and pour everything into the casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes, until browned.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in frying pan and drain. Stir in the salt and pepper and spread in pie plate. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour into pie plate. Bake 25 minutes. Top with 2 sliced tomatoes and the cheese.
Bake until knife comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes). Cool for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.
